#CEUFW FW #25456
 You know what? I 'am tired.
 
 I'm in my third year in this university and things aren't seem what they used to be. Back in high school, I was this go-getter or high achieving type of student. Let's just say that I was happy back then. Entering college, I was fueled with excitement because I picked a course that would suit me since I can't get to study my first choice due to financial incapacities. 
 
 This was 2021, I did not had the experience of doing online classes because of the modular mode in public schools. At first it was nice, almost to what I had during modular mode with the addition of going into online class every once a week. As time passed, deep isolation from people and just focusing on academics took a toll on my sanity. Eating what's left of joy and pride I once had. Many of the easiest works and lessons on canvas became difficult to process and answer. I couldn't help myself during those times, felt loss into the abyss of vast nothingness, forgotten.
 
 As I step into the months ending second year, tensions risen which affected more of my sanity. Everything tearing apart, stepped upon once again. I try everything to keep myself together, I cannot think of my beloved ones loosing the kid with hopes and dreams for his future. Seeing their faces drowning in sorrow as the coffin reach the soil. I just couldn't see it.
 
 CEU made me weak and depressed, an institution that would bring the light upon the students for their futures, instead created an arena where students fight amongst themselves. This battlefield made the students to strive for inflicting to each other baseless and unmannerly behavior amongst each other. Such acts that would tarnish the idea of growing and developing harmonically with each other.
 
 Ending this small story, I'm thankful that I've met friends to support me will my endeavors. I can't name you all here for the sake of privacy, you know who you are once you read this. #PUPFreedomWall16726
 
 Bakit sobrang unfair ng mundo? 
 
 Hello, fellow PUPians! Dito na lang ako magkukwento kasi kahit pati yung sarili ko napapanood na rin kakakinig sa sarili kong problema. 
 
 It has been years since he left me. Pero, yung sakit ng ginawa nila sa akin andito pa rin. Dalang-dala ko pa rin. At, kahit anong gawin ko at kumbinsi ko sarili na okay na, hindi pa rin. 
 
 Yes, he cheater on me with his friend.
 
 Noong nagconfess siya sa akin about sa nangyari, para akong hinati nang pinong-pino. Totoo pala yung mga napapanood sa mga movies ano? Kung grabe yung iyak at mga kagaguhan na gagawin mo 'wag lang maisip ulit 'yon? Kahit na wala ka noong may nangyayari sa kanila, parang andoon ka na sumisigaw pero wala silang naririnig. Ganun yung sakit na nararamdaman ko hanggang ngayon. 
 
 I tried dating naman. Some went along, pero nag-eend dahil i can't fully commit myself dahil sa takot. Factor in pa rito na sobrang pinababa nila yung self-confidence ko, that even me can't fathom seeing myself in front of a mirror. Panget na panget ako sa sarili ko. 
 
 But, the thing is, ang pinakagagalit at insecure ko, masaya sila sa buhay nila, respectively. 
 
 Nabalitaan ko na they are fully committed to their partners na for more than a year na. Masaya na sila sa relasyon nila individually, successful college life rito sa PUP, and have a lot of friends‚Äîmga bagay na pinagkait nila sa akin. 
 
 Lord, bakit ang unfair-unfair mo? Sila yung nananakit sa akin pero sila yung bineblessed mo. Masaya na sila pero ako miserable pa rin. For the second time, nararamdaman kong basura ako na pwede nang iwang miserable kasi i am from their dark past. 
 
 Sana pinatay na lang nila ako kaysa maging ganito kalungkot na araw-araw kinukwestyon ang worth. 
 
 Submitted: March 6, 2024 5:46:32 AM PST

#PUPFreedomWall16724
 
 Kapag natanggal ka sa PL/DL or even latin honors kahit na ginawa mo na yung best mo, may pag-asa ka pa para makabawi. Because hindi mo naman mailalagay sa resume mo yung PL/DL, at kung ilalagay mo ay hindi naman siya relevant for employers unless sa academe ka to some extent, and more importantly, even having a latin honor won't guarantee you in finding a high-paying job. Ang dapat niyong habulin ay skills, work ethics, work experiences, licenses, and certifications. Pero don't get me wrong, magkaiba ang nagpapabaya sa pag-aaral and ginagawa na yung best pero di talaga kaya masungkit ang honors kaya bumabawi sa non-academic factors.
 
 Tandaan, minsan, kung sino pa yung pasang-awa o halos bumagsak sila pa yung mas magaling in actual practice kaysa sa laging nakaka-uno sa klase.

 I met a PUPian guy and he ghosted me after our first meetup tapos nakita ko na nagkaroon ng "masc for masc" yung hanap niya sa bio niya. Hindi ko naman tinago ever na hindi ako masculine, sa chat pa lang. I guess nagkaroon siya ng expectations dahil sa mga pictures ko. I don't know, ang panget lang talaga ng feeling ng ganito. I thought na we had a great time. Kasi nag-enjoy din talaga ako. That was the first time I tried to be with someone after so many years of being single. Kaya siguro ako sobrang apektado kasi I really liked that guy. Nakakadurog lang ng dignidad yung online siya tapos delivered lang lahat ng messages mo. Kadiri, I will never put myself in this position na talaga.
 
 Ang panget lang sa feeling na maghost, okay lang naman sa akin kung sasabihin niya na hindi niya ako gusto, pero now I'm left to think kung anong mali or kulang sa akin because of what he did. Hindi kasi ito yung first time na na ghost ako dahil sa pagiging malambot. Lord bakit and hirap maging bading.
 
 Sa mga pass sa halata diyan, ang oa niyo minsan. Kahit mga straight na lalaki may feminine side. I would consider myself pa nga as masc presenting tapos nararanasan ko na yung ganito paano pa kaya yung ibang mga bading. I just have a weird feeling sa mga bading na pass sa halata or nago-ghost kapag na meet na kasi malambot kumilos. Kahit naman iniiwasan ko na yung mga ganong tao, ang hirap pa rin makahanap ng potential partner na walang internalized homophobia.
 
 I guess it's okay na rin, I wouldn't want to be with someone na hindi gusto yung pagkilos ko. Ang attractive kaya ng taong comfortable sa fem and masc side niya. But still, ang panget sa feeling na ma-ghost.

 A very lengthy and pathetic(?) post ahead, don't read if you don't want something sappy.
 
 I yearned for your presence for the longest time, words can't express how much I wanted to make things work. If only you communicated like you said you would. If I were younger and didn't know any better, perhaps, I would not have known the meaning of 'giving up'. We didn't have a label, and to you, what we 'had' may not have been anything special. But to me: it meant everything‚Äîat the time. I couldn't take the disrespect anymore; I know better than to continue to let you lie to me and ignore me like that. 
 
 I am not stupid. Those five months really made me feel as if I could try love again, it never quite got to that point, but I did have genuine feelings. I didn't lie to you when I said I've never made covers on the guitar for a girl before...I learned how to play the kalimba so that I could maybe help you out with your insomnia; I really am no singer, but I sang my heart out for you. When you wanted to go to an art museum, I saved up all my money and the date still didn't go through because you forgot about it. It really is my fault I got attached way too early, but honestly, could you have blamed me? I don't know if you were just using me to fill the empty void in your heart but you were doing things with me only couples would do. I would wait for you the whole day when you said you were busy, when things came up, I'd let you know and still wait in the dead of the night up until the break of dawn‚Äîeven if it was all for naught.
 
 It hurt me deeply every time I would ask you out on a real date and you would come up with some lame excuse like "I want to stay in" or "I'm gonna use the whole month to catch up with other people in my life,"‚Äîis one day too much?. it pained me even moreso when you'd agree to spend time with me and then I would wait for you after you said yes, only for you to somehow always 'fall asleep'. 
 
 Before my uncle passed away the week that you left without a word, his last memory of me was me telling him "She's the best! She always gets what I'm talking about! For once I feel understood, and she's the most gorgeous woman ever. I hope this works out, and she says she likes me too!‚Äù...I mean? Did you ever really like me? Why would you show me that you liked me and flirted with me constantly? What was the reason?
 
 I guess it's my fault it ended...? I apologize for not being too tall, I apologize for not fitting your aesthetic, pinterest e-boy standards, I apologize I don't offer to let you live in one of my mansions or that I don't drive you around in a Mustang. I tried to, y'know? I exercise daily, I'm doing great in college, I look for work. With the very little money that I save up within a month: I spend it all to look better through clothes or through bodily care products.
 
 I learned my lesson, you can't give more effort to anyone who doesn't truly want you‚Äîit'll still push them away...and sometimes, it's time to let a good thing die. 
 
 Despite all that however, I wish you well,

#PUPFreedomWall16008
 
 MATH
 
 Asignaturang di malilimutan ng mga high school students, at iilang mga mag-aaral sa kolehiyo. Math. Ang isa daw sa mga pinakamahirap na subject kung kaya't may iilang mga tao ang nakatanggap ng mga pagpupuri sa iba. Math. Ang asignaturang may kakayahang baguhin ang isang sikolohiya ng isang tao, mapaano mang edad o status sa buhay. Bata, matanda, magulang, dalaga/binata, may asawa, at pati na mga single. Tama ang nabasa nyo, kasama ang mga single. Sa halos lahat ng ipinanganak sa mundo, sa panahong kasalukuyan, Math ang pinaka-ayaw nilang asignaturang. Bakit? Bakit daw? Bakit naman nila ito kinamumuhian?
 
 Matematika ay isa sa mga pundasyon sa pagpapausbong ng mga unang sibilisasyon sa daigdig. Sa tingin ko true naman, diba. Gayun din naman sa kasalukuyang siglo. Di bat ang matematika rin ang isa sa mga naging sandigan upang lumago at maging mahusay pa ang mga teknolohiya na ginagamit natin sa araw-araw? Oumsim naman diba. 
 
 "Teka lang, ano ba ang punto mo rito? Ano ba ang nais iparating mo sa mga mambabasa?"
 
 Nais ko lang naman ipahiwatig ang aking mga naisip nung nakaraan pang araw. Sa tingin ko, may iba sa atin ay hindi na gaano inaalala ang kahalagahan ng matematika. Isa lang naman itong haka-haka mula sa akin. Napapa-isip rin ako na what if *plays Jopay*, what if magkakaroon tayo ng isang henerasyon na lilimutin ang mga konseptong matimatika nang dahil sa makabagong, o sabihin nating maka-advance na techie?
 
 Calculator, isang kagamitan upang mapabilis ang pagkuha ng sagot sa ninanais mong masagutan na math expressions. Basta ganun yun. Ginagamit rin ito ng karamihan sa mga mag-aaral, lalong-lalo na sa elementarya, sa kanilang pag-aaral sa matematika. What if *plays Jopay again* mas dumedepende na sila dito upang makuha lang ang sagot kaysa alamin at isaisip ang konseptong nakapaloob nito?
 
 MATH, as in
 
 Marinig mo lang, 
 Agad
 Titibok ng mabilis ang
 Heart
 
 Sabi din nila, ang MATH ay isang
 
 Mental
 Abuse
 To
 Humans
 
 Kaya, kinakailangan kumain ng MATH, as in
  
 Merienda
 Agahan
 Tanghalian at
 Hapunan
 
 Pero sa totoo ang, ang MATH
 
 Makes our future
 At
 The
 Highest level
 
 ika nga nila diba. HAHAHAHAHAHAHA. Ang gulo talaga ng isinulat kung ito, pero sana ay naintindihan niyo ang mga sinasambit ko. Mula sa aking haka-haka, ano kaya ang masasabi nyo rito? May napapansin rin ba kayong katulad nito? Sa tingin nyo, ano kaya ang mangyayari kapag hindi natin pinahahalagan ang matematika? At ano kaya ang magagawa nyo upang mapatili ang pagpapahalaga ng matematika sa lahat lalo na sa kabataan ngayon? Ihayag nalang sa comments. Need ko ma-read mga thoughts nyo. Tyia!

Ang circle ko na 'to hindi kami sabay-sabay magreview, tapos 'yung dalawa pa sa amin ay sobrang close to the point na kaming natitira sa circle ay nakakafeel na ng awkwardness lol. Ang hirap talaga maghanap ng circle lalo na kapag online lang kayo nagkakilala. Ang hirap humanap ng mga kaibigan na feel mo belong ka or feel mo na same kayo ng passion and goal. Siguro nag-eexpect lang din ako na sabay-sabay kami mag-aral kasi ganoon ang circle ko noong nasa PUPSHS pa ako tho f2f naman kasi kami noon (Class of 2020). Hindi naman ako makapagsabi sa kanila kasi ayaw ko naman magdemand since may sarili naman silang oras. Parang hindi lang talaga kami connected sa isa't isa.

 Ratings para sa mga colleges na nakalandian ko (as requested ng mga prends)
 
 ‚ÄåCAF - 9/10 gaiz, ang effort. basta ang effort & caring hahaha 
 CAL - 8/10 grabe kayo beh, sobrang nakakaintimidate talino nyo. like araw araw yata lagi kaming nag aaway pero ngl, ang sweet nila lalo mga philo :> masaya rin maging friend kasi ang caring haha
 CBA - 2/10 panget kabonding, pa cool kid tapos malalaman mo pinagsasabay sabay na pala kayo. g r r r kaya pala walang time sayo, kasi hindi mo pa schedule 
 CCIS - 7/10 takteng mga IT yan, ibang codes yung alam tapos lakas pang magrecommend sayo. pero masaya silang kausap, pagiging 'busy' lang talaga kalaban nyo 
 CE - 0/10 TAKTE GHOSTERS TAPOS PURO "MAKA-SCORE" ANG ALAM!! PANGET KA BONDING, PAG TINANGGIHAN MO PARANG IKAW PA MAY KASALANAN SMH!!
 CHK - 8/10 NASA CHK ANG TRAUMA PERO DAHIL BOBO AKO, LABAN LANG HAHAHAHAHA JOKE. pero rt, scary mag jowa ng mga taga rito kasi puro mga babaero lalo na pag athletes. masaya lang sila maging tropa pero jowa??? 50/50. kaya nga pag naloko pa ako ng isang beses, isusumpa ko na talaga college na 'to.
 COC - 4/10 ultimate simp, kukulitin ka for a date then di pa pala ready. pero kung gusto mo ng kachat, lumandi ka ng taga coc haha marami silang topic
 COED - 8/10 sweet at maayos naman 'to, kaso may times na mawwindang ka sakanila kasi yung iba landi ng landi, takot naman sa commitment. (di ako yan ah) 
 CPSPA - 1/10 LAGING WALANG TIME!!!! KAKAUSAPIN KA LANG FOR A WHILE THEN ARAL ULIT. OKAY LANG SANA KUNG PARA SA FUTURE NAMIN EH, KASO PARA SA FUTURE PALA NILA NG GBF NYA. SABI SABI PA NA KAYA AKONG IPAGLABAN KATULAD SA BAYAN PERO IIWAN LANG DIN NAMAN.
 ‚ÄåCS‚Äå - 5/10 masarap makipag study buddy sakanila, marami kang matututunan kaso literal na study first sila. mga after exams lang sila lalandi tapos dedma na ulit. smh
 CSSD - 10/10 HOY BEST DITO T-T aalagaan ka pati na rin mental health mo!! 
 ‚Äå‚ÄåCTHTM - 6/10 sarap makipaglandian dito kasi ang fresh parin nila tapos ako na galing main, haggard na haggard na. medyo dry kausap, puro walwal nga lang magiging topic nyo. sila dapat yung inaalagaan gaiz
 ‚ÄåITECH - ‚Äå0/10!! boring kausap tapos kung san san napupunta yung convo. 
 
 at the end of the day, wala naman talaga yan kung saang college ka belong. nasa tao rin yan, kaya gaiz, guard thy heart para di masyadong masakit hehehe

#PUPFreedomWall15391
 
 "Labas ka, Tignan mo ang mga bituin" 
 
 Ang lagi mong sambit gabi-gabing tayo ay magkausap. Ano bang meron at sa bituin ka naakit? Napakalaki ng buwan at mas maliwanag ngunit nais mo kong tumingin sa bituin. Hindi ba maganda sa iyong paningin ang bawat hugis nito kada linggo? Na syang iilaw sa karimlan ng iyong gabi? Na syang may kakayahang makapagpahuni ng mga nilalang na alam kong gusto mong marinig. Ngunit pinili mong mahalin ang bituin kesa buwan. 
 
 "Ang buwan ay nawawalan ng liwanag sa isang araw, Ngunit ang bituin ay kikinang lagi para sayo" 
 
 Yan ang sagot nya sa akin. Kung sabagay tama sya. Walang liwanag ang bagong buwan. Siguro'y kailangan din ng buwan ang magpahinga. 
 
 "Mas maganda ang bituin dahil naguguhit ko rito ang pangalan mo" 
 
 "Pero kaya mo namang isulat ito sa buwan hindi ba?"
 
 "Ngunit limitado lamang ang sakop na espasyo ng buwan, Ang buong kalangitan ay ang aking Kanbas at mukha mo ang aking paboritong ipinta". 
 
 Maganda nga ang bituin, Ang bituin na hindi mawawalan ng kinang sa kalangitan, Ang bituin na hindi mabibilang at ang bituin na kailanman ay mas kaaya ayang pagmasdan kaysa sa bagong buwan... 
 
 Ngunit paumanhin aking sinta, Alam kong ako ang iyong ipininta ngunit kailanman ay hindi ko pa natitignan ang bituin sa gabi. Hindi ako makalabas, Hindi ako makatakas. Ang oras mo sa pagpinta sa gabi ay nasayang dahil lamang sa hindi ako makalabas upang makita ang iyong obra. At ikay umiyak, At kailanman ay hindi na gumuhit sa kalangitan tuwing gabi. 
 
 Pasensya na, At ngayon ko lang nakita ang bituin. Patawad sinta ko, At aking iginuhit ang iyong wangis sa kalangitan, Kahit wala akong kasiguraduhan na titignan mo rin ang bituin katulad ng dati.

#PUPFreedomWall15308
 
 Masokista siguro ang ibang mga guro ng PUP at gustong-gusto nilang nakikita na pinahihirapan ang mga estudyante. 
 
 Napatatanong ako nitong nakaraan kung ano ang kabayaran sa paghabol at pagkamit ng mga pangarap ng masang estudyante. Does striving for their goal means staking their mental and emotional health in the process? Then, if so, to what type of student are they molding? Are we still preparing them for what lies ahead in the future when we already exhaust their well-being? 
 
 Alam ko na may patuloy na tunggalian sa lipunan and reaching one's goal doesn't come easy. Kailangang lumaban, magpatuloy, at bumangon sa kabila ng maraming pagsubok sa labas at loob ng pamantasan. But that struggle is born out of the capitalist notion of success. That before we succeed, we must first compete and conform to the environment of the academe and society. But my concern is, should we stay like this? To what extent are we turning our students? To heartless unapologetic merciless human beings? 
 
 Ang akin lang, Pamantasan at kaguruan mismo ang gumagabay sa mga estudyante na maging makatao. This is attained through holistic approach of teaching. Ihanda ninyo ang estudyante sa laban sa labas ng pamantasan nang hindi kailangang itaya ng bawat isa ang kanilang sarili sa proseso ng lakbay sa akademya. Prepare them, I mean, to the world by expanding their awareness to their skills while letting them discover their other potentials without hampering them in attaining their internal growth. Empower the students instead of terrorizing them. If they did try to raise some concern regarding the challenges they face in the academe, listen to them and make time to correct what went wrong. Success is achieved through collectivism. Hindi kailanman ito nakakamit when we set high walls between educators and students. Boundaries are in default, mind you. Pero kailangang tandaan na nakakamit ang tagumpay when we learn to settle our differences and when we empower everyone to things they are not capable of. Ang edukasyon ay kailangang maging makamasa at demokratiko. Wala akong naaalala sa pagkabata na ang edukasyon ay kailangang maging instrumento na pupuksa sa mag-aaral na mangarap at magpatuloy. Sinasabi niyo nga na it is the key to success. But how can it be the key when education extinguishes the fire of passion, hope, and dream of the students that burns with them? 
 
 I aspire to be an educator and a lawyer someday. At kailanman hindi ko gaganyanin ang mga estudyante ko. I will help them in dealing with their challenges than left them struggling, anxious, and burnt out. 
 
 PUP CPSPA

Pinadpad ako ng tadhana rito, ngunit hindi na nya ako kayang ibalik sa nakaraan. Sa pagnanais kong balikan ang alaalang iyon, marami akong pinalampas na pagkakataon sa kasalukuyan. Hindi kita masisisi, at hinding hindi kita kayang sisihin dahil kung titignan, isa lang akong parte ng iyong kahapon. 
 
 Hindi ako naging kabanata, bagkus ako ay isang talababa lamang sa istorya ng buhay mo. Pilitin ko man na isalin ang kuwento mo sa sarili kong paksa, hinding hindi tayo pwedeng magtugma. Nakulong ako sa nakaraan, at pasensya ngunit kahit anong pilit ko ay hindi ko kayang bumitaw, kahit alaala na lang ang pinanghahawakan ko.

 6 figure salary or studies?

#PUPFreedomWall14468
 
 PUP used to be my dream school. Not anymore.
 
 Dumating ako sa PUP as a student with high hopes na I would be happier learning here than my previous school. Pero eventually, malalaman mo talagang walang perfect school. Okay sana kung sinusubukan maging better in terms ng learning e, pero hindi. Better in appearance lang. 
 
 Sa department namin, okay naman talaga in general. Better dito than some departments based sa naririnig ko. Salamat sa previous chairperson namin na ginawa ang best niya para maging conducive ang learning. Sa professors, wala depende talaga eh. May iba na halata mong passion at nageeffort talaga kaya madami ka natututunan. May ibang parang umay na umay at ginagawa na lang ang bagay-bagay para sa kumita. Kung ikaw yung prof na latter, please lang po, wag niyo na po idamay edukasyon ng mga iskolar sa kapaguran o katamaran niyo. 
 
 Kung usapang school system? As in PUP in general? Wala talaga. Sobrang nakakahiya. Ang registrars/accountants masusungit. Hindi filtered ng maayos ang professors. Facilities bago gibain, di ka makaka-CR ng maayos. I doubt kasama yun sa aayusin, kasi walang CR sa part na giniba (If I'm seeing it correctly). Kita niyo naman pati paano sila nag-adapt sa pandemic, painfully incompetent compared to other schools. Realtalk lang. Yung iba may F2F na, sila ang dami pang ibang priority. Parang di nila priority yung welfare ng mg studyante mismo o kung matututo nga ba, inuna pa yung building na binuo kung kailan F2F na supposedly. 
 
 Pero ito talaga yung last straw. Up to my last day in PUP disappointed pa rin ako. Imagine, parang tinipid na nga kasi sa PUP Gym lang (willing naman kami magbayad kung PICC man lang), hindi ka na nga kasama sa latin honors kahit qualified ka kasi transferee ka, hindi pa makakamartsa magulang mo, kahit man lang sa processional. OA siguro para sa inyo, pero imagine, pinag-aral ka ng magulang mo tapos sa graduation mo wala naman pala sila gagawin, kahit mag-martsa man lang. Doon na nga lang sila magkaka-sense of pride somehow, at ganun naman talaga usual na mangyari, pero kahit yun pinagkait samin. My sibling asked me "bakit hindi niyo nireklamo?" Nalaman na lang namin noong practice na, which is days away from graduating. 
 
 Gagraduate na nga lang kami, pakiramdam pa namin pinapahiya pa kami. Pinag-aral din naman kami ng magulang namin kaya pareho lang sana dapat ng privilege, kahit dun man lang. Ang sakit ipamalita sa kanila na wala silang gagawin. Pakiramdam namin outsider kami sa sarili naming paaralan. Nakakasama ng loob. 
 
 Siguro kung may kakilala man ako at pipili siya ng university, ididiscourage ko na lang mag-PUP. Bakit? Kasi habang tumatagal, walang nasa taas na nag-aayos ng sistema. kung ganito pa rin ka-uncaring ang PUP sa mga mag-aaral, wag na lang kayo dito.
 
 StuDEAD
 PUP Main

 Bilang isang freshie sa ilalim ng CAF Department, pumasok ako sa paaaralang ito nang may mataas at matayog na pangarap, ang makapagtapos ng BSA at gumraduate nang may Latin honors. Unfortunately, unang semestre pa lamang, tinanggalan na ako ng pag-asang makamit ito dahil sa 2.75 na marka sa aking major subject. Masakit? Oo. Dahil alam ko sa sarili kong mas deserve ko ng mas mataas na grado. Ngunit mas masakit na tila ba walang pakialam sa amin ang professor namin lalo na't siya ang dean ng aming department. 
 
 Labis ang galit na aking nadarama hanggang sa ngayon dahil sa naging karanasan ko sa unang semestre. Naranasan niyo na bang mag-aral na walang kasiguraduhan kung tama ang iyong ginagawa dahil lamang walang guro ang gagabay sayo? Naranasan mo na bang umattend ng synchronous class kung saan ang professor mismo ang hindi sigurado sa kaniyang itinuturo? Naranasan mo na bang magmakaawa at maghintay ng matagal na oras makamit lamang ang reply ng iyong guro patungkol sa iyong hinaing? Kung hindi pa ay maswerte ka dahil kung naging handle ka ni dean ay malamang dalawa na tayong umiiyak hanggang ngayon. 
 
 PUP aming gabay, hiling ko'y sana ngayong panahon ng pandemya ay tulungan niyo ang bawat estudyante ninyong makamit ang hangarin naming kaligayahan na masilayan ang pag-asang makakapagtapos kami ng may Latin honors sa pamamagitan ng pagbago ng inyong standards. Hindi sapat at kakarampot ang aming natututunan sa bawat synchronous at asynchronous classes namin. Pakinggan ninyo kami sapagkat alam kong nagsisikap ang lahat upang makamit ang ginintuang tagumpay na ito.

 Para sa mga working-students gaya ko.
 
 Alam kong deserve nating makapagpahinga. Pero kung hindi natin kayang isakripisyo ang pahinga habang pinagsasabay ang pag-aaral at pagtatrabaho, mas mainam kung piliin na lang muna ang mas importante sa dalawa base sa kasalukuyang kalagayan, kasi hindi naman tungkol sa bilis ng pagtatapos ng pag-aaral o pag-asenso ang karera ng buhay.
 
 Hindi na kasi patas para sa mga working-student gaya ko, na nagsasakripisyo ng tulog para lang magampanan ang dalawang responsibilidad, ang makita ang ibang working-students na tanging trabaho na lang ang iniintindi.
 
 Sobrang bigat ng semestre na ito para sa akin. Sa kagustuhan kong pairalin ang pagkahabag sa mga kapwa ko working-students, nakalimutan kong dapat ko rin pala itong bigyang limitasyon. Hindi ko maiwasang sumama ang loob dahil napagtanto ko na ang mga nilaan kong oras sa pag-aaral, matapos ang nakakapagod na trabaho, ay katumbas ng pahinga nila. Maraming pagkakataong ako na lamang ang gumagawa ng mga pangkat na gawain. May mga pagkakataon ding nagbubulag-bulagan na lang ako sa nangyayari kahit alam kong naglalaro o naggagala lamang sila pagtapos ng trabaho. Ito ay sa kadahilanang may parte pa rin sa akin na ayaw kong ipagkait ang kasiyahan sa kanila.
 
 Ayaw ko na sanang paabutin pa ito rito dahil ayaw kong kaawaan. Wala na kasing espasyo sa dibdib ko para sa mga hindi pagkakaunawaan kaya sa tingin ko'y sapat nang dito ko ito sabihin.
 
 Minsan, sa kamamadali natin sa karera ng buhay, hindi natin namamalayang nakapapatid na pala tayo ng iba.
 
 Nawa'y matutunan din nating bumuo ng pansariling desisyong hindi makaaapekto nang malaki sa ibang tao.

#PUPFreedomWall14038
 
 In response with #PUPFreedomWall13936
 
 Hi, matagal ng usapin ang retention policy sa CAF. Marami na rin ang mga estudyanteng tumindig laban dito. Pero bakit nga ba eto naging anti-student? Unang una ang system sa CAF ay hindi ginawa para gawing emotionally at physically strong ang mga students gaya ng sinasabi mo. Ang mga policies gaya ng Dos Policy at Retention na pinapatupad ng Accountancy Dept ay discriminative at anti-student kasi hindi nito napagtutuunan ng pansin yung level ng pagkatuto ng bawat estudyante. Pinatupad ito para 'salain' ang bilang ng mga students na mag-advance sa mga susunod na taon. Ito ay sagot nila sa lumiliit na budget ng edukasyon sa mga SUCs at hindi nito naa-accommodate yung tunay na pangangailangan ng kolehiyo/university, which is yung quality education at sapat na budget. Dahil dito nawawalan ng academic freedom ang mga students na makapagtapos sa napili nilang program.
 Pangalawa lehitimo yung pagtingin ng mga isko na wala talagang sense yung evals na maging basehan para makagraduate. Apat na taon ka ng nasa program, dapat yung evals ay maging gauge na lang ng college para idetermine yung magiging kahinaan ng mga students sa magiging board exam at ito dapat yung pagtutuunan ng pansin ng mga prof sa susunod.
 Pangatlo, very pressing issue din na dahil may retention policy sa CAF matatanggal sa roster ng free education ang isang isko kapag natanggal siya sa BSA o sa kahit na anong program na may ganito ring policy. Sa huli, mapipilitan na pa ang isang student, na natanggal na nga sa gusto nilang program, na saluhin yung burden sa pagbabayad ng tuition.
 Panghuli, the fact na kinikwestyon mo yung hinaing ng nakararami shows na iniinvalidate mo sila. Actually mas dapat ngang pagtuunan ng pansin ang mga issue na ito dahil majority yung tinatamaan. Wala namang tamad na student o tao, yung system yung nagtutulak para maging ganoon sila. Syempre sino ba naman di mawawalan ng pag-asa at motivation kung nakikita nila na mababaliwala lang effort nila at the end of the day diba? Kasi kung titignan natin ang nangyayari, wala ng pake yung admin sa struggle na kinakaharap ng mga nasasakupan nito. Naging bulag at secluded sila sa realities ng mga studyante nila.
 Huwag natin isisi sa mga estudyante yung dapat na responsibility ng admin. Hindi dapat maging dahilan ang kahit anong method of learning (e.g. online, f2f) para maging inhumane ang mga exams. In the first place kung maganda yung curriculum at totoong may objective na matuto ang lahat equally edi hindi na magkokopyahan ang mga students gaya ng ini-insinuate mo. Dapat nga mas compassionate ang mga prof sa mga ganitong circumstances. Huwag tayong elitista.
 
 CAF SC '16-'17
 
 Submitted: July 31, 2022 10:03:14 PM +08

May kasungitan din sya at tahimik lang pero may laman kapag nagbabahagi siya ng thoughts niya. Hindi ko lang din alam kung anong sogie nya. Wala naman akong lakas ng loob alamin dahil nakakahiya at baka mamisinterpret kapag online. 
 
 Hindi ko alam kung paano ko sasabihin sa kaniya lahat ng bagay na gusto ko sa kanya. Gusto ko kapag bigla siyang napapangiti, sobrang genuine ng smile niya. Gusto ko yung tahimik lang siya sa gilid pero alam kong ang dami ng tumatakbo sa isip niya. Gusto ko yung mga mata nya kahit na alam kong nasa sulok lang ako nun. Gusto ko rin yung minsan parang ang sungit niya bigla. Wala lang, siguro ang korni pero hindi naman sapat na batayan ang mga bagay na yan para ijustify at mapatunayan na gusto ko sya dahil gusto ko pa syang makilala. 
 
 Actually, ngayon ay magkaibigan kami. Tinuturing ko syang kaibigan pero hindi ko alam kung kaibigan din ba ang turing niya sa akin. Feeling ko kasi sya yung tipo ng tao na hindi madaling magtiwala. Mas mahirap pala pag kinaibigan mo yung crush mo. Mas mag-aassume ka sa mga bagay na ginagawa niya sayo. Yung tipong kahit wala namang ibig sabihin, may dahilan ka para bigyan ng ibig sabihin kasi magkaibigan kayo. Gets ba? Ang gulo. 
 
 Gagraduate na kami, malapit na. Isang taon na lang. Pero hindi ko alam kung sasabihin ko ba 'tong nararamdaman ko. Every time na magkakasama kasi kami nandun yung nararamdaman ko yung tension. May ilang. Hindi kami magkadikit sa mga litrato, hindi namin magawang magtabi, at hindi namin magawang magkatinginan. Hindi ko alam, baka hindi nya lang talaga ako gusto at nakakahalata na sya. Hindi ko rin alam baka nararamdaman nya ang tensyon sa pagitan naming dalawa. 
 
 Sana magkaroon ako ng lakas ng loob na sabihin ang lahat. Kasi malapit na akong sumuko sa isang bagay na hindi pa naman nagsisimula at mukhang hindi naman talaga magsisimula -- ang tayo.

 Okay, BSA student here. Just came here to rant a bit. I have known someone from one of my blockmates who's really passionate about our course. Sobra niyang galing and sobra niyang sipag sa lahat ng activities. It's safe to say that they really deserve to get a spot in BSA considering how they manage to get by thru sheer hardwork and perseverance.
 
 Pero to be honest, dahil sa pandemic na 'to, I could see their resolve wavering a bit. Napansin ko rin na may mga hesitations na sa mga kilos niya as if they are now doubting their capabilities. There are just so many factors that hinder the students to show their full potential.
 
 It's quite saddening to say the least dahil alam ko na isa siya sa mga sure board passers sa CPALE if ever. And now they're so unsure kung itutuloy pa nila itong course. And to be honest, gano'n na rin ako. I'm starting to doubt myself too. 
 
 I know, I can do this. Alam ko na kaya ko tong course na to if it wasn't for this pandemic. I know my capabilities and I know that I can manage kung face-to-face ang method natin. 
 
 The responsibility from your family, financial problems, and the pressure from the academe are taking a toll on my mental health. I am barely holding on sa course na to. But there's only so much I can take. 
 
 Some of you may think that this is my choice and that I have to face the consequences of my decisions. That's true. This is my choice and my dream has always been set to becoming a CPA eversince. I never regret taking this course, I just think that taking this course in the midst of health crisis could somehow extinguish your spark and blur your dream of being a CPA incessantly. 
 
 Sobrang nakakalungkot lang. Parang hinihintay ko na lang talaga ang sarili ko na maburn-out before admitting defeat. I also consider transferring but practical reasons befell me; I want to graduate on time to support my hardworking parents. (This is my personal choice)
 
 And now, I am just hoping na sana makaya ko despite my struggles accumulating as time goes by. And if ever makarating man sa CAF itong rant ko, I am deeply hoping for them to somehow lighten the academic pressure. Sobrang nakaka-anxious lang 'yung retention policy. Kahit na mediyo nam-maintain ko naman kahit papano, it still affects my mental health dahil sa pressure na nakukuha namin and 'yung thought that my dream will go down the drain once I failed, scares me so much. Im just hoping for a chill yet productive environment habang pandemic pa. Dahil kung di ko man matapos ang course na to, for sure, itong course ang tatapos sa'kin. 
 
 That's all I want to say. Padayon to us „Ö° isko at iska ng bayan!

Hindi ba dapat sa mga ganyang situation nagsisimula yung pagsasapraktika ng mga natutunan ninyo sa mga taong nag-aaral kayo ng historiograpiya at historical methods? Makukulong ba kayo kapag nagkondena kayo sa halalang pinatakbo ng makinarya ng disimpormasyon at kasinungalingan? Magaling lang kayo magbunganga sa mga social media accounts ninyo pero hindi ninyo magamit ang SMK bilang kolektibong pagtatanggol ng Kasaysayang binababoy. Mahilig kayo magkabit ng mga taguri sa sarili nyo bilang mga "radikal" at "militante" pero hindi niyo magawang i-"bypass" ang konsti nyo na nagpapanatili sa status quo ng pagiging pipi ng SMK. 
 
 Kung tutuusin nga, matagal na ninyong hindi sinusunod ang Konstitusyon ninyo dahil maraming provisions especially sa Article IV ang hindi naman naisasakatuparan. At hindi ba't ang bolo at kalasag sa inyong logo, ayon na rin sa Article III Sec. 1 ay nangangahulugan na ang PUP SMK ay may tungkuling ipagtanggol at pangalagaan ang Kasaysayan? Bakit hindi niyo magawa ang responsibilidad na ito? Takot kayong malabag ang Konstitusyon sa pagiging "pulitikal," yet hindi niyo magampanan ang tungkuling iniaatang ng Konstitusyon ding ito?  Pangalawa, kung ang pag-amyenda pala sa Konstitusyon nyo ay hindi nyo magawa dahil sa maraming academic requirements na kailangang gawin, edi sana 'yung ginagawa nyong pagdaldal sa social media accounts nyo ay inilaan niyo na lang sana sa pagsasagawa ng mga online meeting at caucus para sa pagbabago ng konstitustyon. Actually, ang daming officers nyo ang nagkakalat ng kung ano anong cringiness sa social media. Kung may time kayong magkalat sa social media, sana may time din kayo para ayusin ang consti.
 
 Lastly, sana alam niyo na nagawa ang konsti na iyan sa panahon na si Mcdo Pascual pa ang tagapayo ng SMK. At malamang sa malamang, may mga interes yang chismosong kalbo na iyan na isiningit niya sa konstitusyon ninyo para sa panahon ng matinding krisis pangkasaysayan ay maging pipi kayo't walang silbi.

 Never believe a suicidal person. 
 
 I had a boyfriend of two years. Our relationship was far from ideal as it revolved around fear. He told me he was suicidal, and that I should not let go of him because when I do, he'll probably kill himself. I tried hard to understand, but he used suicide as a free pass to cheat on me and ignore me. 
 
 I cried every night wondering where I went wrong and why am I being treated like trash. It took a toll on my mental health; I had insomnia and I can barely focus on my studies while he is out there, cheating on me with every girl he meets in Omegle. After I ended that relationship, I realized 2 things. 
 
 1. Don't pressure yourself to be there for someone who's suicidal. It is never your responsibility to help people who don't want to help themselves.
 2. Don't hesistate to leave people who tells you that they will kill themselves if you left. Manipulative people will use suicide to manipulate you into staying in a toxic relationship. It may be true, it may be not, but at least you will get to free yourself from the pressure and pain that they are giving. It's not worth to take their place.

#PUPFreedomWall13176
 
 Pressured. Lost.
 
 Have you ever felt lost? or just got lost all of a sudden? Masaya ka lang kanina tapos biglang naramdaman mo na hindi mo na alam ang gagawin mo, ano uunahin mo, ano ba ang susundin mo muna. 
 
 I'm a working student. Of course, kapag working student ka, matic na ubos oras mo sa trabaho o di kaya sa acads naman. Sobrang dalang na magka time ka para matulog. I also only have two days off sa work, sometimes three, depending sa utos ng boss. Pero kahit na may day off ako, hindi ko pa rin naeenjoy yun dahil sa mga gawain sa bahay. Gusto mong magpahinga dahil sa pagod pero dahil isa akong "mabuti at masunuring anak", ako lagi ang utusan nila. Ako ang mamamalengke, ako ang magluluto ng lunch at dinner namin.
 
 I have siblings, but none of them are useful. Bakit kamo? Kahit na utos utusan sila, ang lagi nalang sabi ay "mamaya na" kahit na nakahiga lang naman at nagcecellphone, hanggang sa nakalayas na hindi na nagawang maghugas ng pinggan o ligpitin ang gamit. Ang ending, ako pa ang maghuhugas para sa kanila, ako pa ang makakatanggap ng talak ng magulang kasi marumi ang bahay lalo na ang lababo sa dami ng hugasin. Lagi nilang sinasabi, "may trabaho na ako, ikaw nagaaral lang kaya ikaw na diyan". Are they dumb? I pretty sure that they know that college life isn't as easy as it seems. Kaya nga sila hindi nagtapos ng pag-aaral. 
 
 Studying is not easy as it seems. Lalo kung nagtatrabaho ka pa at the same time. But they don't get it, they will never understand it. Ang mahirap pa, hindi ako makaangal dahil ayaw ko ng away. Kaya madalas katulong ako sa umaga, mag-aaral naman sa gabi. 
 
 My parents always tell me that I'm their only hope, ako nalang ang nagiisang anak na maaasahan nilang makakapagtapos. They always say na kahit maghigpit sila ng sobra sa akin ay gagawin nila para lang makapagtapos ako. What my older siblings did to their lives affected me so much. I just wanted to have a good life. Hindi yung pinepressure ako na gawin ko to gawin ko yan kasi hindi nila nagawa. It's not my fault though. It's their decision in life, not mine. Paano nalang kapag sinabi kong pagod na ako mag-aral? Would they let me stop? Of course, no. They will still force me to study kahit sobrang pagod ko na, sobra na mental breakdown ko, my anxiety keeps getting worse, and the pressure that I always feel tuwing matutulog at paggising. Ang bigat sa pakiramdam yung kahit na sabihin nilang hindi nila need ng mataas na grades, passing grades are enough, thinking that they are now good parents kasi hindi nila ako pinepressure na pataasin yung grades. Pero pinipilit nga lang na mag-aral.
 
 Kapagod lang talaga promise.
 
 ps. medyo broken pa ako kasi taken na si ken.
 
 - pagudtom ng educ

#PUPFreedomWall13080
 
 This is the last time that I'll write to you.
 
 I'm never a fan of goodbyes. I don't even say that when I part with other people. 
 
 I never say it unless I know that I'll never see them again.
 
 And maybe that's how it is for us.
 
 So this is my farewell.
 
 To the places we've been to- from where it all started to where it ended.
 
 I will walk through them again without a heavy heart.
 
 To our songs- your recommendations and to those that remind me of you.
 
 I will enjoy it without your trace; the words in it won't pertain to you anymore.
 
 To the photos we took together- it wasn't a lot but it meant so much.
 
 I will still wear the same smile and happiness even without you.
 
 To your corner in my journal- where I wrote our firsts and our bucket list.
 
 I will finally move forward without the thought of your return that held me back.
 
 To your friends- whose energies I love.
 
 To the conversations we had- meaningful or meaningless.
 
 To these feelings I have- love, from its joy to the pain.
 
 For my peace.
 
 Now is the time I finally close our book.
 
 This is the end of us, and my new beginning.

#PUPFreedomWall12970
 
 Paki-basa lalo na kung COCian ka dahil observation ko ito sa student council natin. 
 
 Ngayong natapos ang sem, nakita ko rin talaga iyong pagkakaiba ng student council noon at ngayon. May negative at positive akong observation. Simulan siguro natin sa positive dahil mas marami naman talagang positive observations. 
 
 Yung una, sobrang consultative talaga ng council ngayon. Kahit wala namang consultation or yung commustahan ba yun naming mga class reps. Kinakamusta talaga ako ng mga officers kahit on a normal day para lang makamusta yung naging daloy ng araw ng klase namin. Pangalawa, responsive sila sa mga concerns. So far, nareresolve naman lahat ng concern ng sections namin. At isa talaga sa mga naappreciate ko sa kanila ay kapag may concern kami sa prof, nandun talaga ang guidance. Unlike before na idk parang laging sinasabi na wala kaming laban sa mga prof. Tsaka sobra yung pagpaparticipate at pakikiisa nila sa mga relevant campaigns inside or outside the university. Lagi rin kaming inuupdate sa mga nagiging actions nila regarding our concerns. Evident din na lagi nila kaming isinasama sa mga pinaglalaban namin as community like LBE, yung sa NTFELCAC, redtagging atbp. Observe ko rin na hindi lang talaga sila gumagawa through online. Siguro magandang example na nagkakaroon sila ng consultation sa mga guards and janitors tapos nagpapaabot na rin sila ng kaunting tulong. Katulad nung mga sinabi nila sa campaign magkakaroon talaga sila ng actions na outside the university. Siguro, well-appreciated din iyong pagsama sa mga rally to represent us, gusto ko nga rin minsang jumoin kaso nakakahiyang magreachout. 
 
 Siguro yung negative lang na masasabi ko yung makulit talaga sila minsan magmessage lalo na kung may urgent na agenda sila na kailangan naming tumugon as class reps. Guilty naman ako na minsan na hindi ako nakakareply agad pero siguro somehow positive, kasi dun mo makikita iyong pagiging consultative nila at yung sense of urgency nila. Siguro yung isa pa yung webinars medyo onti pa lang ata unlike nung last council pero okay lang naman lalo na kung di naman nagbebenefit ang mga students. Mas okay pa rin para sakin yung SC na tumitindig sa laban namin, nakikinig sa amin, at gumagawa ng relevant action para sa amin. 
 
 To conclude, (wow essay? haha) sobrang iba ng council noon sa ngayon. Kung irarate ang council ngayon, siguro 9/10. Siguro dahil may mga comments akong negative. Pero sa ngayon, sobrang dama ko sila. Kung anuman ang nasabi nila nung campaign nila, nagagawa nila. Sana same observation din ito mula sa mga ka-college ko. Deserve din naman ng SC ng appreciation dahil parang di sila nagpapahinga. :)

#PUPFreedomWall12805
 
 So are you also like me who's confused like what course is right and designed for me?
 
 Worry not cause here are 10 Criteria in choosing the right course for you. Thank me later hehe
 
 1. Passion 
 
 Basically what you enjoy during your free time. 
 
 You can't choose a course that you don't love and enjoy. You're just torturing yourself.
 
 For example: gaming, photography, painting/drawing, writing, playing instruments etc.
 
 Passion has been downplayed by many content creators, articles, friends, even my parents. Simply for the reason 'it wasn't sustainable' 
 
 Pano kung nawalan ka na ng passion is the popular question but hear me on this 
 
 Mawawalan ka talaga ng passion if 
 
 a. You didn't know the purpose why you are doing things
 b. You don't make plans and follow it
 c. You don't make adjustments on your work and see where you got it wrong
 c. You don't manage your expectations 
 d. You don't take breaks
 e. You receive negative feedback
 f. That's why it's important that you have someone who supports you, believes in you, corrects you, build you up and not putting you down
 
 2. Creativity 
 
 You need this cause a lot things in college you need to be original, passionate, nakakasabay at least. Yes pede kang kumuha ng inspiration sa iba but never copy their work
 
 Creativity happens if you experience bigla bigla nalang may mga ideas popping inside your head and you wanted to experiment them
 
 Now creativity doesn't always equate to art. You can be creative on your routine, room setup, thesis, essays
 
 Rule of a thumb:
 
 a. You need to try things out and explore. Malay mo maenjoy mo ung mga bagay na yun and you're gonna have passion for it. If not, try out other things
 
 b. You always ask yourself these questions
 b1. How can I be more efficient in solving problems 
 b2. In what ways can I be more effective
 b3. In what ways can I make my design more beautiful 
 
 Basically you're creating new ideas, ways or concepts to enhance your work, to reinforce both structures or processes, to be more efficient
 
 3. Focus on your strengths and personality/Research your course
 
 San ka ba magaling? 
 
 Now each strands corresponds to your strengths and personality right?
 
 Humanities and Social Sciences (HUMSS) 
 If love involving yourself to people, solving society's problems, teaching, debating, making policies, understanding person's behavior leading a certain organization, public relations etc. then HUMMS is for you
 
 Science, Technology, Engineering, and Math (STEM)
 If you love experiments, discovering wonders of the world and the universe, creating inventions, analyzing numbers or being in the medical field. Then this strand is for you
 
 Accounting, Business and Management (ABM)
 If you‚Äôre dreaming of working in the corporate world, go for the ABM strand. This strand will help you become a business leader or an entrepreneur
 
 General Academic Strand (GAS)
  If you‚Äôre still unsure and want to keep your options open, the GAS strand is for you. This strand includes courses related to all other strands. These said, you‚Äôll have the advantage of exploring different interests you have in mind. GAS strand courses and subjects include Social Sciences, Disaster Preparedness, Humanities, and the like
 
 2. Technical-Vocational-Livelihood Track (TVL)
 TVL is about practical skills that will prepare you right on the job but there specializations kung saan mo ba talaga gusto
 
 List of TVL track strands:
 ICT, Home Economics Strand, Agri-Fishery Arts Strand ,Industrial Arts
 
 3. Arts and Design Track
 Pursuing your passion is one of the greatest joys in life. So, if you‚Äôre into arts and want to further hone your skills and creativity, this track is for you. In this track, you‚Äôll learn subjects related to dance, music, theater, photography, media, and visual arts
 
 4. Sports Track - If you love involving yourself to sports then sports track is for you
 
 3. Purpose
 
 This topic is very difficult, complex, and broad for some/most that needs deep thinking for a considerable amount of time to determine what you want to do in the future and what makes your life meaningful
 
 While recounting and making sense of your past experiences, why did you make those kind of decisions, what you could have done to lessen those regrets, what decisions you need to make now to prevent those regrets from happening repeatedly. At least you can expect something good will happen in your life
 
 But what makes this existential questions hard to answer is not all of us are living in good conditions. Some of us are living on small spaces with little money on hand just trying to survive their day to day life. Some have lump sums of money and yet they aren't satisfied at all. Some have ridiculously strict parents that they haven't experience eating on a fast food or walking down city streets savoring the sceneries, Some are single parents and they have to study at the same time. In fact this is just a little fraction of what reality is‚Äîthat life isn't the same for us all 
  
 That's why I'm writing this career guide because I dropped out of college. I didn't have someone who would give me these guidelines of what course is right for me. This is my purpose to help other people who are confused in life
 
 Now to answer your question
 
 a. Think of something that deeply influences you or affects you. Tulad nung nangyari sakin
 b. You could intersect your passion unto these things. Whether that's art, music, film you could tell your own story.
 c. If not be part of an organization to solve that problem
 d. Have friends who will listen and support you. Mahirap maging echo chamber. You only listen to your voice.
 e. What do you value? What's your personality? What do you want to achieve or see in the future?
 d. Learn from other people and continue to grow
 
 4. Financial Capabilities 
 
 There are courses na magastos and it depends sa University that you will study. So you have to consider that
 
 Budgeting plan for your bills if you gonna live by yourself:
 Dorm or condo, pagkain mo sa araw araw, laundry, school materials, school fees, transportation, data plan or internet plan and many other things
 
 Otherwise if you're a working student or living in your parent‚Äôs/relatives house you can work things out namn
 
 5. Minimum Grade Requirements/Scholarship Grants
 
 Some courses have these minimum grade requirements. This shows the level of difficulty when you are in class
 
 If you're not financially capable don't lose hope. Meron pang scholarship grants that's why "You need to work harder but study smarter"
 
 6. Ask and Learn from others about the University that you will choose. Make sure to look for students' reviews online also but be analytical if their reviews are valid
 
 Since you‚Äôre freshmen. Sanayin nyo na sarili nyo to ask questions but ask the right ones. If you're confused then point out san ka nalilito. Hindi yung manghuhula kami. Nakakastress din minsan pero understandable namn since ganyan kami before lol
 
 There are some universities that excel in that particular kind of course. You have to look at their achievements as a basis for the quality of graduates they produce
 
 You also have to ask about the living realities when studying in that University. Karamihan sa nababasa ko sa Freedom Wall of each universities. Meron mga rants about the poor quality of professors teaching them. It shows the university's poor management, quality control, the type and frequency of professors they employ for the job. If these Universities show a poor track record on how they treat their students. Then it‚Äôs up to you if you can manage those disadvantages otherwise lipat ka nlng
 
 But there are positive one‚Äôs like being part of organizations, having crushes on your blockmates, having meaningful class discussions even though it‚Äôs online, professors who are very understanding to their students, etc.
 
 You can check out their main websites or other websites that talk about their reputation
 
 https://www.topuniversities.com/
 https://www.timeshighereducation.com/
 https://www.thecampusadvisor.com/philippines
 https://ph.indeed.com/cmp/De-La-Salle-University/reviews (employees review)
 
 7. Learn Life Skills/ Study Techniques 
 
 This is one of the most important things that you will need in every aspect of your life
 
 https://www.skillsyouneed.com/general/life-skills.html
 
 Just search in Youtube Study Techniques there are a lot of contents there. (Especially for Med students)
 
 Mas mapapadali studies and trabaho nyo if you invest on these skills
 
 8. Do you see yourself belonging and growing in the course you choose? 
 
 You need to ask yourself this question during all the planning and preparing kac this is a major life decision and commitment that shouldn't be decided on a whim
 
 Try consulting from experts on the field and see if you're really fit for the course. Their years of insight as a practitioner will help you on your journey
 
 9. Career Opportunities/Salary 
 
 At the end of it all, we have to face the reality that there are some careers na mababa sweldo dito. Due to the fact that our country experienced several economic crisis, debts, corruption, etc. 
 
 If you want to fly high butterfly then Paro Paro G overseas because here in the Philippines you have to work 2-3 times as hard and smart apart from everybody else if you want a stable future and hindi ka lang dependent sa current salary and benefits na makukuha mo
 
 You could never be totally confident na magiging chill lang lahat. Gaya nitong pandemic marami na layoffs and bagsak ang economy natin
 
 10. Pray, Ask Wisdom from God and others
 
 Even today I also struggle though I have already clear options to choose from
 
 Do I choose my passion for film and writing or my purpose in the academia?
 
 That's why I ask for wisdom and guidance. I just don't want to have regrets
 
 Goodluck sa inyo lahat!!
 
 - Jaime

#PUPFreedomWall12715
 
 I've been understanding and tolerating a lot of things. Siguro naman deserve ko nang mag walk away sa sobrang pagod.
 
 Most of the time sinasabi ko na okay lang, na naintindihan ko naman pero siguro naghalo halo na kaya sumabog na talaga ako.
 
 For a long time, I've been talking to myself, saying na may problema kasi sila kaya pabayaan mo na,baka busy pa, ikaw na muna, intindihin mo nalang, make sure mo na magaan ibibigay mo sakanila, kamustahin mo then sendan mo ng short message or notes to lift their mood pero these days sobrang pagod na talaga ako na hindi ko na ma justify mga actions nilaand siguro I've been craving for the things that I do din. Gusto ko din ma baby, gusto ko din maintindi. Gusto ko din ng sweet affirmation. 
 
 Sa ngayon, maglalabas muna ako ng sama ng loob:
 
 1 [I've been giving timelines, deadlines, instructions, nagtatanong din ako kung malabo ba o may tanong sila, sinasabi ko din na they can approach me para maayos kung ano man yung dapat maayos/matama. Ginawa ko naman kung ano yung dapat, pero ano nga bang magagawa ko kung ayaw nilang makipag usap,tumulong, o umintindi gaya ng pag intindi ko sakanila. Gusto ko lang namang maramdaman yung pagbawi nila, yung effort nila na pagtulong pabalik o pagtulong sa huli kasi di lang naman para sakin to,para samin to. Kahit Isang "Hi,babawi ako kasi di ako nakatulong nung nakaraan, sorry tsaka thank you ha,mag aambag ako dito,salamat sa pag intindi at pagsalo nung di ko kaya"] 
 
 Nakakainis, nakakasama ng loob kasi hirap ako pero mas hirap sila eh, falling apart na sila, unstable, kaya ako na muna. 
 
 2 [Nakakapagod na din akong magtanong kung kamusta ka na, nakakapagod na din magsabi na kung may problema ka nandito lang ako makikinig (kasi di mo naman ako kwinekwentuhan). Hindi ko din maiwasan isipin kung kinonsider mo ba akong kwentuhan. Ano ba ako sayo? Sino ba ako? Nasabi ko naman na yung side ko pero wala,busy tayo kaya wala paring nangyayari sa inopen up ko. Di naman ako nanghihingi ng bongga o sobra. Yung enough and consistent lang na attention okay na kaso minsan di ko maiwasang tanungin sarili ko na nabibigyan ba ako kahit yung bare minimum? Kasi parang mas bare pa sa bare hahaha o baka nakukulangan lang ako dahil sa expectations ko? Pero baka di lang ma meet love language ko kaya ganito ako, ayoko lang umalis pa kasi may ilalaban pa tong pagod ko hahaha korny man pero gusto ko din nung random message saying na proud ako sayo,mahal kita ganon hahaha]
 
 3 [Naiinis ako. Nakakasama ng loob kasi just because nakikita nila na nababalance ko org,acads,alis with fam, tas nagkaka awards pa ako while doing all those things, naiisip na nila na madali lang. Di nila alam na I've been sacrificing a lot of things. Yung hobby ko, yung sleep ko, yung ibang bagay na important para sakin. Na ipapahinga ko nalang,uunahin ko pa yung iba kasi kailangan nila ako, ngayon lang kasi to and ako lang may alam kaya eto muna. Na just because di ako nagrereklamo while doing all those things, di na ako nahihirapan. Di ko pinapakita pero sa bawat okay lang,keri lang, gusto ko na umayaw, hirap na hirap na ako. Di nila alam na pinagsasabay ko exams plus bonding with fam kasi parehas ng available na sched plus parehas na importante, siguro nga sensitive na ako kasi nainis ako sakanila. dun sa mga side comment nila. Pati dun sa comment na "gala" kahit na nagpasa ako ng requirements kaya ako nasa labas plus breathing time na din kasi di na ako makahinga sa dami ng gawain. Pero sa huli, dinidisregard ko lang tong thoughts na to kasi feeling ko ginagawa ko lang big deal to lalo na sa friends ko to nararamdaman]
 
 Pero ayun, narealize na sa pagintindi ko sakanila,na neglect ko na sarili ko. Napapagod din pala ako,kailangan ko din pala ng pahinga,kailangan ko din ng pag intindi, kailangan kong lumayo muna sakanila. Mahal ko naman sarili ko, pero siguro sa pagpilit ko na I keep yung ibang tao sa buhay ko, unti unti na akong nauubos. Kasalanan ko din naman,ayaw ko silang mawala.
 
 Hayy..Sana okay lang din kayo,wag niyo kalimutang magpahinga at piliin ang sarili lagi.

 Pa-rant lang po kasi masama po loob namin.
 
 College is difficult. Not just the topics being discussed, not just the activities that are given to answer but it is difficult most of the time because of the professors. I'm from CCIS and I know na some of you may think that our course is by far the easiest. Coding lang naman yan, memorizing lang naman yan, wala namang Math dyan, self-study lang yan. 
 
 No, it is not that easy. Lalo na if this is not your first choice, to begin with. Lalo na if ang professor mo ay walang consideration. Lalo na if fast-paced ang teaching ng professor at lunud na lunod ka na sa activities na hindi naman chinecheckan. Ang masaklap pa ay kung ang grade na ibinigay sa buong section niyo ay mababa at talaga naman na hindi deserve ng karamihan.
 
 To Prof na itago natin sa initials na Ma'am Ld, I appreciate your teachings po, I appreciate na tinatry mo po laging umattend sa synch class despite your loaded schedule. I appreciate na may natutunan naman po ako sa klase niyo. Pero ma'am, maaari niyo po bang linawin sa amin ang grading system niyo po? Maaari niyo po bang ipaliwanag in private? Di po yung sasabihin niyo po sa gc yung grade po namin, di po yung sasabihin niyo po na kesyo bagsak sa long quiz ay automatic na bagsak na agad ang grade? Di po yung tipo na magmemeeting po class po namin with you po and naka on cam po kung gusto mag inquire. Ma'am hindi po lahat may lakas ng loob magtanong ng naka on cam lalo na po kung medyo harsh po kayo magsalita. Hindi po lahat confident na ipakita ang grade nila sa iba. May tinatawag po tayong privacy and I believe kabilang na po grades dun. 
 
 May mga classmate po akong may scholarship, private and government, and mawawala po iyon dahil sa grades na binigay niyo po. Sana naman po maging considerate po kayo kahit papaano kasi halos lahat naman po kami nagcocomply ng mga activities niyo po kahit konting time lang po binibigay niyo po at hindi niyo po chinecheckan. #PUPFreedomWall12594
 
 Broke up with my ex. 
 Went to Baguio with friends. 
 Damn. 
 Baguio. 
 You gave me wonderful memories. 
 And some thoughts. 
 
 As I write this, I'm waiting for my ride home. 
 Plus, it's still witching hour and I don't want to leave this terminal at this cover of darkness. 
 
 I can still vividly recall everything. 
 The streets and the passageways. 
 My hotel room. 
 That one disgusting cup of tea I had to took down. 
 My feeling of awe and serenity. 
 And sometimes, annoyance. 
 Partly due to the fact that I finished a book series while on the trip and I can't properly grieve. 
 I dunno if it's the weather being cold or the fact that I had to remind myself not to fall for anyone while I'm there coz it's gonna be an LDR disaster. 
 My head was spinning. 
 I wish it could spin for longer. 
 So many beautiful people everywhere. 
 Cute guys I wanna kiss and take home, cute girls I wanna date and treat right. 
 My whole freaking sexuality was on fire. 
 If I'd choose to be lost somewhere, Baguio City would be top of the list. 
 
 Then again. 
 Walking around Burnham Park, and other parks... 
 I realized that there's more to love than the magic of attractions. 
 I saw a couple look into each other's eyes and I saw meaning. 
 Love is supposed to be fulfilling in more ways than one. 
 As a matter of fact, I witnessed love and its many faces. 
 Love is going to the bustling night market with nothing much to spend but with much to experience and see. 
 Love is going paddling around the lake fearing one of you would be stupid enough to capsize the boat but no one cares coz it's fun nonetheless. 
 Love is embarking for the grand search of strawberries! (like come on, the actual strawberry farms are hella farm from Baguio proper).
 I also found love to be that one person who's brave enough to drag you to a skating rink knowing none of you knows any better. 
 Love is worth pausing your audiobooks for and looking them at the eyes. 
 Love is worth walking a long mile with. 
 Love is the person to complain for when the skies are too gray for your own comfort. 
 They can't do much about it but they'll listen to you anyway. 
 
 I don't have love right now. 
 Maybe I'll never will. 
 But I saw the glimpse of it in other people's story. 
 That's enough to give me hope. 
 
 Who knows? 
 Maybe someday, I won't have to listen to audiobooks while walking around the park just to drown the noise. Coz I'll have someone to actually tell me a more compelling story. 
 
 As I wrap this up, 10 more minutes before I can finally drag myself home, I remembered a story. 
 The adventures of Holden Caulfield from The Catcher in the Rye. 
 For few days, I've been a version of Holden. Pessimistic against the sunny and glorious backdrops, searching for something worthwhile. 
 I found some and more. 
 
 a freewheeling bisexual like Magnus Bane,

 #PUPFreedomWall12348
 
 Sender, I feel you!!! He's a Catholic, and I'm not. Crush ko siya since grade 7 ako at 1st year college sya that time, at a year after, we met again dahil ininvite siya ng kaklase niya na churchmate ko din, I noticed na he's looking at me (oh diba, ang cute ko whahaha). When I was grade 10, nalaman ko pala na gf niya yung student teacher namin, and may jowa din ako that time kaya medyo di big deal sakin. Kahit he comments on my p
 meme shared post sometimes, nung January 2020 lang kami nagkaroon ng communication dahil sa Twice (Nayeon biased siya at pareho kaming Once) at nung binigay niya ang prayer request niya sa akin, so I can pray for him. Nung nag-start ang lockdown, he admitted na crush niya ako at sinabi ko din na crush ko din sya for almost five years. Naging mag-MU na kami at sa Manila pa ako that time during lockdown kaya long distance mag-MU kami. He can send me a voice message, pero when I am trying to video call him, ayaw niya dahil baka mas ma-fall daw sya sa akin lol. We know na di kami pwede dahil parehong religious ang family namin, pero pinatuloy pa din namin, and my family will condemn me for having a relationship with someone that has different religion than me, at mas malala pa if I ever marry someone na Catholic, kaya I didn't open that matter sa kanila. One day, he told me na sinabi niya ang matter na 'yan sa nanay niya and she told him that "Anak, kahit anong sabihin mo, Katoliko ang gusto kong makatuluyan mo", nasaktan ako dahil I can't change ny religion, and kaya niya pero he will face criticisms sa family niya. Sweet naman siya at clingy every time na magkasama kami (di kasi ako ganyan, lol). Even though he's busy dahil sa work, he will make time para magkausap kami. Fast forward, September 2020, a week din siyang hindi nag-chat sa akin at kinabahan na nga ako dahil baka na-ghost na ako. He messaged me nung Sept. 19, na he's feelings for me went deeper, that's why he's avoiding me, I accepted his reason dahil alam kong yan na din ang patutunguhan namin. After two months, he messaged me out of nowhere! O diba, the audacity kung saan dun na naka-move on na ako. He told me about his family problems kaya di na din niya nakakausap ang iba niyang friends, I wondered if I deserve him that time, and he asked me if kamusta ako nung wala siya, ayun okay pa din naman ako kahit he dumped me, wala na kaming communication after niyan. Fast forward, 4 months later, he greeted me on my birthday, I asked him na pumunta dito sa bahay para kumain, he told me na may gig pa siya, and I insisted na pumunta siya after ng gig niya, pumunta din sya, we have a short walk after that at konting usap na din, and I can't help myself but to stare at him dahil na-miss ko sya. Wala na kaming communication ngayon at nagkabalikan na din siya at ng ex niya nung hs sya. He's happy with her na din kahit ldr na sya and I wonder if he felt the same way din sakin. I already moved on na din sakanya and I'm studying hard to be happy, pero that confession that I tagged above triggered me. Siguro kung Catholic din ako, I can freely love him without any hesitations. During the time that I was moving on, I can't cry, but I can't sleep at night dahil sa naging fate naming dalawa. Palaging pumapasok sa mindd kostatement na "atleast we've met" at ang awit na Sol at Luna. Ang moral lesson ay kung March Aries ka, iwasan mo ang December Sagittarius lol. One day, I hope na if ever our paths will cross again, masaya na ako. Kaya if you have a relationship or mutual understanding towards someone that has different religion, be ready to take risks kasi this matter ay stigma pa din sa bansa natin. Yun lang, at pati na din kay kuya sender, your feelings are valid, and I hope na makahanap ka ng babaeng Catholic na mamahalin mo.
 
 PUP mein

 REGARDING SA MGA PUPFW POSTS ABOUT SA MGA TIBAK NA NASA SC... (Long post ahead)
 
 Just wanna remind you that this is NOT a hate post. Baka naman kung anong tibak comments na naman lumitaw. 
 
 Grateful kaming mga students sa representation na ginagampanan ng mga tibak sa labas ng PUP. Grateful kami na merong mga nagrerepresenta na lumubog sa masa at duminig ng mga panawagan ng mga tao.
 
 Pero ito kasi isa rin sa mga gampanin ng mga SC, ang tumugon sa mga concerns at tumulong sa mga pinagdadaanan ng mga estudyante. Lalo na ngayon alam natin gaano kahirap makipag deal sa offices ng PUP, mag asikaso ng documents at makipag communicate sa professors. 
 
 Habang naninindigan tayo sa mundo sa labas, sana ganun din yung paninindigan sa loob. We expected a lot sa tibak officers with their #TayoNaman at sa pinahihiwatig nila na edge nila sa ibang candidates nung SCE. Pero ang nangyayari puro tayo boses pero kulang sa action. Mayroon tayong GC sa R4E pero solely LBE purposes lang talaga nandoon kung pwede namang gamitin na rin ang GC for other academic purposes dahil nandoon na ang mga student leaders pati sila Mx. Albie. 
 
 SC ang tinakbuhan nila, hindi basta mass org. May mga layunin na dapat maaccomplish sa SC patungkol sa student service. For sure alam niyo naman iyon. May pagkakaiba rin ang pangangailangan ng isang normal na estudyante sa pangangailangan ng isang mamamayang may pangarap para sa lipunan. Madami rin umaasa sa inyo na may magagawa kayo sa paghihirap ng mga estudyante sa loob.
 
 Maganda naman yung adhikain wala namang nagsasabing hindi pero try niyo pakinggan kung bakit ba may lumilitaw na mga ganitong confessions sa Freedom Wall. Kapag nag try rin kami mag criticize ng tibak parang kami pa rin mali. Hindi ba dapat malawak din pang unawa niyo sa mga kritisismo dahil nagsisilbi nga kayong representasyon ng mga kabataan ngayon at ng mga progresibong estudyante?

#PUPFreedomWall12066
 
 Ang klase ay microcosm ng ating lipunan. At mas masasalamin ito sa kung paano tayo pumili ng lider. Sa 6 na taon ko sa highschool at 4 na taon ko sa PUP, napansin ko kung paano bumuto ang klase ng mga class officers nito. Sa bawat klase ko mula pa man noong grade 7, napansin ko na bumubuto tayo ng class officers na sabihin na natin "di-kagalingan" pero popular naman - sila yung tipong average students with lots of friends. Madalas pa na sila yung mga kunsintidor o mas malala, prumutor pa ng kopyahan. One time pa nga, naalala ko Yung platform ng isa sa tumakbong class president na kaklase ko sa PUP na 'ang kopyahan ay hahayaan'. At ayun, nanalo siya. Hanggang ngayon, nagtataka ako kung bakit pinipili natin yung mga ganong uri ng estudyante. Siguro dahil hindi naman talaga pumipili ang botante base sa galing o husay ng pinuno. Bumubuto tayo base sa kung ano ang values natin. Bumubuto tayo kung mapapakinabangan ba natin ang kandidatong ito. Bumubuto tayo base sa interes natin. Medyo selfish diba. 
 
 Kaya napapatanong ako ngayon eh kung bakit kaya ganon tayong mga Filipino, mas pinipili pa natin Yung mga taong may bahid ng kurapsyon (o sa kaso nating mga Isko, mga nangongopya) at "di-kagalingan" basta ito ay papabor sa ating interes. Magandang malaman ang dahilan Kung bakit tayo ganito. Isa pa, kinakatakot ko na baka tayo rin ang henerasyon na magluluklok sa "maling" lider. Sabi nga, history doesn't repeat itself, we repeat history. 
 
 Ano nga ba Ang values mo bilang isang tao?Kung Ang values mo ay salungat sa ikalalago ng Kung ano ang Tama at mabuti, mas mabuting gamitin Ang rason sa pagpili. Kaya sa mga kapwa ko Isko, mabuting isipin kung sino nga ba ang dapat iboto. 
 
 BSA 4th Year

 To the man i love,
 Hindi ako taga PUP but the father of my son and soon to be baby ay nag-aaral dito. I just have a simple message for you my love. I know things aren't good between us. I know din na may mahal ka ng iba. Ang sakit padin isipin na mas pinipili mo siya. I want you ti know na nakakapagod din mag sorry, lalo na kapag hindi naman napapansin. I look so stupid trying to prove something, pero hindi mo ako nakikita because of her. I know i did something wrong but what you're doing right now, it's too much para sa nagawa ko before. You're giving me mixed signals, knowing that we're having a baby. Ang saket lang for me, everytime na nagkakamali ka i choose to forgive you and love you because my unconditional love for you is more powerful than any of your mistakes. I choose to be with you, for better and worst. I choose to love you even if you're hurting me too much. And until now, I'm still loving you even if you have someone else. Pero hindi ako selfish kasi mahal kita. Sana kahit sa mga bata nalang stay for them. They need you, our son needs you, I need you (because of our baby in my tummy). This 2022, i wish you would realize everything. Andito lang ako palagi to support you, kahit ipagtabuyan mo ako paulit ulit. Kahit magalit ka sakin dahil sa tingin mo dinamay ko yung girl, but tbh she needs to know the truth. Nahihirapan akong makitang masaya kayo, habang ako napapabayaan mo with our baby. Sana nga kahit ako nalang yung masaktan, kahit paulit ulit. Okay lang. But I'm with out little one. I hope you considered it. Pero parang nakakawalang respeto. And as for that girl, she just can't say na kayang kaya niyang tanggapin yung anak natin. She deserves someone better, and our children deserves you as their father. But if nagmamahalan talaga kayo, sino ba naman ako para humarang diba?. Just please don't make us feel so less important to you. Because your son and soon to be baby, is the most important. Nasasaktan ka kasi nagkakalabuan kayo ng girl? Eh yung mga anak natin? Ako? Do you think we're happy? Kung kaya ko lang silang dalawa eh why not? Hinayaan na sana kita kasama siya. But i hope you understand. Ou children needs you. Desperada man pakinggan pero para sa mga bata okay lang. Wag mo na akong mahalin, okay lang. Pero yung anak natin, give them what they deserve. And don't choose your girl over them. Hindi ko na alam pano ka gigisingin. Kung paano ka matatauhan. Pero sana balang araw, balang araw marealized mo lahat. Andito padin kami. Kung may mga taong hindi mangiiwan sayo kami yun, mga anak mo yun. Mahal kita, mahal na mahal kita kahit sobrang sakit na. At patuloy lang kitang mamahalin. Because the day that you proposed to me, i promise to love you even if nasa punto na tayo na sobrang hirap na. And for me, loving you unconditionally is the greatest decision i made. Kahit hindi mo ako mahalin pabalik. You always say na, hindi mo alam kung mahal mo pa ako. Okay lang, basta mahalin mo lang mga anak natin. Hanggang dito nalang muna siguro. And for the last time, Iloveyou!

 I have a confession.
 
 I think I'm broken.
 In a way I lose love easily.
 
 How is it that even villains in the movies are able to fall deeply and stupidly with someone and I cant?
 Do they have more to lose than I do?
 
 Is it really possible that I am now with a person I liked most, but my heart is still sometimes calling out to the darkness and void?
 
 Am I meant to be alone?
 
 I thought that maybe, just maybe, I'm just not with the right person. That I have to listen further and deeper and be more receptive to my senses.
 
 It was my regret to play peoples' feelings before. 
 I'm trying to be better.
 
 At first, I thought that maybe it's because of my sexual orientation.
 I dated girls. Mostly. Fell in love and fell out of it.
 Now I'm dating this guy I adore and he's a piece of work, which makes me like him even further. I'd die for this person.
 
 At the end of the I love yous, at the end of the goodnight kisses and movie dates, is hollowness; while all the same, I can't lose him. I don't understand it. I have this feeling that something is missing in this equation. I'm asking the universe for it.
 
 Is it love if you can break at the right moment?
 Is love insanity or supersanity?

 The one who can occasionally feel love but not really, not necessarily.

#PUPFreedomWall11673
 
 His name is J. 
 
 Board top notcher. 
 He got looks. 
 And that annoying smile. 
 Makata. 
 Maaarte. 
 Madaming sinasabi. 
 Egomaniac pa. 
 He likes to collect shoes, and watches, and expensive bags and clothes. 
 He's rich. 
 He likes to collect brilliant people to fall in love with. 
 He's sapiosexual. 
 He's vain? Madalas. 
 Exasperating? Definitely. 
 
 Of all the things thrown at him, it seems along the way, they have forgotten that J is only a man. 
 J gets sad. 
 Depressed. 
 I can't confirm but even suicidal? 
 J is far from perfect. 
 And that's how I see him. 
 Beyond all the nice aesthetics, golden pedestal and physical attributes, I saw his core, his heart and I settled at the bottom on his mind. 
 
 I'm not rich but definitely not poor when it comes to words. I am his Living Tribunal. My mind is not one to spare his. I see through all his bs and lies. And I pity him just how I pity a bird of paradise caught behind a cage of wrought iron. 
 
 He is flawed. 
 And more. 
 
 He's sweet. 
 And thoughtful. 
 He's a giver and he's kind. 
 He sings to you, and spend hours talking to you. 
 He smiles a lot. 
 He has nasty jokes and he's used to my frowns and rolling eyes. 
 
 He's caught in a loveless relationship that made him bitter. 
 But what can I do? 
 I'm just a confidant. 
 A friend. 
 I can't stand watching him destroy himself in smoke and alcohol and wrong decisions. It's not my party to crash. 
 We fell off. 
 
 His lover came back one Thursday night. 
 He said he's happy but his eyes and voice clearly projects mutiny. 
 I said okay. 
 Then we stopped talking. 
 
 One day.
 J came back. 
 Stupidly wounded and hopeless.
 Bearing noose and spoken poetry. 
 The dummy was definitely suicidal. 
 He confessed avoiding. 
 He confessed grandly failing. 
 He confessed being haunted. 
 He confessed missing me. 
 
 Now I'm sleep-deprived. 
 And he's happier. 
 Can't blame him though. 
 We're both smiling. 
 
 This is J. 
 My J. 
 
 The one who makes listening to Taylor's Red album bearable.

 Lagi ako napunta sa PUP FW, pero I'm trying to fight the urge to share a confession every time things get unbearable. Now I'm here writing one. 
 
 Sa totoo lang, ang hirap magpatuloy nung mga nakaraang araw. Wala na akong gana sa lahat ng bagay. Mag-aral, kumain, matulog, kahit gumawa ng mga bagay na gusto ko. I recently lost a loved one at ngayon napipilitan ako mag-function as if nothing happened. Wala eh, kailangan tapusin agad mga school works kase takot ako matambakan ng gawain. At the same time, wala naman akong gana na gumawa ng kahit ano kaya ang ending wala rin akong natatapos. Gulo diba? I'm sure hindi lang naman ako yung nakakaramdam ng ganito. Dagdag pa yung hindi naman na satisfying ang pagkatututo ngayong online class lalo na pag yung course mo required ka magkaroon ng lab at field experience para matuto.

Ibig sabihin kasi nun, nakakaluwag-luwag nga kami, pakiramdam ko naiiwan ko siya, ganun. Para kaming naggrow apart na hindi ko maintindihan. 
 
 Hindi ko alam paano siya tutulungan. Yung presence ko lang mabibigay ko. Di kami makapag-kita e, lalo ngayong pandemic at sobrang controlling ng tatay ko sakin. Minsan nakakapagpadala ako, minsan nakakapunta ako, pero rare occasion talaga.
 
 Question is, ano ba dapat kong gawin? May naiisip ba kayo? Parang di siya natutuwa sa setup namin. Kahit naman ako, but all I say we do is wait. Usapan kasi makagraduate lang ako, magiging legal na kami. Yun din kondisyon ng magulang ko. Ayoko kasing sisihin din siya ng magulang ko sa shortcomings ko.
 
 Salamat sa sasagot.
