#PUPFreedomWall11385
 
 An open letter to my fellow Marcos supporters in PUP, 
 
 Gusto ko lang malaman niyo na hindi kayo nag-iisa. May kasama kayo sa pag-suporta kay BBM. May kasama kayo na nagmamahal sa ating bayan. I hope mga registered voters kayo. And I hope na nag-aaral din kayo ng mabuti tulad ko hihi
 
 Alam ko na marami sa inyo ay nagtatago dahil takot ma-judge. May mga iba naman na na-express na ito sa mga classmates/blockmates/prof natin at nakatanggap ng mga kaliwa't kanang insulto at pangca-cancel culture. Ngunit may mga iba naman na maayos tayong kinakausap ukol dito. Na-appreciate ko kayong mga di nagca-cancel. 
  
 Huwag kayo magpa-apekto sa kanilang mga sinasabi. Ipaliwanag niyo nang maigi ang inyong panig. Huwag mag-komento sa mga paninira at mga ad hominem remarks nila na hindi lang binabato sa atin, kundi binabato rin sa mga supporter ng mga ibang kandidato gaya ni Isko at Ka Leody. Huwag kayong makikipag-away. Huwag magpa-boycott ng isang negosyo. Dahil ang mga ugali na ito ay hindi ugali ng isang tunay na Pilipino. Hindi ito ugali ng isang nagmamahal sa bayan. 
  
 Hayaan nating mamili ang mga PUPian ng gusto nilang iboto dahil ito ay personal nilang desisyon. Kanya-kanya tayo ng opinyon na pinanghahawakan. Kanya-kanya tayo ng gusto ngayong halalan. Basta tayo behave lang. Hindi natin kailangan ng cancel culture dahil nasa atin ang tao. Hindi natin kailangan manira ng ibang kandidato. 
 
 Ngunit kung sakali man na kailangan natin muli ipaglaban ang Sintang Paaralan, wag niyo hayaan na mapahamak ang mga kapwa natin Iskolar ng Bayan.
 At higit sa lahat ay ipagtanggol natin ang PUP. Dahil hindi lamang ito ang paaralan natin sa ngayon. Ito ay magiging paaralan din ng mga susunod na henerasyon. Sinubukan na tayo taasan ng tuition, tanggalan ng accord, at gusto pang ipasara. Ngunit heto pa rin tayo, PUPian pa rin. 
  
 Naging panatiko rin ako dati kina Aquino at Duterte. Ngunit wala akong napala sa kanila. 
  
 Lumaban kung may nangyayaring di maganda. Batikusin kung may kamalian. Patunayan niyo na may democracy sa bansang ito. Patunayan niyo na tunay kayong nagmamahal sa kapwa niyo Pilipino. 
  
 Sa ngayon ay mag-focus muna tayo sa pagtulong sa kapwa ngayong pandemya. Mag-focus sa online classes habang wala pang F2F. Mag-focus muna tayo sa pagtulong sa mga proyekto ng ating komunidad. Magpa-bakuna. Suportahan ang mga local businesses. Upang makaahon muli ang ating bansa sa impact ng pandemic. 
  
 Let's make this nation great again. Sama-sama tayong babangon muli. 
 
 Sa mga kakampinks, peace be with you ‚úåüèº

#PUPFreedomWall11342
 
 TW: suicidal thoughts and tendencies
 
 Struggle ko sa IE
 
 I've been struggling a lot with my mental health this year lalo na sa suicidal thoughts ko. Wala akong mapuntahan para gumaan pakiramdam ko, hindi pa nakakatulong yung gusto ko nang lumabas pero may takot na magka-covid ulit. Hindi ko na rin magawa nang maayos mga kailangan kong gawin kasi parang ginagawa ko na lang kasi kailangan kong gumraduate. Hindi ko rin ma-fathom yung thought na hindi pa rin ako nakakakuha ng trabaho kahit kailangan na kailangan ko. Malas talaga ako sa buhay pero walang magagawa. 
 
 Napapadalas na rin yung dissociation sa point na hindi ko na namamalayan na may hawak na pala akong matulis at may hiwa na mga braso ko. Minsan hindi na alam kung tamang amount ang sleeping pills na naiinom ko dahil sa dissociations ko. Naiisip ko na palang mamatay nang hindi ko namamalayan.
 
 Tapos ito pang struggle sa course ko, dumadagdag pa. Lalo na sa department na napakagulo palagi. Napaka-walang puso ng IE department. IE pa kayo sa lagay na 'yan pero wala kayong consideration sa mga nararamdaman ng mga estudyante niyo! Puro kayo rant ng professionalism pero hindi niyo ma-apply! Sobra kayo maka-pressure sa estudyante, hindi na makatao!
 
 Biglaan kayo palagi magset ng meetings, as if palagi kaming available para sa inyo. Guess what? May mga estudyanteng may trabaho rin, may mga estudyanteng may small businesses, may mga estudyanteng currently may covid, but they try their best para makapagtapos at makapasok sa klase para matuloy ang pag-aaral. Hindi niyo ba naiisip yun? Kaya nga may schedule na sinet para alam ang free time ng estudyante, hindi yung nagsasarili kayo.
 
 Noong OJT pa, sobrang gulo niyo. Wala ba kayong mga gc? May sinet na 54 hours pero may mga prof na nagpush ng 100-200 hours as if naman lahat nakakuha ng company o may pera para sa mga webinars at online courses na maccredit niyo. Hindi nga kayo nagbibigay ng ayuda sa mga estudyante niyo, ganyan pa sistema niyo.
 
 Noong OJT pa, may covid kaming pamilya, naubos ang pera ng pamilya namin para lang sa covid testing tapos pinush ng ilang profs na 100 hours yung online courses na makuha namin. May mga kaklase rin akong nasa parehong sitwasyon ko pero hindi niyo naisip yun. Hindi niyo naisip na nasa pandemya tayo at kung ano ang mga possibleng sitwasyon ng mga estudyante niyo.
 
 Huwag kayong magtaka kung sooner or later, may bigla na lang na mamatay o magpakamatay sa stress dahil sa gulo niyo. Dinadamay niyo mga estudyante niyo sa pagiging disorganized niyo. Sana matauhan din kayo.

 TW: medyo sensitive content
 
 Gusto ko lang i-share ito kasi napapansin ko na for the past couple of years, hindi pa rin siya nawawala sa isip o mga gawain ko sa araw araw. I've been a suicidal person since my high school days. I don't want to say what's the reason behind it but I'm not doing it just for fun, not for clout chasing, but because I really wanted to end my life so bad. I'm on the higher section noong high school ko kaya di makapaniwala mga teacher ko na palagi akong absent and worse, mababa na ang mga grades. Kinausap ako ng isa kong teacher na malapit sakin na sana kung ano man ang problema ko, sana iiwan ko sa bahay iyon at huwag kong pabayaan pag-aaral ko. 
 I decided na sundin ang sinabi niya. I became a suicidal person pero nasa honor. I always come to school na may mga cuts sa parehong wrist ko. I just wear hoodies or long sleeves clothes kahit mainit para lang hindi makita sugat ko. Alam pa rin naman ng mga kaklase ko and teacher ko tho. I did my best in class, palagi akong nagrerecite, palaging nagpapasa ng activity on time, at kung ano ano pa. I also help my classmates whenever they struggle in some of our activities. I hang out with my friends din kapag may time kami para gumala. Ang saya saya ko tuwing nasa labas. Pero tuwing uuwi ako ng bahay, sumasalubong lahat ng problema at kalungkutan ko. Isang beses umuwi akong nakangiti, ngunit pagsara ko ng pintuan, bigla nalang may tumulong luha sa mga mata ko. And I will have this urge na pumuntang banyo habang hawak ang blade at susugatan ko sarili ko. 
 Ever since that day na kinausap ako, naging ganito na ako hanggang ngayong college ako. Kasali ako palagi sa PL, I don't hurt myself anymore though, but I still have this thought na I wanted to end myself instead of studying these shits. Nahihirapan na ako sobra. Wala na talaga akong gana mag-aral. Pero nagsisipag pa rin ako lalo ngayon ay puro groupings kami. Ayaw kong madamay pati mga kaklase ko sa pagbagsak ko. Pero gusto ko na talaga huminto. Nakakapagod.
 -I tried seeking help sa counseling but I still can't find the reason to live. They're doing their best pero parang di pa rin ako natutulungan.

 My sunflower, 
 
 Hi. 
 How are you? 
 Magaling ka na ba? 
 Take your meds on time okay?

 Will miss having to talk to you during my breaks and lunches, when I get home, before I sleep and before I get to work. You were injected to my routine. 
 But that's okay. This is not me asking for you back. 
 Basta masaya. Basta comfortable. Basta di ka vulnerable. Dun din ako. 
 Di ako selfish. 
 This is more like, a thank you and good bye. 
 
 Alam mo, I wrote you letters. 
 Mga ilan din. Before that night. 
 I guess it's for me to keep na lang din.
 Nanghinayang lang ako ng konti kasi I found peace and comfort. With you. Your presence. 
 Thank you for the inspiration. 
 Pero wala eh. Natalo tayo. 
 At wala ng bawi. 
 
 Are you in a cycle of hurt, my sunflower?
 Try to break free of it, okay?
 
 Furthermore, 
 Fyi, you destroyed me that day. 
 So destroyed to the point I didn't fear coming out to my mother after so many years. 
 She said you broke my heart. And that was my mother saying that. 
 You betrayed me by letting go so easily, even after I revealed everything. 
 Natakot ka masira? Ako din eh. Mas natakot akong aalis ka. Sayang lods.

 I burned all the bridges between us. 
 No messages kept. To go back to. 
 I loved your music. I'd miss that. 
 
 I'll remember you by the time I find myself in the next Taylor Swift concert while with someone else. 
 I hope you find the love story you deserve.

 you used to be my sunflower,

 Hi Ms. COC
 
 Ito yung huling araw ng kwento natin. 
 
 Ramdam ko na yung panlalamig mo mula noong nagkaayos tayo ulit. Sobrang nag aalala ako sa araw araw na parang hindi na tayo bumalik sa dating masaya, may parteng kulang. At pinilit kong maniwala na baka wala ka lang talaga sa mood. Hinintay ko iyon hanggang tumagal, nawala na yung labyutoo mo sakin palagi. Hindi na kagaya noon na nagdedemand ka ng oras mula sakin, hindi kagaya noon na nauuna kang naggogoodmorning sakin. At habang mas tumatagal, lalong nawawala kaya mapapansin mo na lagi akong nag aalala at nag tatanong kung anong problema, sa ating dalawa ba or sa paligid mo. At habang nangyayari yun, sabi ko ilalaban kita hanggang huli kahit mahirap kahit palagi tayong nag aaway kahit na minsan ayaw mo na ako makausap at ako ang nagdudulot ng trigger mo. 
 
 Lalo pa itong lumala, mas lumala rin yung overthink ko kase mas lalo kang nagiging malamig sakin. Hanggang sa nagtalo tayo ulit at mula noon ay hindi mo na ako kinausap. Hindi ko alam ang gagawin ko noon, lumuluha ako mula umaga at hanggang sa pagtulog, naisip kong iyon na ang katapusan ng lahat. 
 
 Pero sabi ko hindi, please lang wag kang lalayo. Kahit na malamig ang turing mo sakin nitong mga nakaraan ay naiiwan parin sakin yung mga labyu mo noon. Yung good morning mo sakin kapag nauuna kang magising, Hindi ako sanay ng wala ang mga iyon, ayokong maniwala na dumudulo na tayo sa pag hihiwalay kaya naman sa araw araw ay pinipilit kong hindi pumatak ang luha ko. Gusto kong maniwala na pagod ka lang talaga, busy ka lang talaga. At darating din yung time na magiging okay na ulit tayo. 
 
 Pero bakit ngayon palang ramdam ko nang wala kana?
  Bakit pakiramdam ko Hindi na ako mahalaga? 
 Asan na yung dating ikaw, asan na yung dating tayo. 
 Binabalikan ko yung mga masasaya nating pag uusap noon, yung kilig, yung tawa, yung pag aalala natin sa isat isa at yung pagmamahal natin pareho. 
 
 Hindi naba babalik yun? 
 
 Deserve mo ang mahalin at maniwala ka man o hindi minahal kita ng totoo, pinahalagahan, iningatan, pinangarap na makasama ka habambuhay, lahat ng mga sinasabi ko sayo ay totoo. 
 
 Kung paanong hindi ako nagsasawa sa selfie mo, kung paanong gusto ko laging marinig ang boses mo, kung paanong Hindi ako matahimik kapag di kita kausap. Bawat gabi at umaga na bubungad sakin ay masaya ako kase andyan ka. 
 
 Ngayong wala kana, hindi parin ako makapaniwala. Hanggang ngayon ay lumalaban parin ako. Mahal na mahal kita at mamahalin parin kita. 
 
 Palagi.

 Hello! So, I am currently in a relationship, and it's my first ever serious relationship. We get along well, during talking stage, kaya rin na-develop, but as time goes by, I've realized na we don't have anything in common. Sabi niya, okay lang naman daw yon, as long as we both love each other. Okay lang din naman sakin, but I'm having doubts, if mag-lalast ba yung relationship namin, kahit wala kaming common ground. 
 
 "How would we bond?" 
 "What do we talk about?"
 
 Earlier days ng relationship, okay, marami pa namang napag-uusapan, sa chat or in person, since we're both getting to know eo pa. Eh ngayong kilalang kilala namin isa't isa, wala na kami mapag-usapan, and the convo is getting boring na rin, wala kasing bago, wala kaming mapagchikahan, kasi magkaiba kami ng mga trip sa buhay. Kahit yung huli naming meetup, nanunuod na lang siya minsan sa phone niya. Mas nakakapanghina pa yung fact na yung huling partner niya ay marami silang in common (music, books, movies, series), I feel like such a downgrade tuloy, kasi I can't give that bond to him.
 
 So ayon, for me, it's important na you and your partner should have something in common, to last. Don't get me wrong, I love him, but I fear that we'll get bored of eo, and fall out of love, eventually. I don't wanna waste his time eh. I wanna know your opinions if you think this will work pa ba... Kasi every time I think about this, naddrain talaga ako, I really need help. Thank you.

Ngayon bumalik. Walang sincere apology. Kung magsorry man, parang pinagmu-mukha pa na kasalanan mo kaysa kasalanan niya. Pero tatanggapin mo ulit kasi pinangakuan ka naman ng kung ano-ano. Pustahan tayo, yung mga ibibigay niyang regalo sa 'yo, iuutang niya ulit at ikaw na naman ang magbabayad. 
 
 Payag ka? Dapat hindi. Kitang-kita mo na nga ngayon nahihirapan ka tapos papahirapan mo na naman ulit yung sarili mo. 
 
 Sana sa paparating na halalan, maging wais ka na. Tandaan mo na sa iisang boto mo nakasalalay ang kinabukasan ng bansa at ng mga Pilipino. Suriin mo nang mabuti ang bawat kandidatong napupusuan mo. Piliin mo kung sinong may integridad, may malasakit, may paninindigan, at tapat. Piliin mo kung sinong tunay na karapatdapat na mamuno. Piliin mo yung kayang ipaglaban ang bansa laban sa mga dayuhang manlulupig. Nasa sa 'yo kung hahayaan mong linlangin at pahirapan ka ulit ng mga mapang-abuso, o pipiliin mo ang kinabukasan na may magandang pagbabago.

#PUPFreedomWall10048
 
 Not a rant but long post ahead. 
 
 I have been observing sa group ng freshmen group and walang katapusan ang mga away over petty things. May mga seniors na ilang taon ko nang nakikitang nagkakalat sa mga freshmen groups every year, yung iba sa kanila matagal nang graduate. Pareho namang may mali. Mali yung mga seniors for starting petty issues na dapat ay wala silang pake. Mali rin yung mga freshman na foul kung makipag argumento at sa ibang tao pinoproject ang galit nila. Valid yung galit niyo sa mga taong nagbibigay ng kritisismo sa batch niyo pero siguraduhin din na valid yung actions at pananalita. College is a tough journey. Tama naman yung sinasabi ng iba na hindi pwedeng iyakin ka lang sa college. Hindi literal na bawal kang umiyak, you can cry if you want to. Pero kung di mo kayang alamin kung ano yung mga bagay na dapat mong pagtuunan ng pansin at nagsasayang ka ng oras sa mga bagay na hindi mo na dapat pinapansin, baka mas lalo ka lang mahirapan. That's the reality. Payo lang bilang isang graduating student, college is tough, so is the life after it. You cannot just waste your time arguing with people on social media kahit na halatang pinagtitripan ka na lang nila. 
 
 Sa mga seniors naman, dami niyong time. Magfocus kayo sa mga trabaho niyo at kailangan niyong gawin. Let the kids be kids. Parang di kayo pumasok sa PUP nang nakaporma o ginawa yung mga kalokohan na ginagawa ng freshies ngayon. 
 
 PUP CAL

#PUPFreedomWall9834
 
 Kinda long post ehe
 
 Please, if you're not interested in someone who's trying to get your affection, please just flat out tell them "no".
 
 I asked this girl out during senior high school and she said "I'll think about it, siguro once matapos ko highschool let's go out" so eto ako, about to make a stupid decision because I was young, dumb, pretty horny, and stupid.
 
 Fast forward a year later, nakapasok na kami sa respective universities namin. We kept in touch naman during those two years and we've had a relatively good friendship so far. So I asked her out to go on a movie and she said yes.
 
 After which I asked her out again, she replied with a "Ayaw kasi ng parents ko, baka maka-affect sa grades ko" kind of thing.
 
 So ayun, I accepted naman since her mother was a decent and respectable person (I've talked to her family before) and thought that it was understandable.
 
 But after that, I stupidly still tried to get her to look my way, y'know? I helped her out sa studies niya, started convos when she's looking for some small talk, the small things. Heck, nagpatutor sa akin ng Java yan but I had no idea about the programming language so I took the time to learn it from scratch para lang ituro sa kanya jusme.
 
 Tapos most of the time ipaparamdam niya sayo na you're annoying and a nuisance. Like you send long/multiple messages tapos maglilike react lang, or magsesend lang ng "ok" na parang bang di masakit ;-;
 
 So ayun, I told this story with my friends naman and they agree na I should stop chasing after her. I eventually took their advice to heart and started studying harder na lang.
 
 With all the red lights she's been giving off noon, she started showing green lights na. Tipong magsisimula na siya ng late night talks, niyayaya na ako para sa mga date, etc. Tapos ako eto, litong-lito kasi that enthusiasm was not there noong ako nag-iinitiate.
 
 Naisip ko na mas mabuti na if di na ako kumagat sa ganoong pang-akit kasi sino ba namang matutuwa na 3 years ka'ng binigyan ng red light tapos once you stop giving them attention magbibigay sila ng green light?
 
 Yung pagkasweet niya bigla sa chat is unnerving. Di ako sanay. Usually cold siya tapos bigla niya ako papakitaan ng lambing??
 
 So ayun, I let it pass na lang. Hassle pa mag-isip ng reason para i-justify yung sudden shift sa pakikitungo. Then during one voice chat with our friend circle nagmention siya na kesyo may sugar daddy siya, na kesyo maraming nanliligaw sa kanya, kesyo marami na siyang pinaasa-- like what the fuck? Bakit proud na proud ka sa ginagawa mo? I understand naman na you feel that way but can you please have a bit of heart na wag i-kwento yun when I'm also there? Wala naman kasing previous topic related sa love life then you suddenly bring it up as if may pinapa-alam ka to people in the chat. It's just disheartening, to be honest.
 
 So ayun lang, I just wanted to sorta vent. Please turn down people you don't find yourself romantically interested in or attached to. Especially if you just want to be showered with attention.
 
 For people naman na feel like they're being led on, please take the time to reflect din. Don't waste your years trying to chase someone who won't reciprocate your feelings.
 
 Pero grabe talaga yung Java tutorial, the power of simping is actually real di ko inexpect na magagawa ko yun ehe

 To the political parties and our fellow iskolar ng bayan
 
 Nakakadiri at nakakabahala ang pagkalat ng mga fake news, false accusation, at black propaganda mula sa iba't ibang parties at accounts ngayong SCE.
 
 Bilang isang estudyante na saksi sa lahat ng mga pangyayaring nagaganap ngayong eleksyon, hindi ko na maatim na manahimik.
 Hindi lingid sa kaalaman ng mga partido na tumatakbo ngayong halalan ang pagkakaroon ng dialogue ng mga paralegal mula sa iba't iba't partido, comelec at student publications. Bilang isa ring paralegal, nagkakaroon ng diskurso ang komisyon sa atin hinggil sa proseso ng casting at canvassing of votes at iba pang mga usapin ngayong halalan. Bilang bahagi ng mga pag-uusap na iyon, tungkulin natin na maipaabot sa ating mga kandidato, miyembro ng ating mga partido at kapwa estudyante ang naging daloy at laman ng mga pag-uusap na iyon. Ngunit iba ata ang ating naipapaabot sa ating mga kapwa estudyante?
 
 Sa kapwa ko paralegals mula SPEAK, LABAN, SAMASA at independent CPSPA bakit hindi natin maipabatid sa ating mga miyembro at kapwa estudyante ang tunay na naging laman ng mga pag-uusap na iyon? Bakit kailangan pa nating baliktarin sa publiko kung ano ang mga napag-usapan sa mga dialogue na iyon? Noong tinanong kayo sa meeting kahapon kung saan nyo nakuha at paano kayo nagcome up sa laman ng inyong mga joint statements, nagkaroon ba kayo ng malinaw na kasagutan? WALA, ang tahimik nyo nga eh hindi ba? May nailabas ba kayong mga ebidensya na magpapatunay sa inyong mga paratang? WALA. 
 Bakit hindi ninyo aminin sa publiko na ang laman ng inyong mga joint statements ay assumptions nyo lang?
 Kung gaano sana kalakas ang ating loob na magbitiw sa publiko ng mga paratang sa iba't ibang tao at organisasyon, sana ay ganoon din kalakas ang ating loob na aminin ang ating mga pagkakamali at mabigyan ito ng linaw.
 Bilang bahagi ng partido na nabanggit, nakakasuka kung paano ko nasasaksihan ang pilit na pagmamanipula ng mga kasapi ng aking partido sa iba't ibang impormasyon na kumakalat ngayong halalan, anonymous man o hindi. ALAM NYO YAN SA SARILI NYO.
 
 Hinahamon ko lahat ng paralegals, COMELEC at maging ang mga student publications na naging bahagi ng pag-uusap kahapon na ipaalam sa ating mga kapwa iskolar ng bayan ang katotohanan sa likod ng mga joint statements na iyon at iba pang mga issue na lumalabas ngayon tungkol sa election. Parang hindi ata makatao para sa iba't ibang mga organisasyon, partido at tao na bahagi ng eleksyon na ito na nadadawit ang kanilang mga pangalan sa iba't ibang mga paratang na ibinabato sa kanila sa publiko. Kung wala sa inyong magsasalita, paano ito malalaman ng ating mga kapwa estudyante? Bakit nananatiling tikom ang inyong mga bibig? Ano bang kinakatakot natin kung alam naman nating lahat ang katotohanan?
 
 Para sa SPEAK, SAMASA, LABAN AT IBA PANG MGA PARTIDO, kung tunay nga na tayo ay naghahangad ng malinis at patas na halalan, bakit tila tayo ang nanggugulo sa hangarin na iyon? Saksi tayo sa naging eleksyon noong mga nakaraang taon at alam natin sa ating mga sarili na ibang iba ang nagiging daloy ng eleksyon ngayon. Hindi ba't kahit papaano, mas ayos ang eleksyon ngayon? Natatakot ba tayo na hindi na block voting at maaaring mabawasan ang ating impluwensya sa ating mga kapwa estudyante sa pagkakaisa ng miyembro ng iba't ibang partido na maluluklok sa pwesto ngayong darating na Academic Year?
 
 Para sa admins at moderators nitong freedom wall, tama na ang pakikisawsaw at pagtolerate sa mga black propaganda at fake news laban sa iba't ibang mga organisasyon at political parties, pula man, asul, puti o lila.
 
 Sa mga anonymous accounts at nagcconfess dito ng mga akusasyon at paratang laban sa iba't ibang kandidato, organisasyon, at parties, kilala ko na kayo. KANDIDATO KAYO HINDI BA?  To all political parties, candidates and all PUPians,
 
 I am a concerned student of our Sintang Paaralan and l am writing this open letter to inform all students, parties and candidates involved that there is an on-going conspiracy to commit electoral sabotage and fraud instigated by the so called ‚Äúindependent‚Äù headed by former student Elijah san Fernando, Current Student Regent Rommel Lemon Gonzaga, OSS Chief Abraham Sagun and some of the candidates who will be running under the ‚Äúindependent‚Äù slate.
 
 I was invited by our student council officers to run and they immediately added me to their group chat even though l did not confirm their invitation for me to run, but l embraced it anyway since l also want to serve the students with integrity and all my capacity. And after sometime of being active, l was also added to several group chats where l got disappointed and disgusted especially to Kuya Elijah San Fernando and other candidates who mock other political parties instead of talking about our plans for the election and if ever we won in this election.
 
 Sa mga ganitong inconsistencies ko napatunayan na minamanipula at minamaniobra talaga nila ang eleksyon kaya kahit wala dapat kinalaman si SR Lemon dito kasi dapat manatili siyang non partisan eh hindi niya nagagawa dahil may motibo agad sila na ayusin ang ANAK Federation kaya kailangan nilang kausapin yung KMP daw na nanalo sa PUP Taguig at makipag-usap doon para mag-build connection bilang isa rin sa paghahanda nila para sa ANAK. Kaya nung nagpalit kami ng pangalan from TINDIG to PUPian (PUP Independent Action Network) ang tingin ko ginawa nalang yun for the sake na hindi ma-associate samin si SR kasi siya yung isa sa mga unang naglabas sa facebook niya tungkol sa affliation niya sa TINDIG kasama yung iba pa namin paralegal eh.
 
 It took some time for me to realize that we are not really an independent slate but a mere pawn in this coming election as we are being misguided by Kuya Elijah and SR Lemon Gonzaga. I know that this is just a step for their preparation in the ANAK Federation. Lately ko lang din kasi naintindihan na yung ANAK pala ay mula sa mga Presidents ng Student Councils. Kaya mas naging malinaw sakin ang lahat because according to Kuya Elijah and SR Lemon, they want to engage with the student council elections as they also want to win and we will use the branding as the alternative candidates that will bring accountability to the studentry. Napag-usapan nga namin mga candidates one time na sinabi daw pala ni Kuya Elijah na sure win na ni SR yung sa San Juan Elections sa isang gc, while we are preparing for the Student Council Elections in Main kasi yun na pala ang gusto nilang mangyari kaya kinuha talaga nila kami para magpakita ng power kumbaga na marami ang independent ganon at maensure nila yung sa SR. Pero sa totoo lang, yung iba samin dito parang nahatak lang at katulad ko noon ay hindi rin aware sa mga nangyayari sa loob at sa mga ‚Äúinside‚Äù operations kuno nila. 
 
 Nababanggit din yung mga issues na kinakaharap sa PUP, at dahil nga si Kuya Elijah daw ang mas nakakaaalam paano inavigate yung campus politics sa PUP eh siya din yung nagbibigay ng narrative at sagot don sa mga ibang nagtatanong o nagssend ng link sa gc namin ng mga issue. Pinaka-mainit doon yung sa Ignite Concert. Sa totoo lang ang dami ng twist of narratives ang nangyayari at kung hindi masusuri ng mga students ang bawat pahayag eh mamimisdirect sila sa mga nangyayari. Ang pinapalabas kasi nila eh may pagkukulang yung mga dati nilang kasamahan sa SPEAK, at sinabi niya sa isang patawag na meeting na alam niya at alam nila na nasa OSR lang yung mga receipts. 
 
 Ang hindi ko maintindihan eh bakit kaya hindi nila sinabi kung totoong nandoon yung resibo, kasi ang ginawa nila ay itinuro nalang pabalik sa mga organizers ng speak yung pagkukulang tapos yung mga existing student council officers na kasama namin sa gc eh nag-release ng statement nila ng disaffiliation. Hanggang ngayon di ko talaga gets yun kasi malinaw naman na alam nila yung part na need nilang gawin doon sa ignite, at alam nilang tatamaan sila doon kasi natatandaan ko napag-usapan din namin mga candidates na nung nag-file ng inquiry yung mga paralegal namin tungkol sa clarification ng mga certification at clearance na kailangan i-provide sa COMELEC, nabanggit ng mga paralegal namin yung isa sa concern niya eh possible na tamaan daw yung mga iba pa namin kasamang candidates. At nag-agree naman doon si Kuya Elijah, kaya pinaliwanag samin na yun daw yung gagamitin namin case kung madidisqualify daw yung iba sa amin.
 
 Eh pero si SR Lemon naman yung nagpapadala ng sulat sa mga organizers na yun eh. Si SR Lemon na hindi part na organizing committee don sa concert kaya lito ako sa sinabi ni Kuya Elijah na hindi daw nagrerespond yung mga organizers na pinadalahan nila ng sulat na kasama yung mga student councils na involve doon, kaya yun daw yung magbbuild ng case namin na wag idisqualify yung mga candidates namin na matatamaan ng concert. Kung ganoon nga ibig bang sabihin non eh tama na unresponsive din pala yung mga local councils? Kasi kung ganon wala silang karapatan mag-disaffliate kasi di naman yung councils ang sumusulat sa organizers kasi kabilang sila doon. O kung mali man ako, ibig palang sabihin iisa lang yung OSR ngayon tsaka yung mga Student Councils na kasama namin ngayon at pinagtatakpan niya lang mga kasama niya at kaibigan niya para pumabor samin yung sitwasyon? 
 
 Hindi ko talaga kayang tumagal sa ganitong sitwasyon lalo pa at halata namin si Kuya Elijah ang nagbibigay ng instructions kay SR Lemon kung ano ang gagawin at pagttwist ng narrative para mabaligtad kung ano man yung totoo at mapasama ang ibang Partido. Take note, hindi lang naman yung SPEAK inaatake nila eh, pati yung SAMASA target din nila sa election na ito kasi bukod sa Ignite, eh binabanggit rin nila yung unliquidated funds ng SAMASA kaya sabi ni Kuya Elijah at SR Lemon na yari daw sila kapag lumabas na yung mga certification sa IA. Kaya itong si SR Lemon nakikipag-usap sa samasa para kunware ay hindi siya bias pero sa totoo lang eh pinapaniwala at nilalaro niya lang rin itong mga to para hindi siya masiraan ng samasa o kaya nitong sila Kuya Elijah kaya ganon ginagawa niya. 
 
 Ayon, ganon yung mga usapan nila sa groupchat, yung ibang parties. Si Kuya Jake nga may mga pa-‚Äútea‚Äù pang nalalaman sa mga nangyayari daw sa galaw ng SAMASA, kasi sabi kami daw ang target ng samasa kasi seemingly rising at may laban daw kaya sabi ni Kuya Jake ay threatened daw samin yung SAMASA. Ito namang mga kasama ko parang nasobrahan ata sa yabang kaya kung ano ano na naman pinagsasabi tungkol sa SAMASA, pati kulay ng pubmat nila tinitignan at nilalait, halos puro mababaw na usapan talaga andon. Kaya nga pati yung kulay daw ng independent violet or ube kasi yung kulay ng SPEAK at SAMASA pag pinagsama eh violet. Mabuti naman at marunong pa sila sa color wheel, pero di ko lang talaga ma-gets bakit pati yung ganon nirarason nila sa mga gc namin. 
 
 Sa totoo lang, hindi naman kailangan ng malalimang suri para hindi maintindihan ang mga nangyayari. Kaya kaming mga nasa independent/tindig/PUPian at yung mga kasama ko pang iba nakakapansin nito ay narealize namin na niloloko nalang tayo pare-parehas ng mga ito, pati na ang mga Iskolar ng Bayan kaya naman minarapat namin ilabas na yung mga nalalaman sa systematic nilang pandaraya at pagmamanipula sa election. Hindi lang talaga namin kayang i-reveal kung sino kami kasi feeling namin at tanggap naman na namin na at risk kami dahil sa ginawa namin ito at kaya nila kaming balikan anytime dahil marami silang connection. 
 
 Sana sa mga maiiwan at nananatili pa rin sa independent, kung gusto niyo talagang maging independent, kaya niyong gawin yun na hindi nagmamanipulate at sumama sa ganitong gawain. We all know what is happening and we all know that there is something wrong inside.  It in this end that we release this unity statement:
 
 We, Laban PUP, the Sandigan ng mga Mag-aaral para sa Sambayanan (SAMASA PUP), the PUP Students' Party for Equality and Advancement of Knowledge (PUP SPEAK), and the Independent CPSPA, stand united against the intervention of the PUP administration in the ongoing polls and the PUP COMELEC's ardent refusal to let student publications cover the single most crucial step of the student council election‚Äîthe verification of bonafide voters among the electorate.
 
 Under Article IV Sec. 13, Paragraph C, of the 2021 Election Code, one of the powers and functions of the COMELEC is to: ‚ÄúConduct information drives, and orientations to all voters, candidates, and parties regarding the conduct of the online elections.‚Äù In Paragraph G of the same article and section, the COMELEC is also mandated to: ‚ÄúEnact and release clear resolutions stating the platform that they will use for the conduct of the elections, the canvassing of votes, and the platform for regulating the campaign materials an campaign activities.‚Äù
 
 Furthermore, the Code gives clear instructions for the COMELEC in the casting and canvassing of votes, as well as verifying the students who will be voting in the elections. Article VII, Section 31 states that: ‚ÄúPlatform for Elections - The elections shall be held online, the Commission shall have an operational plan that shall serve as their technical guide for the conduct of the elections. This plan shall be made available to all voters, candidates, and interested parties.‚Äù 
 
 The provision for the verification of voters is stated in Section 32: ‚ÄúPeriod of Verification of Bona Fide Voters - The Commission shall have a protocol to ensure that only bona fide students of PUP will be allowed to vote. This period will be determined in the Election Calendar by the SCA.‚Äù
 
 The COMELEC has failed to strictly abide by the provisions stated above. This failure has caused discrepancies and has made the elections non-inclusive, given that there are still students who cannot access their Webmail account, and that the platform was not fully oriented and levelled-off to all the students. 
 
 Before the campaign period started, the COMELEC should have started sending out information and conducting orientations across the colleges, so that the electorate, the paralegals of the different slates and parties, and other interested groups may scrutinize the platform that they will use. Since this is the first online and remote elections in PUP, it is important that everyone is well-versed on its conduct, and should have undergone a series of simulations. In that way, we can rule out any possible opportunity to tamper or manipulate the entire electoral process, and ensure a fair, honest, and inclusive elections. 
 
 Furthermore, the operational plan, as stated in the Code, must be made available to all students, including the voters, for further scrutiny. This document should have been released ahead of time so that the students can familiarize themselves with the platform, and that any issues or problems concerning the platform may be raised, and resolved ahead of time.
 
 The instructions on how to vote using the PUP Webmail Account, that was released by the COMELEC last September 23, 2021, does not satisfy the provisions stating that it must be an operational plan. This late release of the instructions, and the platform is a manifestation of the lack of preparation on the part of the COMELEC, therefore causing the discrepancies of the casting of votes. Moreover, the lack of sufficient time for a proper dialogue and orientation with all paralegals and voters, makes it difficult to identify the possible problems in the casting of votes, which brings us to our current dilemma. 
 
 There have been reported incidents where students can access the precincts of other colleges, aside from their own college. In this situation, any student can actually vote in different colleges, and therefore increase the number of votes for the candidates. To illustrate this scenario, imagine mobilizing and instructing one hundred (100) students from one college, to vote in the other thirteen (13) precincts using their webmail. That can produce one thousand three hundred (1,300) additional votes coming from the same individuals. This further endangers the sanctity of the electoral process.
 
 On the subject of the period of verification of voters, this task of the COMELEC should have been accomplished days before the campaign period. According to the recent meeting between the paralegals and the COMELEC, there will be another verification process with the COMELEC and the Office of the Student Services (OSS), starting on September 29, 2021, during the canvassing of votes. 
 
 Again, we see this mechanism as proof that the COMELEC has failed to conduct an orderly election. The process of verifying whether a voter is a bona fide student or not, should have happened before the casting of votes took place. With the mechanism of the COMELEC, they will be counting the votes, while verifying if the voter is a bona fide student. 
 
 This tedious process will involve sorting out each vote one by one, which will be time consuming and unproductive. It will also be prone to the intervention of the PUP administration since the OSS will have a direct role in the verification process. There is a thin line between ‚Äúadministration coordination‚Äù and ‚Äúadministration intervention.‚Äù As much as we want the COMELEC to be provided with the resources and assistance needed to conduct this election, the PUP Administration must refrain from having a direct role in any mechanism or activity in this election.
 
 Now that we are already approaching the period of canvassing, we must be able to protect the sanctity and integrity of the votes casted by our students and make it free from any malicious or nefarious motive. 
 
 Most importantly we condemn the intervention of PUP Administrators particularly those hailing from the Office of Student Services (OSS)‚ÄîOSS Director John Mark Distor and OSS Chief Abraham Sagun.
 
 Distor was recently removed from office as the Chairperson of the Department of Psychology of the College of Social Sciences and Development after railroading the entry of Hands Off Our Children (HOOC) in our campus to forge a partnership supposedly to provide "psychological services" to those being recruited in mass organizations.
 
 HOOC has long been notorious in endangering the rights and welfare of youth across the country by being a state machinery for red-tagging and spreading black propaganda against democratic dissent.
 
 Sagun, on the other hand, has been tied with a newly established ‚Äúpolitical coalition‚Äù posing as a set of independent candidates, that contradictingly functions as a party, according to an article written by a certain ‚ÄúStar Century.‚Äù Although this article can be a mere allegation or form of black propaganda, it is unacceptable that this election will involve individuals from the administration with questionable ethics, and may add another layer of conflict of interest.
 
 We condemn the PUP COMELEC's dubious relations with the aforementioned office. It is outside the mandate and the jurisdiction of the OSS to hold records of students regarding their admission. Should the PUP COMELEC need to verify the validity of votes based on admission, the Administration and Registrar's Office (ARO) should first be considered. Despite heated arguments during the paralegal meeting yesterday, the Commission stood firm that their partnership with the OSS is "admin assistance," not admin intervention.
 
 Various political parties and candidates in PUP are standing together to assert the right of every Iskolar ng Bayan to a clean and honest student council election. We call for the democratization of the verification process of ballots and for opening each and every step of the student council election to the coverage of PUP student publications.
 
 With all the grounds stated above, we Laban PUP, the Sandigan ng mga Mag-aaral para sa Sambayanan (SAMASA PUP), the PUP Students' Party for Equality and Advancement of Knowledge (PUP SPEAK), and the Independent CPSPA, is calling on the COMELEC to immediately call for a hearing with all campaign managers and paralegals to answer all their questions and concerns with election, particularly the possibility of the votes being tainted and manipulated.
 
 It is only through this action, that we can fully protect the integrity of this election and uphold the right to suffrage of the Iskolar ng Bayan.
 
 The paralegals of the parties and slates who are unified in this position, are currently geared to formally submit a motion to the COMELEC regarding this issue.
 
 We call for the Iskolar ng Bayan to be vigilant in defending the sanctity of the Student Council and its historic role in being at the forefront of the struggle for genuine social change in our campus and the nation as a whole.
 
 The PUP community deserves better. COMELEC, do better.

CHARLIE DEL ROSARIO
 
 Recognized as Martyr on November 29, 2001 By the Bantayog ng mga Bayani Foundation
 
 By: Estelita Del Rosario
 
 Nasaan na si Kuya? (Where is my Kuya Now?)
 
 These are the words emblazoned on the campaign poster calling forthe enactment of an anti-disappearance law in the Philippines. The photograph on the poster is that of Professor Charlie del Rosario, the first Filipino desaparecido, kuya to six siblings.
 
 "Kuya" is the Filipino term of endearment of younger siblings for their older brothers. "Nasaan na si Kuya?" was intended to evoke in the reader the feelings of a younger siblings desperately searching for a dear big brother. But, shortly after the initial mounting of the anti-disappearance campaign posters,the television show Pinoy Big Brother (PBB) gained popularity, so much so that people who see the campaign poster would jokingly claim that they know where Kuya is -he's somewhere in the vicinity of the Big Brother house, supervising the surveillance of the housemates. As the PBB craze swept the country, the word "Kuya" has taken on a new meaning: that of an omniscient, omnipresent entity who calls all the shorts. A veritable panopticon, constantly watching the housemates, closely monitoring every move made and every word said. He has the absolute powerto punishthosewhobreak hisrules and reward those who abide by them. In this way he has total control, ensuring that nobody goes against Kuya's system. The Kuya charater in PBB inspired by the character of Big Brother in George Orwell's novel "1984" on which the television show itself is based. In the novel, Big Brotheris an agent of the fictional State of Oceania who, with the help of ubiquitous high-end espionage devices, is able to see everything that everyone in Oceania does. People who are found to be in any way expressing dissent to the state- in deeds, words, or even thoughts-are abducted. The term Orwell uses for his forcible deprivation of liberty of a person is "vaporization" This act of vaporization is essentially what constitutes an act of enforced or involuntary disappearance. It is an ironic coincidence that people identify the kuya in the anti-disappearance poster, kuya Charlie, with the Kuya in PBB whose character was inspired by the character of Big Brother in 1984. Ironic, because Kuya Charlie was a victim of "vaporization" perpetrated by a "Big Brother" Charlie was last seen mounting campaign posters before he was forcibly disappeared. Now, his is the face gracing the campaign poster decrying enforced disappearance and demanding the enactment of a law against it. Professor Charlie del Rosario, missing for thirty-five long years now, is KuyaCharlie to six younger siblings. To me, he is simply Charlie, a beloved younger brother. I may not be able to answer the question. "Nasaan si Charlie?" But being his only Ate, I can definitely tell you kung sinosi Charlie-who Charlie is.
 
 Who is Charlie?
 
 My brother was born Carlos B. del Rosario. He was "Carling" during his childhood days, "Caloy" in high school, and "Charlie" during his College and professional life. He was born in Sta Cruz, Manila on November 4, 1943, and the second among eight children of our poor parents who worked as market vendors to support the family, endeavoring to provide all of eight of us siblings a good education. We children had to do our share and as early as the primary grades, all of us, including Charlie, had to help manage the family store which exists up to now. Having to divide time between working at the stores and studying did not keep Charlie from excelling in school. My little brother was very much an achiever. He graduated from the Bonifacio Elementary School in 1957 with an honorable mention award. At the Arellano High School, he served as Boy City Councilor of Manila during the Boys and Girls Week; won awards as stage actor, orator and declaimer; represented the school in student leadership and press conferences and upon graduation in 1961, received the prestigious Juan dela Cruz Award for Leadership.
 
 Do not mislead though, his academic excellence does not mean that he was one to avoid mischief likethe plague. Charlie did have his share of "naughty acts." His high school classmates, Professor Loida Yacat of the Polytechnic University of the Philippines (PUP) would relate to me several incidents of the vanishing pan de sal inside her school bag during their physics class, only to see it reappear in the hands of Charlie and his male seatmates whom she would catch clandestinely munching her baon while listening to their teacher discuss the properties of matter and the laws of motion. Charlie's scholastic prowess guaranteed his admission to the University of the Philippines (UP). But, after a year in UP, he told me that he would transfer to a different university. He wanted to use his leadership ability to serve as president of the Student Council, but UP being the vast campus that it is, he acknowledged that his desire of becoming the president of UP's Student Council might not prosper for financial reasons. He then transferred to the Lyceum of the Philippines where he earned his AB Political Science degree in 1966. This move didn't make him the President but Charlie was more than happy to be given the opportunity to offer his leadership skills as Vice President of the student government.
 
 It was in Lyceum where Charlie started to become the student activist that he was until his graduation. He even served as Chairman of the Philippine Delegation to the International conference for the Liquidation of Foreign Military Bases held in Jakarta, Indonesia in 1965. His friends attest that it was Charlie who built the chapters or core groups which later on became the mass bases of future founders of the militant group Kabataang Makabayan (KM). Charlie was one of the founding members of KM in 1964 and was deeply involved in its activities. He was elected as KM's first Vice President National Treasure, General Secretary and Executive Member of the Committee of Advisers in the National
 
 Council. After attaining his AB Political Science degree from Lyceum. Charlie taught at the Philippines College of Commerce (now PUP). Students sought after him as instructor because of his being comic despite being an activist.
 
 He would go to class wearing sandals, which would draw the attention of his students to his feet. When hecatches them looking at his feet. He would say "Hoy, walang patay na kuko yan!" ("see? No dead toenails!") Even when we were little, Charlie always was an amiable individual who had no trouble connecting with any person and blended easily in any group. His warmth and genial disposition stayed with him and manifested itself even inside the Scholarly classroom; quickly endearing him to his students as he incorporated humor in what otherwise might have been overly cerebral collegelectures. Hiscolleagues, onthe other hand acknowledge him for his being an organization man; an outstanding instructor; an effective articulator for nationalism, social reforms and civil liberties; a silent worker who is diligent, trustworthy and dynamic. Charlie being who he is, I had much respect for him despite his being younger than me. It was he who saw the potential teacher in me and suggested that I give teaching a try at the PCC in December 1970 on a part-time basis. Today, thirty-six years later, I am still teaching at the College of Engineering of the PUP.
 
 Where is Charlie?
 
 Six months before his disappearance, Charlie was no longer living with us. He was last seen on the night of March 19, 1971 putting up posters on the National Congress of the Movement for a Democratic Philippines (MDP) at the PCC compound in Lepanto. He was scheduled to attend the MDP meeting in Cubao, Quezon City afterwards. It is believed that the so-called Task Force Lawin, a military unit, abducted and had done away with him. This happened before the suspicion of the writ of habeas corpus and the declaration of Martial law, and therefore he is considered as the first desaparecido or victim of involuntary disappearance in the Marcos regime. Charlie's disappearance was a shattering experience for the family. Our father, Feliciano, would search through newspapers, monitor the radio and television broadcasts for reports on found bodies and would send someone to check if it is Charlie only to find out, every single time, that it's not him. In 1980, nine years after Charlie disappeared, our father died without ever seeing his eldest son again.
 
 As if the pains our family suffered were not enough, our suffering was further aggravated when inthe midnight of June 11, 1974, two truckloads of military men raided our house. Unsatisfied even after opening all drawers and cabinets for undisclosed reasons- and without any search or arrest warrants- we were brought to Camp Crame, where our father and there brothers Reynaldo, Felicito and Manuel were detained while I, along with my sister Teresita were sent to the Ipil Rehabilitation Center in Taguig without knowing the reason why. The military said there was a red alert on because the next day was June 12, Independence Day, so they had to round up all possible suspects. We were detained for abouta month.I became sickand was hospitalized upon release. The temporary release was followed by more than a year of weekly reporting to RECOC IV by all members of the family. We experienced a lot of physical, emotional, and mental torture. I found my locker at the Department of Civil Engineers of the University of the East broken and searched. Many of my friends became afraid to be seen with me. The only visitors I had who bravedthe detention center were my co-members in the Legion of Mary. My brother Felicito was kicked out of the PCC and my youngest brother Manuel was refused readmission in high school and we had to appeal to the military to give him clearance.
 
 My father passed away in 1980. He never got to know that Martial law was lifted. He did not live long enough to witnessthepeoplewar revolution in 1986. He did not know that victims filed a suit against Marcos, and that we won. My father did not have an idea that there would actually bean organization of families of victims of involuntary disappearance, that there would be small but concrete success in the battle against enforced disappearance. All he knew was that Charlie is still missing. After thirty-years, the fate and whereabouts of my little brother are still unknown. We have yet to know where we can recover his body. But we believe that our brother Charlie did not die in vain. The following testimonies are a testament that the life he lived, though unfairly and cruelly curtailed, was a life lived to the fullest:
 
 "He died in the service of the Filipino people and nation."
 
 "Ka Charlie was a staunch nationalist, a firm believer and advocate of our country's right to national sovereignty and genuine independence.
 
 "He advocated the unity of all the exploited sectors and classes of our society, particularly the peasants, and the workers, armed with a worker's ideology that is the best antidote to the exploitation by local and foreign tyrants."
 
 We may never know the answer to "Nasaan na si Charlie?" but as long as we know the answer to "Sino si Charlie?" he can never be truly gone. Whoever was responsible for Charlie's disappearance may think that they have vaporized my little brother, but they never have. And they never will.
 
 #NeverForget
 #NeverAgain

#PUPFreedomWall9270
 
 Isang bukas na liham sa mga PUPians at sa mga kandidato ngayong Eleksyon sa PUP.
 
 Marami sa mga bata ngayon ang hindi naniniwala sa eleksyon. Bakit ba? Sa mahabang kasaysayan ng eleksyon sa PUP, hindi raw nila maramdaman ang mga konseho, marami rin nagsasabi na hindi nila naa-address ang mga concerns ng mga students. Tuwing eleksyon, sariling interes lang daw ang inaatupag at hindi interes ng mga estudyante. Ika nga nila ito ay bardagulan lamang ng mga political parties.
 
 My stand here is here. Remember that these are also students. Yes, maybe we can justify that some of these candidates only wanted to run for their personal interests but it is not the whole. I understand that we hold a higher expectations for these students who bravely attempts to seek office for this upcoming elections but this is just one thing. How about the system that cages us that limit us to move here? What I mean here is that, PUP is a broken system. A lot of slow processes and as students we can only do so much.
 
 If you do not believe in this elections, I do. Because I do believe in the power of the PUPians. You have the power to abstain. If you have the power to elect, then you also have the power to kick someone in your council who does not do their job. 
 
 First and foremost, elections shall be an avenue to champion our calls as students and not just as students but as citizens of this country as the 2022 elections is just around the corner. It does not end with the candidates or with whatever political banner they carry, IT IS ABOUT US. QUESTION THE CANDIDATES. Let's give them the benefit of a doubt as I will also give you one, as my fellow PUPian. 
 
 To end this, I would like to ask each one of you? What have you done for this community? Have you ever stand up for the causes that really matter? Ayaw ko sana sabihin ito, pero sana matamaan tayong lahat na sana lahat tayo may ambag din dito because we can have ambag if we really wanted change kahit hindi eleksyon. So FUCK YOU if galit ka na nga at pipiliin mo pa na hindi makibahagi sa pagsulong because you have the power if you really wanted to.
 
 This election is a double-edged sword for all of us.
 
 VOTE. 
 
 PUP Manila

#PUPFreedomWall9063
 
 My thoughts on the upcoming SCE as a student of PUP for 6 years. (Oo dito na 'ko lumaki lol)
 
 Sa mga kapwa ko iskolar ng bayan, sa mga nakaraang taon naging sobrang gulo at parang bardagulan ang SCE na hindi naman dapat dahil sa SPEAK. Both parties (SAMASA and SPEAK) are promising sa mga campaigns and all pero honestly, sa ilang taon ko sa PUP hindi ko naman nadama ang SC lol. Ilang taon naupo ang SPEAK as SC pero sorry, 'di ko sila ramdam. Ni hindi ko nga sila kilala. I voted for them noon pero nagsisisi ako kasi wala namang pagbabago. Hindi ko ramdam na talaga bang sila ay para sa mga estudyante. Ni hindi nakapag-advocate ng student-friendly policies. When the burden of online classes started, nasaan sila? When students started dropping out because they can't handle the heavy academic workload and juggle their work, nasaan sila?
 
 Gets naman kung sige, naging pabaya sila. Oo nagkamali sila. Oo kinurakot nila yung fund ng IGNITE at mga relief goods na hindi naman nakarating sa mga dapat pagbigyan. Oo sige sabihin natun lahat ng tao nagkakamali para lang i-justify lahat ng 'yan. Pero do they rectify their mistakes? Bumabawi ba sila? Anong ginagawa nila para itama ang mga mali nila? Ilang taon na silang nakaupo at laging nananalo pero they don't make an effort to rectify their mistakes. They think they're all so high and mighty just because SC sila, edi ba dapat nga mas malapit sila sa ating mga estudyante, pero bakit baligtad ang nangyayari? 
 
 One thing's for sure para sa akin ngayong upcoming SCE, I'm not gonna vote for people who don't rectify their mistakes. People who don't take accountability of their mistakes and actions. People who are corrupt and a bunch of liars. Sawang-sawa na ako, just like kung gaano na ako kasawa kay Duterte. Dumating sa point na ayoko na lang bumoto kasi parang walang nangyayari. Which is false dahil kaya lang naman parang walang pagbabago sa Sintang Paaralan ay dahil maling mga tao ang naluklok. At upon looking at the bigger picture and looking at things and situation in a deeper perspective, hindi ako papayag na pati sa PUP SCE ay magrereflect ang baho at gulo ng kasalukuyang national government natin. 
 
 PUP MAIN

#PUPFreedomWall9029
 
 dear incoming freshies, 
 
 sa mga gustong mag psych d'yan, think twice muna 
 
 i'm not discouraging anyone na gustong mag-psych since i understand na there are personal reasons why would you like to take psychology dito sa pup but take it from your kuya na incoming 4th year, marami kayong dapat malaman as aspiring psych students sa pup psych department. 
 
 1. medyo overrated ang psych sa pup. ive seen much better programs under cssd like history and coop na worth exploring if hindi ka pa talaga super settled sa psych. personally, hindi naman ako umay sa program ko after 3 years dito sa department dahil na rin sa sariling sikap nag mag-aral at maging interested sa program ko but i've grown indifferent sa mga quality of lectures minsan. 
 
 2. nasa extremes ang quality of teaching ng mga professors sa psych. i understand na every department naman talaga may profs na parang di dapat binibigyan ng moral license magturo haha char dahil being knowledgeable doesn't equate to having effective pedagogy. i'm not pointing fingers to any specific prof since may kalayaan naman sila practice naman ng academic freedom and siguro may bias lang din ako sa way of teaching pero based on observations, talagang mauumay ka sa ibang profs na di mo sure if sure sila sa tinuturo nila. on the other hand, hats off sa mga profs na from course plans to execution eh magaling and organized talaga. this is not to shame any profs but maybe a call to step up your game in terms of quality of teaching 
 
 3. i know that some psych students are actually smart and compassionate pero kagaya ng nasabi ko above, i don't think the quality of teaching of other professors unleashes the best of these students 
 
 4. maraming profs ang may side hussle sa psych, like admin works sa univ or others stuff. nothing against them because i know para sa credentials nila 'yon (not going technical about it pero ayon basta need nila gawin your for reasons) pero tbh minsan nassacrifice yung quality of teaching nila dahil sa mga other engagements nila. i'm not yet working so maybe di ko pa alam yung tunay na kalakaran sa akademya and i don't mean to sound condescending pero hindi naman siguro rocket science to put teaching and your students as one of your priorities hehe. gugulat na lang kayo di magpapakita yung prof nang matagal na panahon tapos ang rason e admin works pala. sana may regular checking din if nababalance ng profs yung mga engagements nila 
 
 5. sobrang daming section sa psych sa di ko malamang dahilan (maybe for accomplishment reports ng mga admin? haha) kaya ayon di ko rin fully masisi mga profs minsan because maybe they are tired to dealing with numerous sections inside the department and even outside of the department. i know some profs na di na makatao yung teaching loads and i guess it also affects their mh and way of teaching 
 
 6. overall, oks naman mga psych students and not to biased but pansin ko na they are one of the most approachable and compassionate people i've encountered. practicing walk the talk din siguro but ayon depende rin siguro sa dynamics ng block na mapupuntahan mo. di naman maiiwasan yung mga tea and such pero pansin ko sa mga ibang psych students (parang awa wag kunin ang bato na hindi para sa inyo) ang daming out of proportion yung pagiging patola at take sa ibang issues
 
 7. maraming work opportunities aside from being a psychologist pag nag psych kayo, it's a common fallacy din kasi na gusto ko i-address. ma-eexplore nyo pa naman siguro yan habang tumatagal kayo sa program niyo hehe but if amidst all stuff na mangyari sa inyo habang nag-aaral kayo ng psych eh gusto niyo pa rin i pursue ang pagiging psychologist then support lang
 
 8. oversaturated ang research subjects, like sana quality > quantity 
 
 9. wag niyong gagawing personality ang pagiging psych student. iwasan niyong magkaroon ng messiah complex na tingin niyo lahat ng problema ng mga tropa, jowa, o pamilya niyo eh dapat ayusin niyo. it takes mastery para maintindihan na di lahat ng situation ay kailangan ng immediate intervention niyo
 
 10. umay sa mga non-psych subjects na galing yung mga profs sa cs. pasok kayo ng department para malaman niyo bakit haha
 
 11. wag mahihiya mag-approach sa mga ate at kuya and even sa department if may mga concerns kayo. personally, natutunan ko na kahit gaano ako ka-asocial e walang mangyayari sa akin kapag hinayaan ko lang mabulok yung mga acad concerns ko without asking for help. try niyo rin maging involved sa mga student orgs kasi personally marami akong natutunan by joining such pero kapag di niyo talaga feel oks lang yan 
 
 12. pagdating naman sa study habits, wag magrely solely sa mga IMs na binibigay ng profs. matutong magrefer sa journals at books for knowledge acquisition dami namang open sources na mga matterloads online. study smart not hard, tip lang kasi yung ibang profs galing lang online yung mga pa quiz hahaha ewan 
 
 13. isapuso ang mga natututunan sa program dahil nasa panahon tayo ng pandemya and the least you want to be is maging asshole sa ibang tao
 
 pota medyo napahaba. this is my personal take sa psych program and take this lightly dahil baka maiba naman yung experience niyo kapag nakapasok na kayo ng department but sure ako na lahat ng mga nabanggit ko rito ay galing sa aking personal experience. 
 
 final note: regardless anong program pipiliin niyo, mag-aral mabuti at magbahagi ng kalaaman para sa bayan. welcome to pup at padayon!

#PUPFreedomWall9009
 
 For the incoming freshies, sophomores, and transferees who have never set foot on PUP Manila campus: 
 
 Not all buildings and rooms have air-conditioned rooms. Most of the rooms are hot and humid all year round. You'll have to work your way up and down as the sole elevator is not functioning at all. You may take the stairs or slide your way down through the dome (if you can). 
 
 The Oval and Gym are the only places where all the freshies from all colleges and institute gather together to take their PE and NSTP class. There's a building that almost all students/colleges call it their second home - Main Building (or Main). It is confusing where your class is - one side has odd-numbered rooms, and the other has even-numbered rooms but the rule of thumb is always know the correct wing you are heading to. The restrooms are located either on the end of wings, so always remember when you need to freshen up or call of nature comes. 
 
 There are cats roaming around the campus (you can even find a chicken - but is for you to find out where it can be seen), and play with them. Most can be found in the ground floor (odd-numbered side facing chapel). 
 
 You can opt-out in attending Freshmen Orientation either in the Gym or Bulwangang Balagtas. But I'm sure you will be forced somehow. Apart from audio-visual clips and speeches that would probably wish it was quick and over, you will have a taste of being a PUPian. Which means, you would cramped up with a big number of people in a not so well ventilated venue. You are being warned. 
 
 PUP doesn't have much university-wide events but it is up to your respective colleges and departments to have their own "gimiks and ganaps". Any PUP student especially in Main campus would associate a enourmous tarpaulins to Marketing students bringing their A-game in celebrating their department week; the Engineering students most notable for Battle of the Bands even Non-Engineering students would set their sights going in that event. You need to go whenever there are concerts being held in the campus - you can even ask an alumni what is the most notable concert ever happen (pro-tip: ask a Marketing student about it) 
 
 Bonfire will gonna be embedded to your identity as a PUPian. Your parents and friends gonna ask you this, your neighborhood will be curious to know this, and your employer might even ask you this: "Diba kayo yung nagsunog ng silya". So, prepare to answer this inevitable question from the moment you become a PUPian. 
 
 The bathrooms are a no-brainer, it is filthy, clogged, unsanitary for most of the times and most of all it is temporary closed for maintenance. Head over to the NALLRC building if you want a much better to take your nature break, and don't expect a bidet when there's a dipper around to help yourself. 
 
 Wear an ID at all times (sometimes even only upon entering the campus). You forgot/lost your ID? Sneak your way in, improvise or even borrow your friend's ID (shhh don't let everyone know about our little secret okay) 
 
 Trying to enroll using SIS it is a piece of (hell) cake. But it is more painstaking if you are in dire need of extra units or a shiftee/transfree. PUP is not PUP when you haven't experienced Pila Ulit Pila. Try to get beyond 6 units, even the atheists will pray to have their petitions be signed by the VPAA immediately. As they say, "early bird catches the worm" so work your ass off to get the units you need fast. 
 
 Umbrellas will always be a handy tool for you to survive as a PUPian. Does your room feels like hell due to blazing heat and sunlight? Place your umbrella on top of glass jalousies to serve a block in the direct heat. Taking your exams in hallways? Use the umbrella too. So make sure you have your eyes on your umbrellas or else it would gone even on a broad daylight. 
 
 There profs who really good, bad, and worse. Just how diverse the students are, so are the profs. Keep in mind the two grading system, one is the fair system, and the other one is the "roleta/wheel of fortune system". If you want to keep your laude dreams alive, then stay away from the latter at all costs. 
 
 There are nicknames for the buildings across the campus. Main for Main Campus/Building, COC for COC - just keep it classic. CEA which houses the Eng'g and CADBE students. Hasmin for CTHTM and Grad School. Condotel for some SHS students. And everyone knows what real TBA means - Tahanan ng Alumni. 
 
 The campus looks smaller and scattered but it was envisioned before to be like UPD. Find the arch located near ITech and that's were they said to be start of the proposed whole PUP compound. Before you strut your way around the catwalk, check the uneven pavements first or you will have your walk of shame and be an instant laughingstock. 
 
 West Wing got it all for you. Sci cals, ballpens, shirts, lanyards, load, notebooks, blue books, comp shops and a free trip to sauna. 
 
 6th floor is iconic floor. There were many horror stories specifically in Claro M. Recto hall and some stories which are best kept under wraps for now (and its about sex). Feeling hungry, head over to lagoon for a quick bite or make your way to Teresa, the eateries adjacent to CEA or even in SM Sta.Mesa. To complete your eating experience PUP edition, make sure to tick this off your bucketlist. FEWA and submarine (can be found in lagoon), Mango Graham shake in Banana Island(?), G-Spot in COC and the iconic sisigan in Teresa. 
 
 There are a lot of things that I've missed or not included and the list may not fully represent what is like to be a PUPian. I may have left the campus already a few years back but the photos, memories, and experiences makes my stay a very memorable one. The thing I can do for now is to give you a glimpse on what like to be in the campus, and I hope someday, you will have your own version of it. Please make your stay a worthwhile for the rest of us who have finished their journey. Looking forward to have the PUP life you truly deserve.

#PUPFreedomWall8997
 
 For the incoming freshies, sophomores, and transferees who have never set foot on the Ateneo campus:
 
 Not all the buildings have air-conditioned rooms, as a matter of fact, almost all buildings are not air-conditioned. Also, almost all of the buildings are quite old. But there are a lot of trees, and the wind is nice, it's quite like smelling the breeze of Pasig River, especially when you're on West Wing. There's nothing like sitting down on linear park while watching cool people make out and laugh, that's if you can tolerate the smell of the river beside the park. 
 
 There's a building for orgs called Charlie Del Rosario (but please don't ask senior where Charlie is, because until now we also still don't know - and you'll know why soon), and some accredited org has a room there- almost. You'll have to share the room with another org, but it's okay. The rooms are mainly a place to hold supplies, merchandise, and paperwork. But you'll find that some orgs have beds, TVs, and consoles in their room too, who am I kidding? No org has that supply there. It's kinda a place to chill and rest as well.
 
 There are cats on campus, and you can play with them. Sometimes, they'll follow you everywhere especially if you have foods. PUP cats are famous, just check their twitter account and facebook page. 
 
 No, you don't have to call us ate or kuya. We prefer it if you just call us by our names normally.
 
 When you walk into the catwalk towards the freedom park, there are dozens of seniors who wear shorts, slippers, pajamas, or pambahay in general, don't mind them, they dress comfortably depending on the heat of their room inside PUP, but almost all rooms are hot anyway. Don't feel awkward if they look at you, that's probably because you're quite new to the university and you wear your OOTD. 
 
 The entire campus is good for resting, you'll find sleeping people anywhere, like literally anywhere. You can just chill anywhere you want, just make sure that the place will not be occupied by any class or org. 
 
 Inside the campus, you'll see orgs anywhere, there are people dancing across the campus, but their favorite place is the chapel, it's also quite quiet there and conducive for dance practice. Some people you will notice are debating or doing some public speaking trainings around west wing rooms. You can watch a few of their rounds, they will be accommodating. Most orgs in PUP are accommodating and welcoming, so don't hesitate to join organizations while you're inside the university.
 
 Ateneo doesn't have many campus-wide events, but there will be multiple smaller events going on during the same time, each college and departments will have their own celebrations of events, there will be different weeks for each college with different competitions, sometimes they also walk around campus when they have costume competitions. The largest university-wide event in PUP would probably be the founding anniversary- there are events for competitive people like extemporaneous, public speaking, chess, quiz bees, and more. Colleges compete against each other during this time, other PUP campus will also be participating so you get to see and interact with them as well. If you're the chill type of person, there are multiple booths on the catwalk of PUP, you have some bazaars there are small food stalls. These are normally handled by different organizations for their funds and to also participate. 
 
 The bonfire to celebrate UAAP athletes is probably the one time where it's permissible to drink on campus. Go if you have the chance. Maybe Itchyworms will perform there again. - Just kidding, we don't compete in UAAP. But its fun once in a while to watch people practice basketball and volleyball beside the football field, that's if you have an umbrella with you or you don't mind burning under the sun. 
 
 The restrooms are very popular, if you like mango juice with submarine, you'll love it, so let's just not talk about it. If you are looking for a decent one, the nearest would be in Ninoy/Library, because the next decent restroom is in Jollibee Stop and Shop. You'll also find drawings of male genitalia sometimes, don't mind them, that's for random people who want to express their creative side. 
 
 Wear an ID at all times. The guards will not stop you if you don't visibly have it on your person but it's best to just wear it. There are people who wear it normally on their neck, and people who just have it on their hands. The former is more preferred. Although most guards won't care much as long as you present it upon entrance. 
 
 We don't have the Round 1 and Round 2 enlistment system in F2F. You'll automatically have the class list you'll take for the next semester (except when u dropped/withdrawn a class prereq for your next class). It's mostly a block section for majority of the classes so you really don't have to think about enlisting. 
 
 Usually, every end of sem, that's when your prof will show up, for your finals, without meeting you for the rest of the semester. In PUP, you'll have adjustment periods, it's kinda like the season for you to go to SM Sta. Mesa because most likely, there will be no professors who will be attending your class. Sometimes, it's because of the tagging which confuses your profs. I can't fully describe the adjustment period during f2f, it's best you experience it yourself, but it's normally the time that lagoon will be filled with students waiting for their profs. 
 
 Speaking of which, PUP has its own intramuros, or the wall rather, which has all the cheap but awesome foods available for students. Lagoon is a place to chill for everyone, you can eat while observing the matcha water of PUP lagoon. My personal favorite is the tofu sisig and the apple punch for beverage. Your 100 pesos will get you full already. 
 
 People will never leave their phones, laptops, and wallets just hanging around anywhere. A lot of time, people do not normally do it because we dont have laptops to leave, or simply because we don't need them - we have the mini recto/divisoria inside to rent computers and print out your papers. Please have caution if you do the same thing with your umbrella and fan; people will definitely steal that. 
 
 The NALLRC (or Library) is probably the coldest place in PUP, and trust me, most people who are there aren't to study, but atleast get a slight touch of cold air inside the campus. 
 
 There are profs with tattoos. And profs with colored hair. And profs who wear pambahay. And profs who will ghost you. And profs who are openly LGBTQ. And profs who have a better fashion sense than you do.
 
 There are usually no common nicknames for the buildings or places: we just call it west wing, north wing, east wing, and south wing, chapel, CHK building, gym, etc. But there are a few places that have nicknames like the catwalk, freedom park, popeye, etc. Ask any PUP'ian and they'll point where you should be going.
 
 Every year, we also have our own version of UP's popular Oblation run, we call it Pylon Run, or as most people call it, the Kikiam Run or kikiam festival. It's the highlight of the PUP founding anniversary. Some boys experience satisfaction with their size, and some girls receive flowers/roses from the "runners". 
 
 The campus can seem a lot smaller than it actually is, but that's because we're also sharing all the hectares with the Senior High School which is integrated within the main building, and Laboratory High School located in front of the NALLRC, and many other buildings. You can walk from one college building to another college building in less than ten minutes; which, yes, includes the infamous distance between the gate and the 6th floor main building, you'll have to run or walk and climb it by stairs. Some people prefer to go by the Lagoon to get iced coffee when they know they're already late anyway. 
 
 PUP Merchandise has all the PUP merch you need. This includes shirts, hoodies, keychains, flash drives, notebooks, handkerchiefs, towels, gift bags, baby clothes, socks, water bottles, clock, plates...
 
 There are two things that you'll probably find in the corners of a PUP building: a green-yellow-red trashcan, or an armchair up for steal. 
 
 On every wall of the campus, you'll see a quote "This our facility, please take good care of it". PUP must be responsible at all times towards what's left for us in terms of facility. Just take care of whatever room you are using, you might need to plug in extension cord in that room anytime soon for your projector. 
 
 Roleta. Enough Said. 
 
 There are a lot of things I've missed, and this list can't encapsulate what the PUP campus life is really like. There's no way I can put it into words. But I'm no longer part of the University and words and photos and old memories are the only things that tether me back to the life I used to have. The only thing I can do now is give them to you like this, and hope that maybe someday, you can fall in love with the campus just like I did. Please enjoy it for the rest of us who can't go back. I hope you have the PUP life that you deserve.
 
 2019-02***- MN-0

 Nasulat ko to dahil hindi ako makatulog kakaisip sa isang girl. 
 
 I want to share my feelings and experience for someone I like which my is my classmates since freshmen. Sa pagpasok ko sa PUP manila, walang akong kamuwang-muwang because I am outside metro manila and in my mind ay mag-aral lang talaga. When it comes to relationship wala akong kamuwang-muwang dahil I am single since birth and I don't know din kong paano ba manligaw o makipagrelasyon sa girl and di pa talaga din open makipag relationship. And she is also single since birth.
 
 When I first meet this girl nung freshmen, wala naman siyang dating sa akin, normal lang siya sa paningin ko. And siya yong tipo na mabilis mapatawa at medyo mababaw ang kaligayahan. Siya yong kapag nagjo-joke ako panay tawa lang. She always support me kahit korni ang joke ko. I really feel appreciated kapag lagi siyang ganun sa akin kaya tuwang tuwa ako sa kanya. I think don nagsimula yong pagkagusto ko sa kanya. 
 
 When we we're in second year, naging officer siya ng organization, at dahil don naging busy siya dahil sa mga activity. Pansin ko para siyang stress and haggard lagi, dahil na din siguro sa dami ginagawa sa org plus school work pa. Nakita ko kong paano siya nagkaroon ng breakout and acne problem sa face niya, and I know kahit di niya sabihin nagiging cause yun ng insecurities niya at nakakakababa ng confidence and I feel her kc nung time na yun I experienced the same problem sa face. Kaya minsan ginagawa nalang namin joke time yong acne and breakout namin kahit na in both of us struggle sa amin inside. Pero kahit na ganun I still like her. Hindi ko nakita yong physical na kaanyuan niya. Yong mahalaga is gusto ko siya for who she is. And nung time na yun in denial pa din ako sa feelings ko sa kanya. 
 
 Nung 3rd year naging president siya ng class namin at ako president at don nagkaroon kami ng time na laging magkasama. I witnessed yong pag grow niya as a person, she is very responsible president. Kong paano siya nag grow as president don din nag grow yong feelings ko sa kanya. Still, medyo denial pa din ako, di ko pa kayang aminin sa sarili ko na gusto ko siya.
 
 I remember one of the unforgettable experience nung time na merong seminar sa department namin and she is one of the organizer, pag akyat niya sa stage biglang nag slowmow at nag blur yong paligid at siya lang yong center ng lahat, siya lang ang nakikita ko na mga ilang seconds, after that I really feel weird and amazed sa nangyari and medyo di ko pa gets why it happened when I look her. Don ko na unti-unting na realized na I think I like her. 
 
 When pandemic hits, wala ng face to face and medyo wala ng communication sa kanya. Then I think about her don ako nagkaroon ng time na magmunimuni at narealize ko na gusto ko talaga siya at naamin ko sa sarili ko yong totoong nararamdaman ko sa kanya. 
 
 I can't contain the feelings, kaya I decided to confess my feelings, I message her with long message at I created a video confessing my true feelings to her. She appreciate it and I don't expect and demand a return sa feelings ko sa kanya because what's important is nasabi ko na I like her. 
 
 She makes my college life special.
