#PUPFreedomWall8931
 
 Isa akong manunulat. Pero for the first time, nagsisisi akong nagsusulat ako. 
 
 I usually write about people lalo na kung hindi ko masort out yung nararamaman ko sa kanila, romantic or not. Last year, may sinulat ako tungkol sa isang lalaki na kasama ko sa org. May weird chemistry kami pero aware naman ako na walang feelings between us. Pareho kaming taken, at never kaming nagflirt sa isa't isa. Pero pag magkasama kami may weird energy talaga na hindi ko ma-describe. 
 
 Kinailangan ko isulat yung mga inisip ko that time kasi ganun akong tipo ng tao. Nasosort out ko yung iniisip ko sa isang tao o bagay kapag sinusulat ko. So naging entry ko siya sa online journal ko kung saan sobrang dalang ko magsulat. Nakakalimutan ko din kasi na nageexist yun. Pero nag-notif ata one day sa gmail ko na it's been a year since I wrote something. Feeling ko binuksan ng jowa ko yung gmail ko. For what reasons? Di ko alam. Ayun, nabasa niya lahat ng laman nun, pero mas affected siya dun sa entry ko dun sa guy. Yung laman nung entry, finifigure out ko ano ba nararamdaman ko dun sa guy eh sure naman ako na jowa ko na til the end?
 
 Ngayon di ko makausap ng matino. To be honest walang mali sa relasyon namin, at yun yung mas nakakainis. Kasi after I wrote that entry down, na-dismiss naman kaagad sa thought ko. January 2020 pa yun. Pero ngayon, dahil nabasa niya imbis na narinig sa akin mismo, nasasaktan siya kasi di ko sinabi. Eh hindi ko na nga naalalang sinulat ko yun until brining up niya. 
 
 Hindi ko na rin alam. Hindi ko inexpect na magiging problema namin yan kasi kahit ako, hindi ko naman prinoblema talaga. Nagdideal ako ngayon sa suicidal thoughts at anxiety dahil madami na ko problema bago pa yan. Pero at this rate, pag sinabi ko sa jowa ko na hindi ko kayang i-deal yang problema na yan (na hindi naman naging problema talaga sakin) feeling ko mukha lang ako pa-victim kasi siya yung nasaktan. Pero nagsorry naman na ako at nag-explain. Inassure ko rin siya. At bago niya mabasa yun aware naman siya na binubuhos ko lahat sa kanya. Ilang araw na kong stuck sa kama ko tapos dumagdag pa yan na hindi naman dapat namin problema. Kasagsagan ng finals pero imbis na hilingin kong makapasa ako, hinihiling ko mawala nalang ako.
 
 Kahit itong entry na to, nagsisisi akong sinusulat ko. Pero nandito na lang din sa parang dulo. Ibuhos ko na.

 I have a really terrible anxiety/social anxiety, and I feel so depress sometimes. May times na wala talaga akong ganang harapin ang mga gagawin sa school. I'll just sleep and sleep or do what others call productive procrastination (like reading books or managing my small business). Hindi pa ako nakakapag-consult sa professional so I don't really want to self-diagnose, but not being able to name what's happening inside you is just hard. Sinubukan kong magpa-schedule ng free online consultation kaso hindi naman sila nagre-reply. My family don't also talk about mental health kaya hindi ako makapag-open up sa kanila and I can't tell them how much I need help.
 
 Meron naman kaming internet connection pero pinili ko ang modular. Nung face to face classes, I always have anxiety attacks kapag nasa school and I know I can't avoid them kahit online class pa 'yan. I don't post pictures of myself and I'm not comfortable being infront of a camera. I also have a hard time connecting with other people as well as communicating with my classmates. I don't even have friends. Ito rin ang dahilan kung bakit minsan feeling ko hindi ko kayang ma-survive ang college. 'Yong bagong announcement ng CHED? Pagkabasa ko n'on, medyo nakahinga ako nang maluwag. I'm so guilty for feeling this way, especially after seeing the posts of other students who are against it.

#PUPFreedomWall8590
 
 Oppa niyo pagod na irl
 
 Kala niyo ba pareho ang mga Korean sa kdrama at irl? 7 years ko sila nakasama sa iisang school at dorm. May roommate akong Korean ngayon. Wag kayo palinlang sa mga palabas. Masasarap pagkain nila pero sa totoong buhay kahit pogi o maganda nagbabasa lang ng buhok sa umaga tapos pareho lang yung damit na sinusuot 3 days (minsan 1 week) in a row. DI KO NILALAHAT HA. Naging kultura na ata nila yan kasi malamig daw sa kanila at nakakatamad maligo. Yung dinadry cleaning ang damit, nalimutan ko bakit. Pero kumakapit yung amoy ng pagkain nila sa damit nila kaya dagdag amoy din. Parang ganito: yung di ka maliligo tapos puro samgyup, kimchi ulam mo? Parang amoy usok/kulob yung damit tapos ilang araw pa papatagalin. Kakakain din nila ng mga ganun, yung natural na amoy nila hindi favorable minsan. Sa Korea nanuneutralize daw yung amoy somehow dahil ata sa lamig, pero sa Pinas ekis syempre parang impyerno dito eh, mangangamoy barbeque ka. Or sadyang iba lang talaga hangin sa Korea, ewan lols. Kung ikaw yung may thing sa mababangong tao, ireconsider mo mga oppa mo ate. 
 
 Pati ugali nila iba irl, as a normal human being should be. Kung naghahanap ka ng mala-kdramang oppa, good luck. Kilatisin niyo ng maayos yan. May few na nagmmaintain ng hygiene na swak sa culture natin at ugaling kamahal-mahal. Masakit sila mambatok though, kasi tumutunog pag binabatukan nila. Lalakas eh.
 
 Again, hindi lahat ng Korean ganyan. May iilan na mabubuting kaibigan. Maayos at masaya kausap, may sense of humor, lakas mang-realtalk, matalino (lalo sa math), mapagbigay din sila most of the time. Ang sinasabi ko lang, hindi pareho ang mga oppa sa kdrama at sa totoong buhay. Sabi nung isa kong kaibigan, nakakasira daw ng relationships minsan kasi ang taas daw ng expectation sa kanila ng ibang bansa na umakto gaya ng mga oppa sa kdrama. 
 
 Kaya kung ako, dun ako sa Pinoy na madiskarte, matalino, mabango, at hindi DDS. üòÜ

#PUPFreedomWall8454
 
 Nasasaktan ako kasi rare lang yung mga taong nakakaintindi sakin.
 
 Yung personality ko kasi yung tipong malalim makaramdam ng emosyon. Aware naman akong nakakaoverwhelm yun sa karamihan, kaya iilan lang talaga napagsasabihan ko ng tunay kong naffeel. Madaming nago-open up sakin, kasi I seem like the listening type daw. Ayoko kasi iparamdam sa tao na invalid yung emosyon nila. Gusto ko lagi iparamdam na may nakikinig (opo BS Psych ako haha). Years ago meron akong emotional wall at masaya naman ako kasi nailalabas ko yung saloobin ko kahit papaano through art and poem. Oo, may taong kayang di mag-open up sa iba. Masaya naman ako nun.
 
 Then he came to my life at pinaramdam na it's okay to feel vulnerable with him. Na maiintindihan niya ako. "Sabihin mo lahat", he said. "Iintindihin ko", he said. 
 
 Tapos nung isang gabi, nag-express ako ng nararamdaman kong frustration sa kanya sa pag-aaway namin. Sabi ko hindi siya nagsasabi ng nararamdaman niya hanggang sa napupuno nalang siya at nagugulat nalang ako, nagbibitaw siya ng mga words na alam mong may meaning dahil kilala ko siya. Example: "Ganyan ka naman lagi e!" tas ako clueless sa tinutukoy niya. After 4 or 5 years, ineexpect ko naman din kasi na magiging komportable siya sakin sa lahat ng bagay. Nagiging open naman ako sa kanya. Aware naman siyang nakikinig ako sa mga sinasabi niya at hindi naman ako immature gaya ng iba. Sobrang rare namin mag-away guys, once every 2 months lang sa sobrang chill ng personality namin. Lagi kong sinasabi na pag-usapan ng maayos kung kaya naman idaan sa ganun.
 
 Nung isang araw yung chat. Kanina lang siya nagreply (kung di pa ko magchachat kung may balak ba siya magreply) na may sakit siya at di daw nakakatulong mga pinagsasasabi ko. In my defense, hindi ko naman alam dahil yun nga - di nga nagsasabi ng nararamdaman. Ineexpect niya ata manghuhula ako. Nagsorry ako nevertheless kasi may sakit siya at di nga naman makakatulong mga sinabi ko kung ganun. Sabi ko hindi na ako magsasalita. Sabi niya "Mas maganda pa nga kung wala kang sasabihin na matino." Napahinto lang ako kasi inisip ko, hindi pala matino para sa kanya lahat ng sinabi ko. I pick my words wisely. Natutunan ko yun dahil ayoko talaga makasakit ng tao. Tapos lahat pala ng sinabi ko nung naga-argue kami hindi matino para sa kanya. 
 
 Nag-sorry ulit ako na nasaktan ko siya. Sabi ko pagaling siya, hindi na ako manggugulo. Sabi niya, "Mabuti pa nga."
 
 Iniisip ko nalang na kaya niya yun nasabi kasi may sakit siya. Sana nga ganun nalang. Pero bilang isang taong rare lang magbukas ng emosyon sa iba, na open book sa kanya, grabe yung naging impact sakin. 
 
 Di ko alam ilang gabi akong iiyak nito. Di ko na siya nireplyan pa. Di ko alam ano pang irereply sa taong iniisip na mabuti pa ngang hindi ako magsalita o manggulo. Parang gusto ko nalang maglaho, bumalik sa dating ako na walang nakakarinig sa mga sinasabi ko. Ito yung same exact reason bakit kinakatakot ko mag-open up. Akala ko di ko na to mararamdaman ulit, pero grabe yung impact pag sa taong mahal mo maririnig. 
 
 Sorry dito pa ko nagdrama. Hahaha. Ayoko kasi maka-overwhelm ng nakakakilala sakin. Bumabalik nanaman yung takot ko mag-open up. Salamat kung nabasa mo hanggang dito.

 I still remember our orientation program regarding the start of the new set up for this semester. There were guidelines set up for the student's classes, such as the maximum amount of sessions and hours for each class. It made me wonder about something now that we are at the end of that semester. 
 
 Rules are something meant to be followed, right? It's common sense. If one does not follow it, there are consequences for one's actions, mostly punishments for the not obedient. When students don't follow a set of house rules, they get punished for it. Young and old. A rule is a rule. 
 
 Do those kinds of professors ever get the same judgment? If they do not follow such simple rules, shouldn't they get called out for it? It may sound petty, but it looks like an abuse of authority and power for being the superior one compared to their students. A sight so common even in society's current context. 
 
 I would like to ask if my thoughts are valid-- that I am getting my point across. I know it's such a simple case, yet I think that despite you could say it's something small like a small thorn poking your shoe, it is not meant to be ignored.

Pero isang araw malalaman mo nalang. Yung taong gusto mo eh may kasintahan na. Diba parang tanga o ewan lang. Madali lang naman sabihin na di tayo para sa isat isa or di kita gusto eh pwedeng friend nalang ganon.  It's been a year since nagbreak kami ng ex ko. And no, Im not emotional enough to say mahal ko pa rin siya. It's out of my system to be illogical when things are already done.
 
 Pero, after breaking up, nag-uusap pa rin kami. Wala lang. Not necessarily flirting pero as friends. Hindi naman bawal diba? 
 
 It just so happened that i cared for her so much that i want to heal her from the afflictions that ailed her. I should've done that nung kami pa but i guess kinulangan ako sa bayag to do that. But anyway, i still tried. 
 
 I tried to be the friend that she needs. Yung kaibigan na kailangan niya. Yung kaibigan na kasama niya. And as we go down this 'kaibigan' stage, she pointed out things to me.
 
 "Stop," sabi niya. "You know why we stick around? Kasi we're still attached to each other"
 
 And I want to say that it's not true but then again, sino bang matinong tao ang magkakaroon pa ng pakialam sa ex niya. I mean, there are things in the past that should be left in the past. But how can I forget something or someone from the past that made me feel something? Not necessarily sexual ha, virgin pa po ako and i don't intend to take away my virginity. It's just, nakakapanghinayang that we're so alike, so compatible, and yet, hindi kami nagtagal.
 
 Siguro kasi immature pa kami. Afterall, we're still young and there is so much left to learn and to realize. It's just that rushing things is not good.
 
 So we came to the point na we're not bound to talk for a long time. She even said na block namin isa't isa. Well, I agreed but i forgot to block her or i didn't rlly block her. Just so you know, at this point, I still care for her pero i need to get over what is left from the attachments.
 
 So ayun, during the time period, iniiwasan ko makipag-interact sa kanya online. We still have mutual friends and I dont wanna react to those posts lalo na kapag nakatag siya. I don't want to be the sagabal of her recovery.
 
 I managed to ask one of my friends to ask if she's okay. They said na okay naman na siya. I feel relieved na at that point. I want to tell her things kasi I feel very comfortable with her because it feels like looking at a reflection. But i still have to maintain my word of not talking to her for a long time.
 
 Until...nagmessage siya sakin this Valentines day. It's already a year since last na hinaranahan ko siya. It's almost a year since nagbreak kami. And things go back to where they were in the first place.
 
 It feels like I'm going back to the start.
 
 ano reactions niyo mga kapiyups? i feel confused over this, esp na she's already my ex.

#PUPFreedomWall8116
 
 Not from PUP, but I do appreciate the sentiment and goal of the university. Growing up as an academically achieving child, I was always taught not to judge others. But at the same time, I was taught that it was really only the big three that mattered. PUP? Out of the question; I was better than that-- too smart for that.
 
 In a way, it's how a common story you'll hear. UP is for the smart people, and PUP is for those who didn't pass the UPCAT. There's always this clamor and denial that UP is better, but that's the truth. It's a better funded university, it offers more opportunities, and it offers prestige to those who teach and learn. A rich history of achievers and a culture of quality education helps too.
 
 The thing is, people tend to think that being smarter or receiving better education makes them better people. It doesn't. Being smarter doesn't make you worth more than the next person, it just makes you smarter than the next person. Being better educated functions in the same manner.
 
 It's high time for people to accept that not everyone is getting into the top university, not everyone is going to be the smartest person in the room, and not everyone is going to have the same great opportunities at the end of the day. 
 
 There will always be someone who's smarter, better educated, or rewarded with better opportunities. Denying that as a fact is counterintuitive and detrimental to moving forward Filipino society to a more nuanced and more understanding conception of education-- who gets it, why they get it, and what happens when they get it.
 
 At the end of the day, it makes a difference who went to UP, who went to ADMU, who went to DLSU, and who went to PUP. 
 
 It shouldn't. The first step to moving forward is understanding that not all schools and not all students are created equal. Some schools will always have better facilities and better education. But understanding and accepting that is the first step to raising up the less fortunate educational institutions to a level that we can all collectively be proud of.
 
 - UPeep

#PUPFreedomWall8098
 
 Miss ko nang pumasok sa Sintang Paaralan, kaya bigla kong naalala yung mga huling alaala ko sa school nung face-to-face pa ang klase.
 
 Sa grupo naming magkakaibigan, halo ang babae at lalaki. Sa fourth floor madalas ang klase namin, at sinuswerte kami sa schedule dahil madalas, hapon na nagsisimula ang mga klase namin, so mga 11am o 12nn. Dahil hapon na ang start ng mga klase, madalas kami inaabot ng gabi sa PUP. Marami kaming mga kaklase na palatambay sa classroom fahil hinihintay yung PNR, kaya hindi na bagong may tao sa fourth floor ng West Wing hanggang mga 9pm. Normal na yun.
 
 Isang araw nung December 2019, napagdesisyunan naming magkakaibigan pagkatapos ng klase na magpunta sa Gateway Mall o kahit saan sa Cubao dahil patapos naman na ang taon. Kumbaga, bonding bago magbakasyon. Syempre, pumayag kami lahat. Nung dismissal na, meron kaming kaibigan, si M. Ito kasi si M, laging lowbat ang cellphone. Asa rin siya lagi na may dala naman powerbank yung isa naming kaibigan kaya lagi siyang nakikihiram. Kaso nung araw na yun, lowbat din yung powerbank ng isa naming kaibigan, kaya napilitan siyang mag-charge sa classroom namin. Sabi niya kahit 30% lang daw ang battery, hintayin namin siya. Kaya yun ang nangyari.
 
 Nang magtayuan na mga kaibigan ko, syempre sumama na rin ako. Malapit sa pintuan ang pinwestuhan ko para mahangin. Sira kasi yung electric fan ng room, as always. Lumabas na kaming magkakaibigan, at nagulat ako nang tuluy-tuloy silang naglakad papunta sa dome na para bang hindi namin maiiwan si M. Paglingon ko kasi sa classroom, nandon pa rin siya sa likod ng room, malapit sa saksakan.
 
 Sinigawan pa ako nung kasama ko nung naghihintay lang ako sa room, dahil ayokong nang-iiwan ng kaibigan. Nasa dulo ng fourth floor ang room namin, kaya naman kita ko na kung aling mga room ang wala nang ilaw tas bukod sa room namin, may dalawa na lang ata na meron pang mga nakatambay, naghihintay rin siguro sa PNR. Tanaw ko sa pwesto ko sa tapat ng room na yung mga kaibigan namin ni M e tumigil sa dome, para siguro hintayin kami.
 
 Sumandal lang ako sa railings at tinignan ang lagoon, hanggang sa tinapik ako ng kaibigan ko na naiinip na raw kanina pa raw sila sa dome. Ano raw bang hinihintay ko.
 
 Sinabi kong si M, nagcha-charge pa sa loob. Akala ko pa hindi na siya sasama kaya bigla silang lumabas ng room at iniwan siya. Nagulat na lang ako na sabi nung kaibigan ko, kanina pa raw sila lahat sa dome, kasama si M. Ako na lang daw ang hinihintay nila.
 
 Napalingon ako sa loob ng classroom, at ayun, wala na nga si M sa loob. Naguluhan ako kasi hindi ko naman nakita o narinig na lumabas siya ng room. Ugali rin ng mga kaklase ko na mag-babye kapag may lalabas ng room, kaya imposible na hindi ko napansin.
 
 Napatingin ako sa dome tas yun, nakita ko nga si M na kasama na sila roon.
 
 Hindi ako nagsalita, pero weirdong-weirdo ako nun. Inisip ko tuloy kung imahinasyon ko lang ba yun o totoong nangyari dahil marami rin namang nakukwento ang professors namin sa fourth floor ng West Wing, lalo na sa mga dulong classroom.

Nakakamiss mga pupians na kahit ngarag at crinam yung gawa, sure kang hindi nag s-settle sa average at mediocre outputs. I don't intend to romanticise poverty pero sa na witness ko sa mga pupians noong shs, kahit huling pera nalang sa bulsa ang meron para makagawa ng project, they still see to it na makakapagpasa sila nang maayos at maganda. Namaximize 'yong oras sa pagtuturo at kwentuhan kung gano kaputangina ng current administration. Naalala ko midterm exam namin, wala sa ppt at tinuro 'yong mga tanong hahahaha. Nasa chegg at quizlet. Meron iba napapansin ko hindi na rin kumakain ng maayos kasi magkakano lang ang pera sa bulsa.
 
 Nakakalungkot lang kasi may ibang prof (madalas fulltime) na kapag magdemand sa project akala mo privileged mga students nila. Hindi marunong magset ng budget for a project, hindi rin marunong magcanvass muna. Meron pang iba may paregalo pa dapat.

 I left PUP with these impression sa mga profs nila; maraming nagsasamantala sa kahirapan, marami rin ang nagbabadya dahill kailangan ng mga studyante ng maayos na grades. Nakakahiya. 
 
 Although may mga naging kaibigan akong prof na maayos at matitino, pero bihirang bihira; halos bilang sa daliri sa isang kamay.

Pangarap ko rin po makapag time travel, pasubok naman. We appreciate nga po pala yung activity na about sa "libro" ninyo, nakakalawak po ng isipan (kung naintindihan lang sana namin mga formula). Anyway, full of surprises po kayo... Sana lang po di totoo tsismis about the wheel of fortune ninyo kasi di nakakatuwang surpresa yon.
 
 To prof. #3, ang bilis niyo po magturo, halatang alam na alam ninyo lesson niyo. It's a good thing, at least we know we can ask you for clarifications pero sana wag po masyadong intimidating. We can add nga po pala na maging considerate po kayo regarding the submission of activities. When it is the app acting up, wala na po kaming magagawa don kahit sobrang aga naming magpasa. Kung ayaw ni app magpasa, ayaw niya talaga. Hindi po lahat may stable wifi connection. Hindi po lahat may reliable medium for ol class (i wish lang lahat kami may cellphone man lang). You say na nandaraya lang din naman kami implying na okay lang mapressure? Lugi naman po kami don. Moreover, na-late na ng pasa (which is hindi naman talaga kasalanan, prepared for that talaga sadyang di pinalad sa technicalities), may deduction pa. Okay lang po, since ito ang 1st time. Oo nga pala, that one time na bigla pong ikaw ay nagpa seatwork, uploading the night before, then may di nakapagpasa due to valid reasons naman. Sana po tinanggap niyo rin kahit may deductions. Aren't medical reasons enough for an excuse? Sa pagkakaalala pa nga po pala namin, nakalagay sa memo na bawal ang graded recitations as well as attendance. Bakit po ginagawa niyo? Is it safe to say na nandaraya ka rin?

 hi amvians! 
 
 just a concerned senior here specially to students who use reading rooms. Stay quiet or silent please. The purpose of that reading room is so we can study in a quiet environment pero lately mostly freshmen and sophomores sobrang ingay at nagdadaldalan nalang. Please go outside sa gazebos or just stay in a free room kung gagawin nyo yon. Nakakairita kasi kahit magearphones ka na mas naririnig parin yung ingay. Just go stay at cafes or somewhere na allowed yung malakas nyong boses. 
 
 Also, tuwing exam season din. Please do not stay outside the rooms like corridors and all kasi nageecho din yung ingay nyo. Yung mga gagamit para maglesson or magexam after nyo hindi makapagfocus kase rinig yung ingay dahil sa pagtatanungan nyo ng ano ang naging sagot. I mean kahit kami rin naman after exams nagtatanungan if same ng sagot pero keep your voice down or lumabas muna ng building before asking kasi nakaharang na nga sa daan nageecho pa yung ingay.

As an introvert, wala ako masyado naging friends sa kabatch ko, especially lagi kaming nagpapalit-palit ng block every sem. And last year, before the Agape and Paskuhan, I've already decided to go by myself to those events, pero nung time na dumating yung Agape, dun ko naramdaman yung lungkot ko na mag-isa lang ako. There's a lot of people with their circle of friends. May mga nakita din akong mga kabatch ko pero nahihiya akong lumapit sa kanila kasi di ko naman sila kaclose at may mga kasama na sila. Akala ko okay lang na mag-isa lang ako pero pag nakakakita ka pala ng mga tao sa paligid mo na may mga kasama sila, nakakalungkot. After I got my food I went back to dorm immediately. When I discussed it with my friends to hear their side and verify the truth, I was shocked. What actually happened was completely different from what this person had told me. Furthermore, it's concerning how this person consistently paints others in a bad light while presenting themselves as the victim. It's puzzling how they effortlessly damage others' reputations while portraying themselves as the one who's been wronged. 
 
 After my friend told me what actually happened, I suddenly began to wonder: What if all the stories this person told me about the other people from our course weren't actually true? I had personally met these people, and my encounters with them were positive. This person even spread a scandalous rumor that raised suspicion. As a result, we decided to approach the students this person had talked about to verify the truth. To our surprise, it turned out that the stories were false. This revelation shocked us because we had believed that these individuals were bad based on the fabricated stories. It's a cautionary tale to remind everyone to be vigilant. Frankly, I'm uncertain about this person's motives‚Äîperhaps an attempt to undermine our batch, I guess.
 
 If the person that I am talking about is reading this post, I just wanna say that I am very disappointed in you and I hope hindi ka na ganyan in the future sa magiging new friends mo.

 Hello. I'm asking for help or advice. Tatanggapin ko lahat ng criticisms bcs I believe I made a big mistake here.
 
 I'm a graduate student na and currently reviewing for board exam AGAIN. Yes, I did it again because I failed to pass the board exam the last time I took it. During my first season of review, I met a Muslim guy who was also a reviewee of the same review center that I enrolled. I was the one who approached him first because I was asking for review files that time. And the story follows.
 
 We because close friends to the point that we always talk to each other EVERY SINGLE DAY. We also shared some thoughts and ideas on what we have learned during our review session. We became study buddies that time until things changed. He confessed his feelings for me. I got confused that time since I was not yet ready for any commitment. But I accepted his confession and entertained him. The conversions went deeper and deeper until I found myself falling for him, too. I was happy with him. But I never tried to confess.
 
 He's so kind, sweet, gentle, and funny. He's actually a walking green flag guy. The only thing that kept me hesitant that time was our religion difference. I am a Christian girl and he's a Muslim guy. I know love sees no boundaries but it's hard to deal with. That's what holding me back.
 
 Two months before boards, he told me that he's going abroad for work and study. I actually stopped him from leaving but I can't control what's coming. He needs to grow and who am I to stop him growing? I let him go and enjoy. In an instant, he's not here already in the Philippines.
 
 Things get harder and harder for us. We barely talked to each other because of the time difference and busy scheds. I also asked him how long will he stay in America ‚Äî how long will I have to wait for him. And all he was saying was "I don't know how long."
 
 I got tired and hopeless. I promised to wait for him but how long? I broke my promise to him and entertained another guy.
 
 I met the other guy through a group chat of reviewees. He approached me first and started teaching me about the board exam topics. Everything was in favor for me because I actually needed someone to teach and help me understand the topics. 
 
 At first he was just teaching me through messenger until we both found out that we live only meters away. I insists to go to their house so that I would be comfortable for us to teach and learn. And the routine continues until the day after boards.
 
 We were still okay with that Muslim guy that time although we're lacking of communications already. That day I confirmed that I failed the board exam, this Muslim guy called me and comforted me even if he's too far from me. Meanwhile, this other guy told me to went to their house to celebrate our failure (since he didn't pass too). Little did I know, something instant just happened that time.
 
 We were just watching movie and enjoying the food served in the table when this guy suddenly asked me if he can hold my hand. I gave him a confusing look but still gave him my hand until I found myself lying in bed and kissing him.
 
 I went home talking to myself what just happened. 
 
 The next succeeding days went deeper and deeper. I started entertaining that guy and doing the things what couples do. On the other side of myself, I felt sorry for that Muslim guy. 
 
 One night, I called this Muslim guy and told him everything. I was crying and kept on saying sorry. I told him that he don't deserve me and everything was my fault. But he also said sorry and tried to understand the situation. Still, it's all my fault. The phone call stopped and he immediately cut the communications between us.
 
 As of now, I am still entertaining the other guy. I admit, I am enjoying his accompany but still, there's a part of me that keeps me coming back to that Muslim guy. :(

 hello, socially awkward freshie here. i remember when i was younger that getting to college will give me a good networking opportunity due to the vast connections i can get with a lot of people from diverse backgrounds and diverse fields due to the many careers and degree programs that the university offers. one thing na i'm struggling with is that people easily find me off-putting which i can easily imply by their non-verbal language and how i could see them interacting with other people whilst being dry when they interact with me. keep in mind, i'm personally somewhat introverted myself so i struggle at even starting conversations to begin with. this applies not only in uni but also in the general aspect of my social life as well.
 
 the thing is however, somebody (outside of uni) brought up to me na i am narcissistic/have narcissistic tendencies daw. at first i could not believe it because at first i thought na i do not "fit" this definition, but after looking it up i realized that maybe what they said about me is true...which is what i reckon to be the possible reason why a lot of people dislike me in the first place.
 
 ang problema lang kasi is i don't know if what i'm doing is narcissistic at large and i just don't know if the actions that i made are the ones that should not be done. i just could not spot the right and wrong things myself since i mostly don't think about the consequences of my actions not until i see a negative reaction or until people bring it up to me that what i did is wrong. minsan na nga lang i just wish na i could watch myself in third-person para aware ako sa mga ginagawa ko huhuhu.
 
 sobra lang ako nahihirapan kasi i'm going to turn 20 in a few months and if there's anything i want to leave in my teenage years it has to be this. i want to change so bad and gusto ko lang maging outgoing in my adulthood especially when it comes to my fellow college-mates, thomasians, fellow career pathtakers, and just people in general pero i reckon that this happens to be my biggest hindrance. ang (advanced) birthday wish ko is alam ko kung saan ako dapat magbago and kung ano ang mga dapat kong gawin at di gawin kasi ayaw ko na to ma-ulit :(((

 Hello nurses! Okay pa ba kayo? Akala ko yung semestral break ay "PAHINGA'' pero puro duty. For me okay lang naman mag duty pero sinabayan pa nila ng ORAL REVALIDA. I want to move and request for a postponement of the oral revalida and the hospital duties because I am feeling extremely stressed and burnt out. My life is not just about school or studying. We have other responsibilities and problems outside of our academic lives. I also want to address the fact that not all of us have the same privileges or resources. Some may have personal struggles that require more attention and time. We should not judge each other for our decisions but rather support and understand each other's circumstances. Moving our oral revalida is not a sign of weakness or laziness. It is a responsible decision that shows we know our limits and are taking care of ourselves. I hope that the oral revalida date of level 3 & 4 can be moved, but not January, please. We are not asking for special treatment, but we are simply pleading for understanding and empathy. Let us not forget that we are not just students; we are also human beings with needs and limitations. I hope that this letter will be taken into consideration, and our voices will be heard. #nursingstudent

#CEUFW FW #27620
 Dami nagrereklamo rito pero dami ring di ko alam kung engot o sinasadya dahil nagfleflex ng grade. Magbasa kayo ng student handbook nandon nakalagay lahat ng qualifications sa PL/DL, latin honors at iba pa. 
 
 1. Qualified ba ang transferees mag latin honor?
 Sagot: Hindi. Unless nag shift ka at lahat ng subjects sa curriculum eh kinuha mo sa CEU at hindi sa dati mong school, hindi nagbibigay ang CEU ng latin honor sa mga transferee.
 
 2. Paano mag-apply as PL/DL?
 Sagot: Mag aannounce ang registrar o department clerks sa email. Otherwise, pumunta kayo sa website ng registrar. https://ceumnlregistrar.com/ourscholar/index
 https://ceumktregistrar.com
 https://ceumlsregistrar.com
 
 3. Anong grade kailangan para mag PL/DL?
 Sagot: PL - 1.20 at walang grade na mas mababa sa 1.75 sa lahat ng subject at kailangan regular load. Kahit irreg ka basta regular ang load ng units.
 
 DL - 1.21-1.50 at walang grade na mas mababa sa 2.00.
 
 4. Kapag irreg ba pwede mag apply sa PL/DL?
 Sagot: Oo nga basta regular ang load ng units.
 
 Lahat ng tanong niyo either nasa handbook o nasa website ng registrar. Magbasa kasi di yung gusto niyo isusubo sa inyo yung sagot lage

 My boyfriend expects me to do everything in our relationship. He expects me to plan and pay everytime we go out. We wouldn't even go on dates if I don't ask him. At first, it was okay for me, given his financial situation that time. It felt wrong lang when I noticed that he can buy expensive stuff for himself naman pala but still lets me pay for our dates. I tried confronting him about this already and he agreed to taking turns in paying. The agreement did not last long as he went back to his old ways after just a couple of weeks. 
 
 I tried convincing myself na babawi siya on other aspects, but no. He does not give me any reassurance, rarely compliments me, and would leave me on delivered and ghost me whenever I try to confront him. He'd rather spend time with his friends than with me. He would rarely update me when he's out with them. When he's with me, he's always on his phone, talking to them, and rambling about his friends' gala that he missed. He even lets his friends disrespect me. 
 
 I envy other girls who get princess treatment from their significant others. No sidewalk rule, carrying my bags, opening the door for me, and offering to buy or get my needs. He just wont do these things if I dont ask him (which seems forced). I don't feel special when I am around him. Don't get me wrong, I really do love him. It's just disappointing that it feels like I am the only one exerting effort on our relationship. This gets even more tiring because he refuses to listen to what I have to say.

 Even as I navigate dating and romance apps and media, I am taunted by the abundance of love surrounding me. They are a reminder of things that I can feel but will never experience. They will always mock me and the void in my heart that runs as deep as I can love. Every hand I see holding another will always make my hand feel empty. Everytime I watch or read romance stories I am taunted by this beautiful thing that I can never have. Like Tantalus, I will reach out to the fruit that will feed my starving soul but the branches would move away and remind me that i am destined to be hungry for all of eternity. They say that grieve and pain are the prices we pay for love but why can't I even feel that I paid for something. Why is it always pain and suffering to love as I do? When will I win? Or should I concede? Accept the fact that pain is worse than a life filled with loneliness? I don't know anymore.

I've been through the awkwardness of being left out, and it's not cool. You guys make plans, and there's an event, but I'm not invited. Then you'll ask if I want to join? Seriously?? If I wasn't invited from the start, why would I want to join? Kung kakain din kayo a simple aya would mean a lot to a person. Words like, "C'mon let's eat sa A2 you want to make sama?" (pero sana wag kayong indecisive and think of the persons' budget). Another thing, let's not do the whole backstabbing thing. Trust me, word gets around, and there's always someone who spills the tea. Karma always finds its way. Lastly, please don't forget to greet your friends on their special days or when they achieve something. A simple happy birthday or congratulations would mean a lot to them, you know? Your effort kahit walang gift (gift is not required) to greet someone on their birthday is so memorable and sapat na 'yon. Sometimes kasi pag may ibang kaibigan na may birthday, todo effort kayo na batiin, pero pagdating sa isang tao sa grupo niyo, walang bumabati at napilitan lang. Spread KINDNESS y'all <3 Let's make the world a better place!
 
 If you ever need someone to talk to or a friend, just care react then i'll hit you up, and let's be friends. Who knows? We might discover some common interests!

 As a graduate student (hindi UPD ang aking undergrad school), I'm taking subjects from other colleges and institutes, aside from my home college, because the Program of Studies is designed that way.

This information should be available on their websites (wala ako mahanap mga dzai sa website nyo or kahit sa pages, kase honestly kung pupuntahan natin ang concerned college or institute time consuming, baka pwedeng ilagay nyo nalang sa website).  The summer break has concluded as Formula 1 returns to the track for the Dutch Grand Prix in Zandvoort, and it was an outstanding race. From the changeable conditions from just the first lap to the end to the several battles up and down the field, this race may just be the best one yet. Not only that, it is a record-equaling race as well.
 
 It is nine wins in a row for Max Verstappen, and he equals the record with Sebastian Vettel with the most consecutive victories in a single season. Despite the changing conditions to clinch his third home win in a row, he was still his dominant self. With this form, he can easily break the record next time in Monza. Sergio P√©rez may be disappointed with his race though. He had a fantastic start as he gambled on the intermediate tires after the first lap when the rain hit which granted him the lead of the race a few laps later. He was undercut by his teammate afterward, but he has been running second for most of the race. However, it all unraveled for him towards the end of the race. When the heavy rain came, he slid off in the first corner on intermediates before pitting for full wets, but he hit the wall on the pit entry and sped as a result. He was issued a penalty, and all his hard work came undone as his podium result turned into a P4 finish. It is not as bad as people may think, but it is not what P√©rez wanted though.
 
 Aston Martin seemed to have returned to their original form from the start of the season as their upgrades have been a success so far. Fernando Alonso returns to the podium since Canada and he appears much happier than before. The car was fast throughout the weekend and Fernando's morale levitated. He made great overtakes during the race too like taking the low line in turn 3 to pass Russell and overtaking Norris on dry tires while it was raining. Overall, a second-place finish is just what he and the team needed after a few races of average finishes and running. However, Lance Stroll's running and finish were nothing but average. Another poor qualifying yields another poor result for the Canadian, and he did not even score a point as well. Maybe he should be turning his attention to tennis now at this point because no matter how much love the team has for him, it almost means nothing in terms of his results in the end (tennis joke yall please laugh).
 
 Alpine had a mega day, especially in the race. Neither of their drivers did not even make it into Q3, most notably Esteban Ocon making a shock Q1 exit. They had to do whatever it took to salvage their race, and it seems like the rain and strategy have been a miracle for them. Just like P√©rez, Gasly took the opportunity to pit for intermediates on the first lap, and he made his way up into the top 5. What's more impressive was that he stayed there and even defended and battled Carlos Sainz in the Ferrari. He may have gotten a penalty mid-race, but he was able to serve it in one of his pitstops, and in the end, he was rewarded an incredible P3. It is his first podium with Alpine and his first podium since Azerbaijan back in 2021, so it was quite a long time coming for the Frenchman. With this sort of pace they have, they are hoping that it would be enough to battle McLaren and reclaim fourth in the constructors championship.
 
 It was not a good qualifying for Ferrari. In Q3, Charles Leclerc crashed after understeering into the wall while Carlos Sainz only qualified sixth. Then in the race, they only had Carlos Sainz to rely on throughout its entirety. This was because Charles Leclerc incurred front wing damage on the first lap alone, and the piece of debris from it surprisingly struck the floor and it too incurred damage as well. Despite pitting for intermediates that put him up into the top 5, he was losing lots and lots of pace, and he only went backward as the race progressed. He eventually had to retire as a result. Going back to Sainz, he struggled to defend and even get past Gasly. He had a superior car than the Alpine, but given the fact that the latter was strong in corner speeds, it was difficult for the Spaniard to find a way to overtake the Frenchman. Then in the restart after the red flag, he had to defend from Lewis Hamilton, which he was able to do, but he lost ground to Gasly ahead. Bear in mind that he has yet to score a podium so far this season, and this race was the closest he has been to achieving that. Unfortunately, he is going to have to wait for a little longer.
 
 Mercedes had an awful start to the race. It was very uncharacteristic of them to make such a poor strategy off the bat. The team strangely let both of their drivers stay out on dry tires while the rain continued to fall, and when they pitted both of them, they were far out of the points with Hamilton in 16th and Russell in 18th at one point. George Russell during the race displayed his dissatisfaction with Mercedes' strategy after he was promised by the team that he was meant to be running in the podium places. However, when the track dried and pitted for dry tires once again, their pace elevated. They made their way back up into the top 10 as the race went on where they were supposed to be in the first place. When the red flag came out, they were running sixth and eighth and were set to have both cars scoring points. However, when the restart happened, that was not the case when Russell made contact with Norris and the former got a puncture that tumbled him down to last place. Lewis Hamilton tried to find a way past Carlos Sainz, but he held back several times and finished a lowly sixth. According to the 7-time world champion, the car had the pace to fight Verstappen for the victory. If that were the case, this was a massive missed opportunity, and it was thanks to a self-inflicted strategic error from Mercedes.
 
 McLaren and Williams were the stars of qualifying. Lando Norris qualified an amazing P2 once again and Oscar Piastri in P8. There was a slight chance that they would have gotten pole, but their result was just as good. Alexander Albon was outstanding as he nearly qualified in the top 3, but P4 was still an impressive result for the Thai driver. Logan Sargeant made his first Q3 appearance by just making it into the top 10, but all of that celebration came to an abrupt end when he crashed by his own doing after just two laps. These two teams were hoping for big results thanks to their grid positions, but just like other teams, it all unraveled on the first lap alone. Both teams also made an odd decision to let their drivers stay out, and they were swallowed up by the pack in almost an instant. McLaren were able to go back up the field, but their finishes were not ideal with Norris finishing seventh and Piastri finishing ninth. The car had pace for the podium or even a win if they were that strong, but the rain and their strategy ruined any chance. Williams will be just as disappointed. Alexander Albon was running sixth at one point, but the heavy rain caught them out once again, and finished eighth. The fact that the team was disappointed with the result shows how far Williams has gone. Being last in most of the races last year was now an afterthought since being near or in the points has been the mindset. However, Logan Sargeant will want to forget this weekend. He crashed out once again, but it was due to a hydraulic problem that made the car not function at all. He was not at fault for the crash, but he was still completely devastated. He had his head down and his tone when being interviewed was low. It was a tough weekend to go through for the American driver.
 
 The bottom three teams in the constructors championship finished out of the points yet again. For Haas, they had a decent start with Kevin Magnussen running in the points after pitting for intermediates. However, neither he nor Nico H√ºlkenberg had any pace in their machinery to be near the points despite the changing conditions. Alfa Romeo had an amazing start with Zhou Guanyu running in the podium places after benefitting from the other drivers ahead of his pitting for intermediate tires the lap after. However, he went backward as well and was running out of the points until the rain hit. He pitted for intermediates early once again in the hopes that he would go up the field once again, but the rain got heavier and it caught him out. He aquaplaned on the start-finish straight and went straight into the barriers at high speed. He was out of the race while Bottas finished down in P14. AlphaTauri did not expect to have this type of weekend. They lost Daniel Ricciardo due to an injury he incurred in practice and was replaced by Liam Lawson. The Kiwi did not have much time to prepare due to FP3 being compromised by rain. In fact, he crashed during that session, so he was heading into qualifying and the race on the back foot. He qualified last for the race while his teammate Yuki Tsunoda was hit by a grid penalty for impeding Hamilton. In the race, Lawson had a good battle with Leclerc in the middle of the race while Tsunoda was running near the points. By the time the restart occurred after the red flag, both drivers were running well and in the end, Liam Lawson on his F1 debut finished a decent P13 while Tsunoda finished P12 but he was hit with a penalty for causing a collision, so he ended up P15. At the moment, Ricciardo is still not fit to race in Monza, so Lawson will be getting a second and proper chance in the next race. Hopefully, he will show his true potential if he does replace him once again.
 
 The second half of the season has started off with a splash, and with back-to-back races coming up, who knows what Monza can deliver? Hopefully, it would be just as good as this race because it was a banger.

 Unpopular Opinion: UPX cats NGOs are band aid at best and should do more than just feeding and TNVR
 
 The main issue is cat and dog ferality, which is damaging at worst on the natural biodiversity of UP campuses. Some might argue "but how about the rats and mice". We naturally have ratsnakes and wolfsnakes for that, unfortunately ratsnakes aren't as cute as cats for us to care about them. They are even killed by solely existing, but I digress. 
 
 These NGOs should also function as a voice for owners to be more responsible, promote and remind society to vaccinate their own pets and keep them safe inside their home as the existence of feral and roaming pet animals itself is the root cause of the problem of having uncared pets/ferality. No pets should be allowed to roam freely as the outside is dangerous for any loved animals, nature is both giving and unforgiving. We should promote pets with a healthy lifespan reaching their peaks at 12-18 years old, not being hit by a car at 3 or being picked up by other feral animals (i.e. dogs) at 2. Outside they too are vulnerable to predation from pythons, birds of prey, dogs, etc... And as much as we find them cute and fun to be with outside, we should promote a culture where pets running feral and living the dangerous wild game should not exist. Besides, aside from the Visayan leopard cats, our country is not prepared to hold another foreign mammalian mesopredator on the loose.
 
 It is like running a community pantry, their existence is good but it also that means there is not enough support from the government or society and that there exist a more fundamental problem that needs to be addressed. As long as this isn't being addressed, outside non-vaccinated/neutered cats would fill up the niche of the dead campus cats/dogs and the cycle continues.
 
 We are at UP, we should bring more of our voice out, start being a responsible pet owner ourselves and propagate more of this message, so that the remaining cats or dogs that we may feed would be the last ones of their generation living their nice lives.
 
 Please post this admin as pets need a good life too, and not just being orphans on a world and culture we created.

 As for what happens after college, I'm still lost but that doesn't stop me from finding answers. PROBABLY THE MOST LASALLIAN THING I'VE EVER ENCOUNTERED IN MY 2 YEARS IN MANILA

I commuted by jeep from pedro gil to p. ocampo, and there was this girl in front of me on the opposite side of the jeep. At first, I didn't notice she was a Lasallian. I just minded my own business and reached my fare to the driver. Then, a few moments later, she reached her fare too. It was a 20-peso coin, so expect a change, of course. Upon passing the coin to the other passengers, she yelled, "Kuya, Taft lang po", and I noticed almost everyone in the jeep got a little confused. Like, gurl, you're literally on freaking Taft WDYM??? Sana ol sa ibang universities na maayos enrollment, may perks sa online class at may kalidad pa rin ang magiging edukasyon kahit blended/online learning. Oo state university ang pup kaya gipit at di ganun ka-sosyal di gaya ng ibang univ. Pero piyups din naman state university ah at ok naman ang enrollment, pati perks at plano nila para sa online/blended learning.

 I don't know to even start this. Ito ang unang beses na gusto kong ibahagi 'yung bigat sa dibdib ko sa ibang tao kasi pakiramdam ko hindi ako kayang maintindihan ng mga taong malapit sakin mismo. Naalala ko 'yung lines sa isang movie na mas maganda daw magkwento sa isang estranghero. They don't know you. They judge, pero hindi ka naman nila kilala o minsan wala silang pakialam sa iyo HAHAHAHAHA I am from PUP, pero bago 'yun, sa probinsya namin ako nag-aral. All goes well. Maayos 'yung naging pag-aaral ko, maayos 'yung relationship ko sa mga magulang ko, but I don't know...I am not even sure kung kelan nagbago 'yung pakikitungo nila samin ng kapatid ko. Honor student siya, consistent, while I took my education seriously during Grade 10, and katulad niya, simula noon ay pareho na kaming nasa honor list. Proud sila sa kaniya, sobrang proud na minsan naiinggit ako kaya nag-aral ako ng mabuti para pantayan siya. They had never been proud of me, pero kuntento ako na nasa graduation ko sila, na nandun si Papa kasi I looked up at him. Gustong-gusto ko siyang ipagmalaki ako , pero alam mo 'yun? 'Yung taong akala mo hindi ka sasaktan, kayang-kaya ka palang pagbuhatan ng kamay. Aware naman tayo doon sa lockdown na ipinatupad ng Government gawa sa virus, we've been on Manila for 3 months sa Quezon sa bahay ng Lolo ko. Doon kami nag-stay, and that time I have a boyfriend, LDR relationship. I'd been on a relationship before, pero ito yung isa sa mga naging boyfriend ko na nagagawa kong kausapin habang nandun siya, he is A. Palagi kaming nag-uusap, unlike me, graduate na siya, at mayroon ng work sa Dubai. Masaya kami. Hindi naman kaso sa akin ang malayo, and I muster the courage na sabihin, at ipaalam kay Papa ang tungkol sa kaniya. As a father naiintindihan ko na strikto siya, na ayaw niya kay A, pero to the extent na gusto niyang humingi ako ng pera? I am not that kind of person, as a matter of fact, hindi naman ako ganoong tao, hindi ako nanghihingi ng kahit ano, material or what sa mga naging boyfriend ko kasi mas gusto ko na ako 'yung nagsisikap para makuha 'yung isang bagay. Yes, nakatanggap ako ng mga masasakit na salita. Aaminin ko na nasasagot ko siya minsan kasi sobra na, pero yung time na umiyak ako, nung pagbuhatan niya ako ng kamay, and all I have that time was myself. My father punched me, ewan ko, hindi naman ako iyakin, pero kusang tumulo ang luha ko that time. Nung gabing mangyari yun, ang daming sinabi niya na halos isumpa niya ako. Nalaman ng Tita ko nung makahanap ako ng tyempo na i-lock 'yung pinto ng bahay kasi nasa labas siya. Hindi ko siya pinagbuksan, natakot ako, pero nung kumatok si Tita, at nagtanong kasi nagwawala si Papa sa labas, kumalma ako kasi nandun naman siya. I told her, umiiyak na sinabi ko sa kaniya 'yung nangyare, pero ni hindi niya ako tinanong kung ayos lang ba ako, kung gusto ko bang matulog doon kasama si Papa. Tumalikod siya, at umalis.Umiyak ako, nalaman ng kapatid ko hanggang sa umabot kay Mama. Umiyak sila, at nagalit. Ni hindi siya nagsorry, parang walang nangyare. Fastforward, nakauwi kami sa probinsya. Akala ko nga hanggang doon na lang 'yun, pero nagkamali ako. He did not hurt me physically now, pero kung may pagkakataon, at wala si Mama? Hindi ko masabi. Hindi ko alam kung kanino ako magkukwento, nasanay ako na kinikimkim lahat ng bigat. Iiyak, then all will be okay soon. Pero ang bigat-bigat kasi akala ko si Mama yung isa sa mag kakampi ko, but same issue goes. Minsan tinatanong ko sa sarili ko, if somebody asked to pay for me, ibebenta kaya nila ako? Hindii ko masabi sa boyfriend ko ang dahilan kung bakit nagsisikap ako na maghanao ng trabaho, at makaipon. Ipinangako ko sa sarili ko na lalayo ako. Kapag kaya ko, gusto kong lumayo. Sila yung nagda-down samin, naikalat na nga nila na sa tuwing di namin ginagawa gusto nila na ang sama-sama namin, na masyado na kaming mapagmataas. Everyone thought we are. halos lahat ng kamag-anak namin, ng kakilala iyon ang naging tingin. Minsan ng umiyak sa harapan ko 'yung kapatid ko, at alam mo 'yun? Ang sakit, pero ni hindi ako makaiyak. There are times na naiisip ko, if I die tapos nagiwan ako ng sulat, mare-realize kaya nila 'yun? HAHAHAHAHAHA I wanted to kill mysef yesterday. I did not cry, wala akong makausap. Wala akong masabihan, ang bigat na sobra, sobra sobra. Nagugupo ako, pero gusto ko muna siyang ilabas ngayon sa inyo. Salamat kahit di ko kayo kilala.

#PUPFreedomWall7810
 
 What if those things that make us happy also make us sad? Friendship should add up to your happiness, right? But what if it also adds up to your anxiety? 
 
 Nung junior high school ako, I didn't make a lot of friends. Actually, I was a loner. Sobrang tahimik at napakamahiyain ko kasi nun. Even nung elementary pa lang ako, wala rin akong naaalalang naging kaibigan. Pag kakain ako tuwing recess o uuwi, mag-isa lang lagi. Meron naman paminsan-minsan, isa o dalawa ganun. Pero pawala-wala rin yung mga yun kasi pag kailangan lang nandyan. Hanggang siguro nung nag-moving up may isa lang akong natatandaan na nag-stick talaga sakin. Tapos yung worst pa nun is yung lagi akong nakakalimutan o walang kagroup tuwing may group projects. Lagi ko yung iniiyak tuwing uuwi ako pababa dun sa school ko. 
 
 Then nung nag-senior high school na ako, I decided I want to change myself. Gusto kong magkaroon ng kaibigan. I knew that I could do more. Masipag naman ako at kahit papaano kaya kong maging leader, so I tried to build up myself and stand up in the class. I even became one of the top students. There, I made a lot of friends. Yung dating nakakalimutan lang sa mga groupings, ngayon pinag-aagawan na sa groupings. Ang saya ko lang nun kasi sa wakas nakita na yung worth ko. Pero at the back of my mind, I always question those friendships. Kaibigan ba talaga nila ako o kaibigan nila ako dahil may pakinabang ako? Hindi ko alam kung nag-ooverthink lang ba ako or what pero alam ko naman na some of them are good friends. Di ko lang talaga maiwasan minsan na mag-isip ng ganito, "What if hindi ako matalino? What if hindi ako kapaki-pakinabang? Magkakaroon kaya ako ng kaibigan?" Nanatili yung tanong na yun sakin hanggang sa grumaduate ako. 
 
 Ngayong college, things happened that change my perspective of friendships. I have friends but, I only let few people in. You know, in college, you can't trust everyone lalo na siguro sa course namin. Pero ayun, I realized na never pala akong nagkaroon ng deep connection with friends before. Never pa pala akong nagkakaroon ng best friend. When I was in senior high, my friends never have known me in a deeper level. We only connect with our common interests and when something bad happens to me, I only keep it to myself kasi ayokong makita nila yung worst ko. Pero ayun nga, college happened and I've craved for deeper connections. Narealize ko yun dahil sobrang stressful sa course namin at minsan nagiging toxic na, I needed someone to be there for me when I was down and vice versa. Gusto ko rin maging home person ng kaibigan ko. By then, I evaluated all my friends. The 2 constant friends that I have right now seemed to be my best friends. Kasi diba, andami na naming pinagsamahan, I can be honest and open sa kanila which I never did before, they were also there during my down moments, and for me they were the best or so I thought. 
 
 Diba ganun na yun? Best friends na dapat yung ganun? Kasi sa iba automatic na yun, diba? Pero it turned out na para sa isang katulad ko, hindi pala. For them, I am not their best friend. Sobrang sakit. I assumed that we were best friends kaya ako nasaktan. Bakit kaya sa iba madali lang magkaroon ng ganun, bakit pag sa akin sobrang hirap at sobrang sakit? Dahil ba late bloomer ako sa friendships? Ang daming tanong sa isipan ko. Ang purpose ko lang ba bilang kaibigan ay tulungan kayo sa mga bagay na nahihirapan kayo? Ganun na lang ba talaga yung pakinabang ko? National Best friends day ko yun nalaman, I mentioned them in a post and they never responded but it's fine for me. Pero nung araw na yun, nagkaroon rin kami ng away at doon ko nalaman kung ano ba ako sa isa sa kanila. I asked my friend, "Ano ba ako sa'yo?" Then I received this cold answer, "Close friends." That answer really broke my heart into pieces. That time rin nagluluksa pa ako dahil naeliminate pa ako sa course ko kaya doble doble yung sakit. Iyak lang ako ng iyak nung gabing yun. Even yung isa ko pang friend, I questioned her of our friendship kasi baka napilitan lang siya sakin na best friend ang turing ko sa kanila. 
 
 To cut the story short, I am still friends with them though. I don't want to lose a friend kaya I still keep them around. Tsaka ayoko rin mang-iwan. Kasi it seemed para sa kanila, mababaw lang ito. I confronted them with the pain that I was feeling but to resolve things among us, I kept this pain aside para maging kaibigan ko parin sila. They are good friends, though kaya siguro okay na ako sa ganito. Pero ito rin yung reason bakit ako umiiyak gabi gabi. All of a sudden, my worth is not appreciated again. Because of this, nahihirapan na ako magtiwala at mag-open up sa ibang tao. Takot na ako. Sila lang kasi yung kaya kong pagsabihan ng kahit ano. Sila lang yung nakakilala sakin ng buong-buo. Yung walang halong pagpapanggap. Tapos ganito pa. Minsan nga nagseselos ako sa mga long-time friends or best friends nila pero kailangan ko itago yung pagseselos na yun eh. Hindi naman kasi clear ang lugar ko sa buhay nila. Kaya siguro magpapaubaya nalang talaga ako. Haysss.
 
 Ngayon, dahil nakakasalamuha ko pa sila dahil sa school, I need to act normal around them. Na walang nagbago sa friendship namin. Masaya naman ako sa kanila pero deep inside nasasaktan na ako. I don't know what to do anymore. Hindi ko alam kung ano ba ang mas okay, ang walang kaibigan o manatili sa ganito kakomplikadong friendship. Pero mahal na mahal ko yung dalawang yun kaya ayoko talaga silang iwan. Mahal ko sila pero ang sakit sakit na.
 
 Sorry kung ang haba at ang messy ng confession ko katulad ng buhay ko. Hindi ko alam kung ano ang gusto kong mangyari sa confession na ito. Kung kailangan ko ba ng advice or what. Pero siguro okay na lang ako sa pag-confess ko rito para maibsan itong bigat sa puso ko kasi pakiramdam ko, itong sakit sa puso ko ang papatay sakin.
 
 PUP Branch
 
 Submitted: October 30, 2020 2:06:22 PM +08

Bukod sa minsan may mga nagsasabing wala na silang pera, which is obvious, marami ginagawan talaga ng paraan makasunod lang sa mga requirements. Meron iba napapansin ko hindi na rin kumakain ng maayos kasi magkakano lang ang pera sa bulsa.
 
 Nakakalungkot lang kasi may ibang prof (madalas fulltime) na kapag magdemand sa project akala mo privileged mga students nila. Hindi marunong magset ng budget for a project, hindi rin marunong magcanvass muna. Meron pang iba may paregalo pa dapat. 
  
 Yes mababa ang sweldo ng prof sa PUP. Pero hindi naman excuse ang ganoon para magpadonate ng mga projects na libo ang halaga. Hindi ko alam ano gagawin nila doon, pero sigurado ako na hindi nila talaga afford ang mga materials na iyon. 
 
 I left PUP with these impression sa mga profs nila; maraming nagsasamantala sa kahirapan, marami rin ang nagbabadya dahill kailangan ng mga studyante ng maayos na grades. Nakakahiya. 
 
 Although may mga naging kaibigan akong prof na maayos at matitino, pero bihirang bihira; halos bilang sa daliri sa isang kamay.

is the jeepney phaseout in the philippines ethical? explore the issue through the lenses of natural law and utilitarian ethics in our latest advocacy video.
the issue of phasing out jeepneys in the philippines has become a highly controversial matter, with differing opinions and views on this subject. the withdrawal of the right to livelihood for jeepney drivers and their families can be considered as a violation of natural law ethics. however, from the perspective of utilitarian ethics, the phaseout may be seen as a necessary step towards modernizing public transportation and reducing air pollution.  providing jeep drivers with alternative livelihood options and financial support to help them transition to more sustainable modes of transport could be a possible solution to this ethical dilemma. in the end, when deciding on decisions which affect society as a whole, consideration must be given to both individual rights and their greater benefit.

Jeepneys  are more than just a means of transportation. It holds a special place in the hearts of Filipinos, representing their resilience and ingenuity. They serve as a symbol of the Filipino spirit, embodying the values of community, resourcefulness, and unity.  Most importantly, jeepneys are the source of income for dedicated drivers to provide for their families. We, the students of 11-Mango , aim to preserve the long-term viability of jeepney drivers‚Äô income in addition to providing affordable transportation that benefits both the drivers and passengers. Through this, the iconic and culturally significant role of jeepneys in Philippine society will be preserved and appreciated.  They will be acknowledged not just as a means of transportation but also as symbolic representations of the country's heritage and sense of community.

for nearly 80 years now, the jeepney, a public utility vehicle, has been the reigning king of philippine roads. no wonder, it is often referred to as the ‚Äúhari ng kalsada‚Äù. but today, the king faces a detrimental challenge --- it is scared to be left behind and replaced by a more modern king.
in june 2017, the government designed an initiative to streamline and organize the country‚Äôs public road transportation system, known as the public utility vehicle modernization program (puvmp). it is crafted for a safer and regulated means of transportation. this program was supposed to be implemented in 2020 but got delayed because of the pandemic.
some features of this modernization program include the consolidation of not less than 15 jeepneys to create a corporation or cooperative and have it registered to ltfrb to be granted a franchise, for them to still function as public transport. moreover, vehicles older than 15 years are no longer allowed to register as puvs, to ensure up-to-date transport. the government urged the surrender of their puvs and promised to give financial assistance to acquire a new modern puv, which roughly costs between 1-3 million pesos.
jeepney drivers and operators surely make a thousand or two per day, and you might think it is not so bad. but consider the fuel price, food, tuition, electricity, water, and even boundary if they do not personally own the vehicle. how much is left from driving since sunrise until midnight? and now, they are asked to spend a million for a modern jeepney - how are they going to pay for it?
hence, after president ferdinand marcos, jr. declared that the phase-out will still continue, different organizations and even jeepney operators themselves proceeded with a rally in different places and urged the government to hear their sentiments and cries. many have also used their social media platforms for everyone to be aware of this issue and tell the government to consider the status of everyone.
moreover, this jeepney phase-out is also a big slap to our culture and heritage. jeepneys are always part of the culture of this country, showcasing the colorful and filipino-ness designs of each jeep, embodying our resilience. the everyday encounter in these vehicles mostly shows the "bayanihan" especially in passing on the fare from one passenger to another until it reaches the driver. these cultures will be burned to ashes if jeepneys are not seen on the roads again.
we appreciate the intent behind this program because who would not want a safer, more comfortable, and modernized public transport? who does not like modernization and to be globally competitive in terms of transportation? of course, no one! we all want to get modernized and not to get left behind with the fast-pacing world. but how about the poor filipino people who rely on their food, education, healthcare, and such, for every single cent they get from driving a jeepney? how about those commuters who can only afford to pay some cent even if it means waiting in a long queue? what about the filipino workers who rely on their living and survival in these jeepneys?
always remember, there was always a time in your life where a jeepney driver fetched and accompanied you to a place where your heart needed to go. sometimes, even saved you and still dropped you off at your home when you got but nothing in your pocket. the jeepneys are a big part of our lives, even without realizing it.
now that they are the ones who are in need of us, are we going to leave them behind or still wait for them even though the queue to modernization will now take much longer? you decide.

~Horror story time ~
*My first time writing one

In the eerie stillness of the De La Salle University (DLSU) campus on a moonless Halloween night, a chilling fog began to roll in from the nearby Taft Avenue. The dimly lit pathways, usually bustling with students, were now shrouded in an unsettling silence.

As the clock struck midnight, a ghostly figure dressed in an old tattered La Salle uniform emerged from the shadows, wandering aimlessly near the St. La Salle Hall. Its hollow eyes stared into the windows of empty classrooms, where ghostly chalk marks on the blackboards seemed to write themselves.

Near the Bro. Connon Hall, a spectral basketball team, frozen in a never-ending game, dribbled the ball with echoing footsteps that reverberated through the corridors. The scoreboard remained stuck at 66-66, a perpetual tie, as if time itself had frozen during this cursed match.

The library, usually a place of quiet study, now housed a spectral librarian who whispered cryptic messages to those brave enough to enter. They spoke of forbidden knowledge and ancient tomes hidden beneath the campus.

In the quadrangle, a phantom marching band played eerie melodies, their instruments producing ghostly notes that sent shivers down the spine of anyone who dared to listen.

As the night wore on, the campus itself seemed to come alive with restless spirits, each one having a tale of woe, unfinished business, or a curse that bound them to this hallowed ground.

Anyone who ventured into DLSU on this Halloween night would be wise to beware, for the horrors of the past and the unquiet spirits of the present had converged in a hauntingly macabre symphony that only the bravest souls would survive. Mwehehehe

 Lumaki akong nasa akin lang ang atensyon at pagmamahal ng magulang ko, nag-iisa lang ako. Hindi sila nakapagtapos pero nabibigay nila ang mga kailangan at gusto ko. Maalaga sila sakin. Kaya lumaki rin akong mapagmahal sa mga malalapit at mahal ko sa buhay. Namana ko rin sa tatay ko ang maramdamin at masyadong malambot na puso. Noong lumaki na ako tsaka ko narealize na nahihirapan pala akong i-express ang nararamdaman ko. Nahihirapan nga ba? O sadyang hindi lang ako naiintindihan ng mga tao sa paligid ko? Kaya parang nadala ko nalang na kimkimin ang mga problema ko dahil sa mga trauma ko. Dahil pag nag-oopen up ako, parang nagiging mali at masama pa ako sa tingin ng ibang tao.
 Nagkaboyfriend ako sa legal age. At masasabi kong tama iyon dahil walang naging hadlang. Open kami sa family. Pero may agwat ang mga edad namin. Estudyante palang ako at siya nagtatrabaho na. Matured na matured na ang pag-iisip niya. More on earning,saving. Nasa tunay nang reyalidad. Simula nung nagquarantine, doon ko nadiskubre ang dark side niya. Naiintindihan ko naman kung gano katoxic ang trabaho niya at di ko kinuha ang mga oras para makapagpahinga siya. Pero pansin ko parang di na ganun yung affection and support gaya nung una. Alam ko naman. Hindi lang puro sweet and happy sa relationship pero ngayong quarantine? Hindi naman nakakasakit ang lambing man lang? Lalo na hindi naman nakakapagkita? Oo hindi lang naman sakin umiikot ang mundo niya pero yung kasiyahan nalang yun? Na maibibigay niya?.Pero ang lagi niyang sinasabi, sa personal siya. Kaya inunawa ko kahit nakakalungkot. Pero pati sa ibang bagay nagbago na rin. Dahil nga mature siya, tila ba lahat ng problema ko mababaw lang. At bumalik yung trauma ko na kapag nag oopen up ako, parang maling mali ang mga ginawa o nararamdaman ko kahit gusto ko lang namang magrant at wala naman akong natatapakang iba. Kaya naglihim ako sa kaniya. Sinarili ko lahat ng problema ko. At nagbunga yun ng depression. Nagalit siya sakin nung nalaman niyang nakakapagsabi ako sa iba pero sa kaniya hindi. Alam ko namang may mali rin ako dahil boyfriend ko siya pero ang hirap at natakot akong mag open up sa kaniya. Lalo pa na parang nararamdaman kong napakababaw lang nun sa tingin niya.I tried to open up once more. Sinabi ko na ganito ako. Hindi ako ganun ka immature pero alam niya naman kung gaano ako kasensitive. Tumatanggap ako ng pagmamatuwid pero yung approach niya kasi iba.Malawak pang-unawa ko pero nagsisimula palang ako, hindi ko pa naabot ang pinakareyalidad sa buhay. At sana maunawaan niyang ugali ko to. Likas akong madamdamin. And it turns out, na nagrarason lang ako. Excuses to think na tama ako. Yun ang tingin niya. Masakit. Sobrang sakit malaman yun sa lalaking mahal mo. Na inaasahan mong uunawain ka at pupulutin sa panahong hindi mo na alam gagawin mo. Pero instead ako pa pala tong mali, for being "me".
 That time I lost my tiny bit of hope. Gusto ko nalang mamatay instantly. Pero ako to. Ako parin nag adjust, inunawa ko parin at nagpakumbaba ng loob. Narealize ko, hindi ko na kailangang patunayan na ganito ako para maintindihan nila at mahalin,tanggapin. Galit,lungkot, lito, pero unti unti magpapalakas ako. Papatunayan kong hindi ako bata gaya ng tingin nila, papatunayan ko na kahit madamdamin ako, kaya ko paring maging matapang. Pero ipapanalangin ko parin, na sana intindihin niya na ganito ang ugali ko-madamdamin, malambot, gaya ng pag-intindi ko sa ugali niya.
